review_headline: I have tried several DE razor brands but have come to realize that I love this DE razor above all the others
review_body: Over the years, I have tried several DE razor brands but have come to realize that I love this DE razor above all the others. The handle is the right length and changing blades is extremely easy. I also don't mind that it is a little heavier than my old DE razor. For those new to DE razors I offer this suggestion, experiment with different razor blade brands, since everyone's face is different. Don't just go with the sharpest blades on the market just because you might fall for the misconception that sharper will equal a closer shave. Also, it will take several shaving attempts before mastering the technique. There are websites out there that can help you perfect your technique and prevent your face from getting chewed up by the razor.

product_title: Silk'n Blue Acne Solution Device
review_body:
I ordered the Silk 'n Blue Acne Solution Device with my fourteen-year-old granddaughter in mind. She is sufferng, like so many young teens, from periodic outbreaks of acne. She and I sat down and opened the box. Inside were the acne device, a cord, a charging device, and a small booklet of instructions in English and a couple of other languages. Both she and I read the instructions. Just inside the front cover is a page of Quick Start Instructions which we both read. The first thing they said to do was plug the charger into the wall and place the device on the charger for 6 to 8 hours. I wouldn't call that a quick start. But we followed the instructions and then went out shopping and had lunch. After we ate, we found a couple of cute summer outfits. That worked to my grand-daughter's advantage. When we got back, she went in and washed her face with plain old soap and water. There was plenty of time for her skin to dry. The charging time was still not up. She and I waited some more. The lesson here is don't expect to be able to use this thing as soon as you open the package. Plan ahead. We didn't.

The 6-hour wait was over and we pressed the on/off switch. A green light flickered to life and finally stayed on. Ready for action. My granddaughter's blemishes were concentrated on her forehead and chin, so those were the areas she concentrated on with the Blue. The LED light was on and she held the Blue against the skin on her forehead for a little over 3 minutes. She found the head of the device was getting pretty warm. She moved the head of the Blue to another place on her forehead every 3 to 4 minutes. She thought the heat was getting pretty warm. She applied the Blue to about 8 areas on her forehead and 3 areas on her chin. It took about 40 minutes to get around to all the areas that had blemishes. She was through for the evening. The Blue was returned to the charger so it would be ready the next morning. After the Blue had been on the charger for another6 hours, I removed it as I had read in the comments not to leave it on after it was fully charged.

The directions said to use the Blue twice a day for 6- to 8-weeks to start and to repeat the treatments twice a week for maintenance. The maintenance schedule seems reasonable but getting there seems to be a real hike to me. Lucky for my granddaughter, it's summer vacation but to keep up that starting schedule during the rest of the year would be difficult.

She managed pretty well through almost 4 weeks of treatments but she was definitely flagging in her enthusiasm. The treatments, lasting at least an half-hour each, twice a day, were taking up an awful lot of time, time she would have preferred doing other things. Fortunately, she was showing some fairly decent results with her skin. Maintenance arrived just in time, or I think she may have given up.

Her skin has been fairly clear now for a couple of weeks and she has been doing the maintenance schedule. I hope she can keep up once school starts again. We discussed the ratings for this device and she felt the amount to time necessary, especially at the beginning, was a real problem. She liked the results aside from the rare new blemish. I thought the time spent charging and getting the Blue off the charger so it didn't overcharge was a pain. All in all, we decided that 3 stars were just about right. The results were pretty good but it took an awful lot of effort to get there.

product_title: Light Mountain Natural Color The Gray! Hair Color & Conditioner, Auburn, 7 oz (197 g) (Pack of 2)
review_body: I have purchased this product twice now and love it!  It is natural and cruelty-free.  The auburn comes out nice on my brown hair.  However this second time that I have used the product, my hair was not as soft as the first batch.  It could be that I did not use as much heat. I used saran wrap along with the plastic bag that comes with the package and it keep most of it from running down my face and neck.  I would also suggest using latex gloves rather than the gloves that come with the kit.  I added paprika and olive oil to stage 2 mixture and allowed both mixtures to sit 2-3 hours before applying.  Colors the grey very well, but difficult to get those stubborn sideburn ones.  Thanks for a great product and will buy again!

product_title: Ariam Beauty Vitamin C Serum Instinctual for Beautiful Youthful Face 20% Vitamin C&E Hyaluronic Acid Serum Nutrient Rich Anti Aging Anti Wrinkle Serum.
review_headline: Great Vitamin C serum for anti aging or sensitive skin.
review_body:
Packaged in a 1 ounce dark brown glass bottle with a pump top. The brown bottle will help prevent oxidation of the Vitamin C, since the Vitamin C in this product is Ascorbic Acid, (better for antiaging), SAP Vitamin C is the kind of Vitamin C in most Vitamin C serums, but it is really better for acne prone skin, but it used more since it is more stable. The serum is really a firm clear gel and has no smell I can detect. 2 pumps and it is enough for your entire face. Absorbs very fast, leave no oil or residue, and no irritation.

I have used it 3 days morning and night and it makes my skin feel wonderful, soft and smooth. It has helped with the bags under my eyes and the firmness is a touch better also. Lines and crows feet are more moisturized and filling in a bit. Can't see any difference in dark spots yet, not had enough time, but the skin tone is starting to be a lot more even in general. I have a redness in my cheeks, capillaries close to the skin and this has helped with that also. Since I have had no irritation it is a keeper for me, I have sensitive skin and a lot of products don't work for me.

This has quality ingredients, made in the USA, paraben free, cruelty free, not tested on animals and comes with a money back guarantee, so you have nothing to lose, only better skin to be revealed. Just a note, combine this with their cleanser and Vit C moisturizer and it is grand!

product_title: Crest 3D White Whitestrips Gentle Routine - Teeth Whitening Kit 28 Treatments
review_headline: True skeptic very happy with Crest 3D whitestrips.
review_body: Years back, I purchased a teeth whitening in a box.  It wasn't for sensitive teeth. My teeth got noticed, but I would get some pretty good zingers and decided, it just wasn't worth it. I have a front left tooth dental implant which was matched to my teeth long ago. I have noticed for some time now that my other front tooth looked shades off from the implant. I was hesitant on buying Crest 3d White Whitestrips Gentle Routine because I read comments where it "took too long," "Didn't see a difference." I thought that I would give it a try because it was better than nothing and I certainly wasn't going to get the regular brand that caused pain. Today is day 16 of using them. All of my teeth that I used the product on match my dental implant exactly. So there is my proof that this product did work. I am such a SKEPTIC! I will say though that I used it every day for an hour a day for 16 days. Also, I don't drink anything but spring water and I use milk on my cereal. Once in a great while I will have a Ginger Ale when I go out to eat. So even though my teeth were a few shades off from my implant after years of not treating them, my teeth were not stained with coffee, tea, or smoke. Not sure if I would have gotten these results as I did this quickly if my teeth were stained. I'm sure it would have taken a lot longer. I am going to stop using this every day now because there is no need too. I have plenty left to use once a week for maintenance.  I will definitely buy this again. Bottom line, this product does work.

product_title: Tarte Amazonian Clay Double Detox Exfoliating Facial Mask 2.64 oz
review_body:
This product claims to do two things: exfoliate and also act as a mask to detoxify. First off, as an exfoliater, it works pretty well. It smooths out any uneven patches without being so rough as to irritate, which is a big deal when you have sensitive skin like I do. Secondly, the mask part of the product feels amazing. You can feel your pores tighten and when you rinse it off, your skin feels smooth and looks healthy. Really my only two complaints with this product is I wish it did a better job at getting rid of black heads and I wish they actually fully filled up the container. You pay about $40-$50 and when you squeeze you can tell there's a lot of extra air.

In general, I think this is great for anyone that has oily or combination skin and has acne. I have combination and acne and I can always tell a difference when I use it. Just make sure to use moisturizer afterwards because the clay does soak up oil really well.

product_title: Jerome Russell Hair Color Thickener 3.5oz (Pack of 3)
review_headline: Great at covering up bald spots; however, hairspray is a must
review_body:
Using this spray-on has become a daily routine in order to cover up the bald spot that I have on my crown area.

There is a slight learning curve in order to effectively use the spray-on. What I had to learn was that a little spritz goes a long way. Just a slight two second spray on your needed scalp area is all that is needed then take a comb or brush and spread to the other areas that need to be covered.

I have to take off one star, though, because the smell of this product is very strong and more on the unpleasant side.

If you are going to use this product, you need to go purchase some hairspray. The hairspray will act in two ways: in order to make the product not leak all over you head and flake on your clothes, and to cover up the smell of the spray-on.

product_title: Wahl Professional 5-Star Balding Clipper #8110 â Great for Barbers and Stylists â Cuts Surgically Close for Full Head Balding â Twice the Speed of Pivot Motor Clippers â Accessories Included
review_headline: From an actual user: they are awesome.
review_body:
First of all, I've actually used this on now.. 5 occasions. First time, I had a family member do it, then I've used it on my own skull since.

It works excellently. the blades are sharp, the only thing I've nicked is the single tiny bump i had on my head (which is now gone, thanks to the clipper), and takes my hair down to about a days' growth. I READ THE MANUAL, because the majority of negative reviews I found on it stated that it cut peoples' scalps a lot. I assume this is because the blades weren't shipped with correct adjustments. Fortunately, mine came shipped just fine (the simple instructions are IN THE MANUAL), and I didn't need to tweak them at all - the cutting blades are a mere <1mm behind the bottom blade, as it should be to get a close shave.

Ya, they're a bit heavier than other clippers, but it doesn't get hot, it runs well, is very well built, the cord is tough and quite long, and the box is suitable as a case.

I decided to stop shaving my face and instead shave my head, and with this clipper, I can shave my head to near-baby smooth in less time than it took to shave my face with my rotary shaver.

As with any close cuts, it's best to wrap a hot towel around your head to soften up the skin. You won't carve yourself up if you shave without this step, but it makes the process a bit easier and gives a slightly closer shave. IOt also works very well on cleaning up my beardline.

So if you want to get VERY close to razor-close shaves, get this thing. I used two different 'regular' clippers on my head while waitign for this one to arrive, and this little machine is quite worth the purchase.

product_title: Alaffia Beautiful Curls Curl Activating Shea Butter Shampoo, 12 oz
review_body:
I just bought a bottle of this from Whole Foods. I noticed that the Alaffia people have added phenoxyethanol to this product. It did not
used to be in curl reviving tonic. I am surprised and disappointed that they put it in. It is known to be toxic. I wrote the company and told
them my feelings about this. If many people would complain, they would probably take it out.
See the following for a commentary.

Phenoxyethanol is a glycol ether. Glycols are a series of chemicals that find their way into all sorts of things: paint, lacquer, jet fuel..... Phenoxyethanol is used as an anti-bacterial in cosmetics as well as a stabilizer in perfume.

The product's Material Safety Data Sheet (MSDS) says that it phenoxyethanol is harmful if swallowed, inhaled or absorbed through the skin and that it can cause reproductive damage. The MSDS refers to 100% concentrations, so is it safe at lower doses? In cosmetics the concentrations are typically 0.5% to 1%.

There are several animal studies that demonstrate that it is toxic - with effects on the brain and the nervous system - at moderate concentrations. In Japan, there is a concentration limit for its use in cosmetics. In Europe, the European Union classifies it as an irritant and there are various studies (on rabbit skin, for example) that demonstrate reactions at low doses. The EPA (Environmental Protection Agency) data sheets show chromosomal changes and genetic mutation effects in testing as well as testicular atrophy and interference with reproductivity in mice.

I also came across a report written by a medical professional who contracted allergies after coming into contact with phenoxyethanol in a detergent used for cleaning lab equipment. It seems he wasn't a fluke. There are over 3,000 known allergans and they were studied, along with the data from 9,948 patients, by a research team in Germany. Phenoxyethanol was in the top 10. An Italian study also determined that phenoxyethanol is a contact allergan. However, a 1990 article in the Journal of the American College of Toxicology said that it was only a mild irritant to rabbit skin at 2%.

Concern that phenoxyethanol is a neurotoxin precedes the FDA. German research in 1999, concluded that it had neurotoxin potential.

Phenoxyethanol breaks down to phenol and acetaldehyde, acetaldehyde converts to acetate. Phenol can disable the immune system's primary response mechanism. Given that, it is at best ironic, that phenoxyethanol is used as an anti-bacterial in vaccines. Acetaldehyde occurs during the breakdown of ethanol, (alchohol and 2-phenoxyETHANOL), it is a suspected carcinogen. Inhalation studies have shown irritation of the eyes, skin, and respiratory tract.

product_title: Best Precision Nail Clipper With Rotating Swivel Head - Great For Thick Nails - Extra Sharp Stainless Steel Clippers For Men Or Women
review_headline: They work and save me a lot of money.
review_body: When I was a young kid on a farm some 70 years ago, (I'm 84 now) my toes were frostbitten.  They managed to save my toes but all of my nails turned black and came off.  When they grew back in they were at least twice as thick and highly curved so that I couldn't clip them in a normal fashion with either type of nail clippers (regular clippers or the side nipper variety).  To do so would cause the nail to flatten out and cut into the flesh of my toes.  I had to go to a podiatrist about every three months and they don't work cheap.  He would first numb my toes and then clip them.  This worked but it caused wounds on each side of each nail that had to be dealt with.  To trim my nails at home requires at least six nips per toe, a feat that was impossible with regular clippers and I no longer have the strength in my hands to use the side nippers.  These clippers made the job at least possible, if not easy.  If I would improve them I would make the jaws open just a little more and add another inch to the handles for more leverage but such an animal doesn't exist.  Until they do, these work fine.

product_title: Seacret Age-Defying face restore serum 30ml
review_headline: Don't buy into the Dead Sea hype!
review_body:
(I actually purchased this product, with others, from a kiosk in my local mall. If you buy Seacret skincare, please take my advice and buy it online instead-the prices are much more reasonable. I think they charged me over $100 at their mall location-I really should have checked online first, but I got suckered in by the salesperson's schpiel. Derp. Plus, the kiosks will not accept returns, even if you haven't opened the product-the one I went to had no signs or anything advertising this policy-it was in tiny print at the bottom of the sales receipt, which of course you aren't given until the sale is complete. Go ahead and laugh-it definitely wasn't the brightest thing I've ever done. Lesson learned.) Now, the review:
This serum was verrrrrrry expensive, and has done nothing at all to justify its price, except break me out for the first time in twenty years. It has also clogged my pores, and milia have cropped up in some spots. I am not foolish enough to believe the claims that the salesperson made that this product line replaces things like Juvederm and Botox-nothing topical is going to get rid of wrinkles and lines-but my usual skincare brand softens any fine lines quite a bit, and brightens and evens my skin tone, and this does none of those things. My skin didn't feel hydrated, or anything but greasy after using this. The one thing I liked about it is that it is fairly lightweight, so you don't have to wait too long for it to absorb, but other than that, there is really nothing special about this serum. Once again, I will say that I have had similar results from drugstore products. Save you money!

product_title: Arm & Hammer Essentials Natural Deodorant Solid, Unscented, 2.5 Ounce
review_body:
Wrote this review before, but it looks like Arm & Hammer re-listed the item to clear out all of the bad reviews it had. Very shady. Luckily, the non-Essentials version is easier to find now that this line of deodorants bombed. Here's my original review:

I used the standard Arm & Hammer unscented for a while and liked it just fine. Then the local stores stopped carrying it in favor of the 'Essentials' version. This stuff is garbage.

For one, it's not unscented, so right there we're off to a bad start. It has a pretty rank, skunky lemony scent to it, that makes you smell like you ran out of regular deodorant and tried to use Pledge thinking no one would be the wiser. Also, this "natural" lemon scent sticks to your clothes like glue, and even after multiple washings is damn near impossible to get out. On top of that, it stained the pits of my shirts, which is a problem I never had with any other deodorant in my life.

Worst of all, this stuff gave me a pretty bad rash. I do not have sensitive skin and have never experienced a rash like this with any other hygienic products. I'm guessing they were going after the crunchy, organic crowd with this new formula and rebranding, but I don't know what kind of natural product could cause a reaction like this (besides poison ivy).

It's a shame, because I've been loyal to the Arm & Hammer brand for most of my life, but they've seriously damaged my trust in them with this terrible product. I'll be shopping around for other brands now.

product_title: Lemon Sonic Skin Cleansing System White By Xnovi
review_body:
I purchased this after reading the positive reviews.
Pros: The Lemon Sonic Skin cleansing system comes beautifully packaged with all parts in their own boxes within the main box. The instructions state that it must charge for 18 hours before first use, which I did, so don't expect to be able to use it upon arrival. It comes with 2 main brushes, 1 with harder bristles and 1 with softer bristles. The handle is ergonomic and comfortable to hold. It vibrates for a set of programmed seconds, pausing slightly so you know when to switch to cleaning a different part of your face.
Cons: Mine was defective. The Lemon Sonic (LS) fully charged after receipt and I was able to use it for a week (this equals roughly 14 minutes of use). The battery indicator light remained white and the product never beeped indicating a charge was needed. One morning I switched it on and it switched off immediately. So I fully charged it a second time. According to the directions the item is fully charged when the white indicator light is solid and not blinking. After the charge I was able to use it 3 times (total of 6 minutes) before the same "dying" process happened. Again, no beeping or red light blinking telling me that it needed charged. Thinking I must be doing something wrong, I charged the LS for another 18 hours hoping that it was user error. Nope, I used it again for 5 days (roughly 10 minutes of use) before it died again. I'm returning for a refund and purchasing a sonic system that relies on batteries.

product_title: Bumble and Bumble Grooming Creme
review_headline: I don't buy grooming creme often, but when I do it's B&b
review_body:
No affiliation with Bumble/Bumble, just having fun in my headline.

I don't have a great deal of hair, but it's dry and wavy where it exists.

Above all other products I've tried (everyday jack, malin+goetz), this is my favorite. No smell and doesn't feel like it's full of chemicals; I don't know the ingredient list so could be totally wrong...but it feels/smells better and "cleaner" than all others I've tried. I might say, "luxurious". Wow, I get my haircut at $16 barber...so it's funny that's the word I want to use to describe hair product.

This 2-ounce tube will last a year or two...so cost isn't really an issue. I use a pea-sized dollop with hair wet or damp (again, not much hair) and totally happy that my hair is soft, stays in place, and doesn't look like it has product in it.

product_title: Conair Instant Heat Volume Rollers
review_headline: Don't try them - they barely get warm and do not curl long, thick hair
review_body: These were a major disappointment. First of all, they barely heated after 15 minutes. I would have felt comfortable letting my 2 year old grandson carry them around after heating because they were just barely warm. Secondly, five rollers is not going to roll your whole head of hair unless you have extremely thin hair. So, for me, I had to roll 1/3 of my head (yes, I have lots of thick shoulder-length hair), wait to roll the next third, and wait again to roll the final third. The result of all this was a very limp, ever so slightly turned up curl which promptly fell flat in about 15 minutes even with hair spray. I saw right away that this was not going to work for me, so I returned it immediately. On the plus side, I will say that even though it didn't curl my thick frizzy hair, it did straighten it nicely and get rid of the frizz which is great if  you wanted straightened hair. I did not.

review_body:
I was just like you one time. Looking at this product, going like "what? really? all these positive reviews? and only $15?? I dunno, MAN"
Sometimes it really is that simple. Sometimes, the sheer number of raving reviews really are indication of an item's quality. This is one of those times. You're here for a reason...you want to take care of your skin. Whether it's acne, scars, hyperpigmentation, what have you. If you haven't already bought this, let me tell you why you should.

Okay first of all, CHEAP. Like, seriously? $15 with shipping? If you're like me and you've tried every product from here to Timbuktu, this should be one of the most economic treatments you've encountered. But like you, I was skeptical. In my mind, cheap = lousy. But this couldn't be farther from the truth.

This stuff is amazing. Okay, yeah, it's NOT MAGIC. Nothing out there is. It will take time and patience, and there is nothing you can do about that. Need your zits gone by this weekend? Yeah this stuff won't do that. BUT, I can tell you from experience, that this weird stinky mask WILL improve your complexion. After years of suffering acne and the inflamed wasteland that comes after, I finally see a light at the end of the tunnel.

I'm in my mid twenties, been suffering mild/aggressive acne since my early teens. Some of us are just born unlucky, and nothing will change that. But this cheap looking miracle is the first product I've tried that has actually worked CONSTANTLY. Benzoyl peroxide, AHA, crappy products advertised by pretty teenagers who've been layered by makeup and Photoshop. None of these have ever done jack for me. But this stuff? Oh boy, let me tell you.

It's kinda gross looking, and mixed with apple cider vinegar it won't smell nice. Putting it on your face, you won't look like a young starlet. As a man, it's a little embarassing to be walking around with a mask on your face. But guess what? WHO CARES. The results speak for themselves. I've been putting this on twice a day, morning and before bed (maybe excessive, but I've only seen positive changes, one must experiment) for about two weeks, always followed by a good moisturizer. I had just suffered a mammoth breakout, worse than I've had in months. This mask stopped the progression of more acne, took the damage that was already done, and slowly but surely subdued it. It's like a ninja. A slow but effective ninja. It will take time...weeks, probably months. Yes, it's a bit of a stretch if you're a long time acne sufferer to assume this mask will magically heal you in a few days' time. But give it a chance to work over the course of a few weeks, and you won't be disappointed. My red spots are fading, everyday I see a difference. The skin in-between blemishes is much cleaner and healthy looking. And whenever a zit rears its bastard face, this mask is like "NAH, not on my watch".

You're still here? Seriously? You haven't read enough of these hundreds of 5 star reviews? I'm willing to bet you've bought worse stuff than this. Expensive stuff, advertised by so called "dermatologists" and scientists. Forget all that. Buy this. Make the commitment to use it as much as you need. Mix a bunch, put it in some airtight tupperware. Put this crap on once a day, couple times a week, whatever you can do. With discipline, your fight against acne will be reinforced by this vigorous cavalry. And for me personally, I finally feel that the war is turning in my favor. DO IT.for themselves. Expensive stuff, advertised by so called "dermatologists" and scientists. Forget all that. Buy this. Make the commitment to use it as much as you need. Mix a bunch, put it in some airtight tupperware. Put this crap on once a day, couple times a week, whatever you can do. With discipline, your fight against acne will be reinforced by this vigorous cavalry. And for me personally, I finally feel that the war is turning in my favor. DO IT.

product_title: Leegoal Electric Manicure Nail Drill File Grinder Grooming Kit,Pink
review_headline: A few disadvantages but worth it...
review_body: This definitely comes in handy when doing acrylic nails, it gets the job done but there are a few disadvantages about this product.  First, the top part that comes off to replace the battery doesn't screw on in a secure locked position so it tends to pop off during usage. Second, there are two  file heads that work a little bit too good sometimes. The main filer & the one that is identical but a little smaller that files the edges & around the cuticle, you have to be very careful not to press hard while using it or you could file right thru ur whole nailbed..... OUCH!! So no need to really apply pressure whIle you're filing with either one. The one file head I really think works the best is the silver all metal sharp one for going under the nail to get any extra acrylic that might have hardened in the wrong spots & shaping/cutting down the cuticle & removing any overgrown cuticle off the nailbed. I would like to know what's the purpose of each filer head & how to clean them after each use without messing them up.

product_title: Mitchum Advanced Control Unscented Gel, Anti-Perspirant & Deodarant 3.4 oz (Pack of 5)
review_body:
I liked the old Mitchum gel, but this new version is terrible. As the other reviewers have noted, the good reviews are for the previous generation of this product.

The new product is so watery that it leaks all over, running down the sides of the container when you roll even a small amount out to be applied. This gets on your hands, your bathroom counter, etc. and is hard to wash off.

Making matters worse, while the old container actually had a cap with 3 bumps on the inside that plugged the three applicator holes through which the product is dispensed, the new container has dozens of holes and the cap does nothing to keep the watery gel inside. So forget packing it in your gym bag or suitcase--you'll find it everywhere: a good amount stuck up in the cap and more anywhere else it can spread.

I will never buy this product again.

product_title: Colgate Enamel Health Toothpaste
review_headline: Brush Brush: A Colgate Clean Mint Enamel Health Whitening Toothpaste Review
review_body:
The Colgate clean mint enamel health whitening toothpaste is designed to care for your teeth while making them stronger and whiter. This toothpaste helps replenish weak enamel areas with natural calcium.

I spoke to my dental hygienist about whitening toothpastes. She said effective whitening requires a prescription strength solution. Whitening toothpastes have limited effect and may make teeth more sensitive. The whitening products, in a way, mimic a cleaning and only remove surface staining. Additionally, she indicated whitening toothpastes may reduce the shine on veneers, making them appear dull and lifeless.

The Colgate clean mint enamel health whitening toothpaste works the same as any other toothpaste on the market. I get my teeth cleaned regularly, and brush daily. The flavor is on the mild side, and I have not noticed any increased sensitivity. I canât say for sure if my enamel is stronger or if my teeth are whiter. I feel as though the enamel strengthening and teeth whitening could be a marketing gimmick

I feel as though the enamel strengthening and teeth whitening could be a gimmick designed to differentiate from other toothpastes on the market. If youâre not worried about damaging veneers, then give the Colgate clean mint enamel health whitening toothpaste a chance. However I wouldnât be willing to pay extra for these features unless my dentist recommended it.

PROS:
Helps replenish natural calcium
Gently polishes and whitens
Fights cavities

CONS:
Whitening may not be effective

product_title: Deva Curl Travel Kit
review_headline: The scent, just can't justify using or buying it if it does not smell good
review_body:
While I am glad that I bought the travel kit as a way to test out all of the products to prevent wasting money, I must say I was not pleased especially given some of the reviews about these products. If I am going to spend a bunch of cash on hair products I expect the fragrance to be wonderful but at the very least pleasant. I have 2 little boys (4yrs and 6 yrs) so for me I want a shower should feel like a luxury and bring me some peace and calm, that is why I do not worry about a splurge on great shampoo, conditioner and body wash products.

Deva Curl No-poo and One Condition: The main drawback and in fact deal breaker for me was the scent. I thought it smelled like some kind of chemical mixed with some sickening sweet candy. There was nothing pleasing about the fragrance. Even my little boys did not like the fragrance, without any prompting my son said it kind of smelled like candy, but also smelled "not like good candy." If 4 and 6 year old boys don't like the smell of "candy" then something is wrong. My husband also right away noticed something different. He asked if I was wearing a new perfume and when I told him no that it was my shampoo he said you don't need to get that again. As for performance they worked fine on my hair, but I have found other low detergent curly shampoos work just as well with a far better scent.

Devacurl Light Defining Gel: This did not have as bad fragrance as the shampoo and conditioner, but it also was no better than any light hold gel you can get at a drugstore so I would not spend the money.

Deva Curl Set it Free: The only thing I did not hate was this leave in conditioner spray. It did not have as strong or as obnoxious of a smell as the other products. This too however is just as good as other leave in conditioning sprays. The spray was light so it did not weigh the hair down, I felt like it did what the product claimed. Therefore I give this travel kit 1 star for the Set it Free. If I were reviewing just the Set it free product I would give it about 3 stars on it's own. don't go out of you way for this product line though.

If they reformulate the scent to a clean fresh smell I would reconsider the shampoo, conditioner and spray. I would not buy the gel even with better scent because there is nothing special there.Set it Free. If I were reviewing just the Set it free product I would give it about 3 stars on it's own. don't go out of you way for this product line though.

If they reformulate the scent to a clean fresh smell I would reconsider the shampoo, conditioner and spray. I would not buy the gel even with better scent because there is nothing special there.

product_title: HSI Professional Glider | Ceramic Tourmaline Ionic Flat Iron Hair Straightener | Straightens & Curls with Adjustable Temp | Incl Glove, Pouch, & Travel Size Argan Oil Hair Treatment | Packaging Varies
review_headline: First flat iron that can actually straighten my hair!
review_body:
I have very very thick, very curly, coarse hair. I have never been able to affectively straighten my hair before. I have tried many different forms of straightening and flat irons over the years but my hair has never been truly straight. After over two hours of straightening my hair would still be bushy and there wouldn't be movement or much shine. I'd always be disappointed and feel like straightening wasn't worth the time and effort.

But then I tried this! It's fantastic! I read so many reviews that I thought just maybe it really works....and it does! It's unbelievable! My hair looks like I was born with straight hair. And instead of taking hours it only takes about 45 minutes. That probably seems like a long time, but I have so much hair. I bet it'd take a lot less time for an average amount of hair. My hair is soft, shiny, has movement and stays straight until I wash it.

I've used this twice now and I only have one complaint. While using it, it will turn off and the reset button will pop out. But I just have to reset it and it's good to go.

Over all I love it! If you feel you have hair that a flat iron will never work on give this one a shot. It might just finally do the trick.

product_title: Scholl Fungal Nail Treatment (3.8ml)
review_headline: Took two doses and some extra TLC but it worked very well for me
review_body:
It worked! IT WORKED! It worked for me!

I had 8 infected toenails and after 3 weeks, had 7 clear nails and was wearing sandals again!
I had one nail that had to grow out (it did) - but initially, my two little toes, had very little improvement.

I purchased a second dose - and to be honest, a rotary tool and some sanding bands - because the two nails that didn't clear up were so thick that the little file simply could not file through them. The extra filing seemed to reduce the thickness and allow the second to penetrate the nail and start working.

In defense of the product, there is an insert with pictures that states something like: "If your nails look like 'this' (and shows a picture), contact a doctor and do not use. I used the product anyway.

I started noticing clearing in 48 hours on most of my nails. And as stated above, had 7 clear within a few weeks.

From the reviews, this clearly doesn't work for everyone - but after 2 treatments and time to let the nails grow out, I am very pleased. VERY pleased. I had been considering expensive laser treatments because as a woman living in the Southwest where open-toed shoes are worn 10 months of the year, I was one of the lucky ones that this product actually helped.

review_headline: If you like shaving with sandpaper, you'll love this razor!
review_body:
OK. This razor is not as bad as shaving with sandpaper (not that I would actually know) but there are many instances when I use it that it catches my hair and is quite painful. Overall, it will give me a decent shave but it is not as smooth and painless as other electric razors I have used in the past.

The PR1235 (awesome name by the way) does a satisfactory job for the price. The main drawback for me is that you cannot run it under a sink to clean it. This makes cleaning a bit more bothersome and consequently it gets cleaned less frequently than other razors I have used.

If you are on a budget, this will do the job; I suggest you save $5-$10 more and get a slightly better model though.

product_title: Beauty Bridge Cosmetics Anti-Aging Illuminating Eye Cream
review_headline: No problems, but no visible results, either
review_body:
NOTE: I received a free sample of this product for review.

I don't usually use any type of eye cream or serum, as I'm not confident that they are effective. However, I do have a chronic issue with dark circles under my eyes, and as I've gotten older (late 40s), I've of course had some aging-related issues as well, which is why I agreed to try this product.

I used this eye cream daily for close to six weeks. The good news is that I did not have any problems or sensitivities with this product. I tend to have oily, acne-prone skin, but I did not experience any breakouts or other related difficulties while using this eye cream. Unfortunately, after regular, consistent use of this eye cream, I didn't notice any particular improvement, either. I've attached photos, so you can review the results for yourself.

Others may certainly have a different result, but personally, I have no basis on which to recommend this product.

review_body:
This unit gives a very close shave. There was a slight learning curve coming from a Remington foil shaver. The holes in the foil are smaller on this unit and I have to go slower but the shave seems to be as close as a triple blade razor. I like the cleaning/charging station, I just drop it in to charge it and run the clean cycle once a week. A quick rinse in warm water after each shave keeps the clippings in the shaver head to a minimum and extends the life of the cleaning cartridge.
I think slightly larger holes in the foil would be better for people with thicker hair and would make it a little faster.

product_title: Earth Therapeutics Exfoliating Green Tea Herbal Soap - 3 Pack
review_body:
I'm giving this a one star due to the ingredients not clearly stated on the package. It's kinda deceptive because the product seems natural, herbal, from "earth" etc, with only 3 ingredients listed....now I'm no rocket scientist but I know it takes more than that to make soap. Here I will list the actual ingredients (which btw aren't exactly earth friendly) contained in this product which I obtained from Earth Therapeutics myself.........Sodium Palmate, Sodium Palm Kernelate, Water, Glycerine, Sorbitol, Fragrance, Palm Acid, Palm Kernel Acid, Oryza Sativa (Rice) Powder, Tetrasodium EDTA, Tetrasodium Etidronate, Tocopheryl Acetate, Ascorbic Acid, Menthol, Carmellia Sinensis (Green Tea) Leaf Extract, Yellow 10, Green 3.
So my advice is, don't ever buy anything that doesn't list all the ingredients & make sure those ingredients are safe.

product_title: Make up Brushes By Xtava
review_body:
I am not very skillful at applying makeup. I need all the help I can get that's what I prefer high quality brushes and when I was given the chance to test this one for quality, I was super excited. The foundation brush is super soft and the handle had a good grip. It's a good length which makes application easy. I was especially appreciative of the directions that were given to expertly apply foundation and I usually just slop it on and hope for the best. They are as follows:

TO USE: Deposit foundation on the back of your hand and begin by dipping only the tip of the brush for lighter coverage, building to heavier coverage by using the broad sides of the brush. Dot small amount of makeup on T-Zone, under eyes, and problem areas, then blend from the middle of the face outward and upward
â¢PRO TIP: Upward brush strokes and a very slightly damp brush yield best results when it comes to natural foundation application

By following these instructions, I was able to apply my foundation without looking like a clown with the hard line around my face. I am a huge fan of XTAVA brushes.

product_title: Botanics Shine Away Ionic Clay Mask 3.5 Oz. by AB
review_body: This is a good, lightweight mask that doesn't dry out my skin. It's not as deep cleaning as some other masks I've used, such as Biore, but it works well enough and is reasonably priced. It's very watery and thin and doesn't feel like a clay paste at all; it's more like gritty, muddy water. At first, this consistency felt strange and I thought it would be cheap and ineffective, but that was not the case. After use, my skin looked softer and less oily and stressed than before. My favorite thing about this mask is that it doesn't irritate my very sensitive skin and doesn't leave it red for hours like many other masks have done, which means I can use it in the morning before I leave the house. Good product. Note: It is much cheaper at Target.

product_title: Black & White Bleach Cream 3/4
review_body: My reaction to this product is mixed. Since this is a skin product, let me just mention that I'm a light-to-medium-complexioned 54yo white chick with combination skin I'm trying to lighten up a little and fade some dark spots. I'm not using it regularly--not a very regimented person--so my results may differ from others. I also use other products with it. I can't see much difference. Also, like some others, I think it does break me out a little. It goes on very dry, does not add moisture, though, and there's not much of a fragrance so it's not unpleasant to use or anything. My advice would be to get a small tube and see how it works for you. It obviously does help some people. As far as fading dark spots and evening out skin tone, I find that Neutrogena Rapid Tone Repair Night works great and it also moisturizes. There's a complementary day product with sunscreen, but the night product seems to work better. I'd like to go really pale, but, honestly, nothing in a tube or bottle is going to significantly lighten your skin, imho.

product_title: SENSUAL INTENSE BY JOHAN B COLOGNE FOR MEN 2.8 OZ / 85 ML EAU DE TOILETTE SPRAY

product_title: Crest 3D White Brilliance Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Deep Cleansing via Daily Two-Step System, 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
review_body:
I wasn't sure what to expect from using this product because I've tried whitening strips before and they are clumsy and inconvenient to use and not all that effective. The two-step process of the Crest 3D Brilliance Cleansing and Whitening System turned out to be easier than I expected and was easy to work in to my normal tooth brushing routine. The first step (the deep cleansing toothpaste) you leave on without rinsing for just a minute, then you proceed to step two (the whitening finisher), brush for a minute more then rinse.

I was really surprised at how well it whitens and how soon I started getting results - after using Crest 3D Brilliance for just a couple of days I noticed a big improvement and with steady use for about three weeks now, my teeth are continuing to whiten and brighten - I'm very happy with the results.

One of my favorite parts was the foaming action because that gets deep down into the crevices that whitening strips could never reach and the micro cleansers polish away stains and leave my mouth feeling very fresh and clean, with clean fresh breath. I can see why they call it 3D Brilliance because my teeth not only look whiter but the illuminating complex makes them very bright and lustrous like no other toothpaste or whitening system has done for me before. I think the two-step system is key - they work together as a team to make my teeth the cleanest and brightest they've ever been. I'm very excited about the product and am so happy that i discovered it through BzzAgent, and was able to try this wonderful product free by participating in one of their campaigns.

product_title: Phillips Imperial Oval Cushion Reinforced Boar Bristle Hair Brush IMP
review_body: This brush is great! I had been wanting a Mason Pearson brush but bought a Sonia Kashuk brush instead to try it out first. I loved how well it detangled and it was definitely better than a typical paddle brush. That brush lasted about 2 months before it was broken and unusable. I've had this brush for 2 years now and it's still in perfect condition. A lot of people say the Mason Pearson is worth it over the Denman or Sonia Kashuk version because it will last forever, but so far the quality of this brush has blown me away. There is no fraying on any boar bristles and not even one plastic bristle has deformed or fallen out. The logo has rubbed off the handle, but the silver paint is still glossy and unchipped. It has that heavy sturdy feeling like with a MP brush and is imo totally indistinguishable. It detangles INCREDIBLY well. When I use paddle brushes now they feel like they really pull my hair and cause a lot of breakage, while I don't feel much tugging at all with this one, and a lot less breakage and hair loss.

product_title: Eucerin Sensitive Facial Skin Q10 Anti-Wrinkle Sensitive Skin Lotion with SPF 15 Sunscreen
review_headline: Eucerin vs Garnier:  a comprehensive review
review_body:
My skin is super sensitive, combination, and very acne-prone, so I'm very careful about what goes on my skin. The way I switch to a new product is this: on the right side of my face, I use my usual lotion. On the left, I use the new lotion. I do this for about a month before switching to the new lotion, unless the new lotion causes a severe reaction. This allows me to systematically test whether or not the new lotion is actually better, as well as control for hormone swings/cycles.

For reference, my old lotion is Garnier Moisture Rescue for Normal/Combo Skin. The Eucerin is thicker than the gel-cream texture of the Garnier, and while neither has an overwhelming scent, the Garnier has a stronger scent. The Eucerin absorbs more slowly, and doesn't spread as easily as the Garnier, but the skin feels softer when it's absorbed.

**Day One**:
The Eucerin side feels softer to the touch, and actually seems less greasy after a night of sleep than the Garnier side. No visible difference in pore size, acne, or fine lines (yet).
My initial impression of the Eucerin is good--I like that it feels softer, yet less greasy, and the SPF and the fact that it doesn't have a scent are two huge positives.

**UPDATE: 8/1/15--Day Three**
The Eucerin continues to make the left side of my face feel softer than the Garnier on the right. To make sure I wasn't imagining it, I asked my boyfriend to tell me if he could feel a difference between the two sides of my face, without telling him which side was which, and he also said that the left side was softer.
I'm now noticing a subtle difference in texture between the two sides as well. Those fine lines that they're talking about do seem lighter with the Eucerin (tested by making a surprised face and then seeing how long it took for the expression lines to fade).
I've had a breakout this morning as well, and noticed something unexpected. The breakout is actually worse on the Garnierside (both number and redness of bumps). I would have expected the Eucerin to be worse since it's new, and I've not experienced an increase in breakouts from the Garnier as opposed to my older lotion. But, for some reason, the Eucerin side of my face isn't as broken out as the Garnier side, to the point where I have a very obvious and comical line down the middle of my face that marks where the clear skin ends. I think I'm going to have a hard time going a full month without switching over completely, but I'll try to soldier on, just in case.

**UPDATE 8/13/15** Ok, I've hit my limit. I'm officially switching to the Eucerin. My skin is calmer, my fine lines have all but disappeared, and it continues to make my skin softer than the Garnier moisturizer. I'm throwing in the towel on the Garnier--this stuff is my new moisturizer.

product_title: Braun M90 Mobile Shaver for Precision Trimming, Great for Travel, Black/Silver
review_body:
I'm pleasantly surprised by this electric shaver.

I hadn't owned or used an electric shaver since my teens in the late '90s or early 2000's. When I took to shaving my head with disposable razors, it just never made sense to keep an electric razor for my face. And when I took to simply allowing my facial hair to grow out (either as a crazy beard or as reasonably maintained stubble), I never had a need for a razor that would give me a clean-shave,

But I bought this shaver on a whim (perhaps thinking I should try the clean-shaven look to create the appearance that I'm putting in some amount of effort). Given the price, and given that I've strictly used disposable razors for the better part of my adult life, I wasn't expecting much from this shaver.

But it does the job.

I took some old hair clippers (meant to be used on the head) and gave my facial hair a quick buzz without any attachments, just to get the hair as short as possible in preparation for this little shaver. And I found that it gave me a pretty smooth shave. It took longer than I would have expected (perhaps because I have poor technique or an oddly shaped face, or perhaps I just had unreasonable expectations because it's been so long since I shaved with an electric shaver).

And my skin felt irritated in a handful of spots. Though, as I explained, I've been in the habit of never really sporting a clean-shave look... so it makes sense that my skin was unaccustomed to such a close shave after so long with a beard or with scruff of some kind.

Still, I am pleased with the results. With some more attention paid to my technique, and with some more attention paid to my skin (pre- and after-shave skin products of some kind, I imagine), I feel like I would be able to produce a very close shave with minimal effort, time, or discomfort.

review_headline: Sample was better quality then the product.
review_body: I sell professional hair products and have for about 13 years now. I received a sample of this product from my sister and it was phenomenal! I couldn't find this item from any of my professional distributors so I broke down and bough it on Amazon, and the price was very good. However,the item I received was not of the same quality  as the sample I had tried ( as another reviewer noted.) This means the product is being cut with water (funny its called crack....once they get you hooked they don't give you the good stuff) which it did have the appearance of because it had "separated" thereby looking grainy even though it was not grainy in texture. OR that Prolock knows exactly how to make a great product, uses this better quality stuff for samples then makes a less quality product. product_title: Secret Outlast Active Fresh Clear Gel Women's Antiperspirant and Deodorant, 2.6 Ounce
review_headline: Dries fast and keeps me dry
review_body:
I was loyal to a competitive brand of antiperspirant for years, but I was given the opportunity to try Secret Outlast Active Fresh Clear Gel as part of the Secret's Clearly Better Challenge so I decided to broaden my horizons.

After using Secret Outlast Clear Gel for about 3 weeks, I am more than satisfied. It goes on smoothly and dries in much shorter time than the brand I was using previously. It keeps me dry and odor free. In fact, I forgot to put it on one day and I was fine. It doesn't hurt at all to apply directly after shaving. :)

I like this Secret antiperspirant a lot, and I intend to buy another when I'm out. However, I'll buy unscented or powder fresh, my typical scent choices.

product_title: Brown Velvet Hair Scrunchies
review_body: These velvet scrunchies by Penny's Boutique are beautiful, the pictures cannot do them justice. I have purchased 7 so far and the quality is amazing. I've had long hair for more than 20 years so I have gone through a lot of scrunchies and these are the BEST I have have ever used. The one I have had the longest over 1 years is unchanged since I got it. It has not stretched out at all. It has not faded in color. They do not feel heavy on my head. They stay put without being too tight and without pulling my hair. I aim to purchase 10 more simply because these are fantastic quality, colors, softness and function that I love. They hold in my regular thickness straight long hair (my hair falls just below my center back when down). I use the size Large because I like the "fluffy look". I do have 1 Jumbo size which does work but I found the Large works better for my hair thickness (not thick hair but not thin, my hair is long and naturally very straight). I only have to "twist and fold over once" with the Large size and it stays in place even while active like play with my dogs outside or while at work. The inside diameter makes the difference on how it will work for a pony tail/bun/messy up doo on different hair types. These Penny's Boutique velvet scrunchies are amazing, I love them and I hope they continue making them.

review_headline: Excellent Serum for all skin types
review_body:
I am a Product Tester and was offered this Anti-Aging Serum by Sublime at a special price during a promotion the company was having; in exchange, I would test their product and give you my honest feedback. I can honestly say that I love this product. It's a serum, which I love, because serums tend to have a more concentrated dose of active ingredients than do creams. (But that's just my personal opinion) I also love the fact that it is a pump dispenser, this way I always get just the right amount without waste or contamination.

I have been using this wonderful serum 3 times a week and the results are astounding! It's nice and light and glides on like silk and has a soft, subtle scent. It's worked wonders on minimizing those fine lines I've started to notice. It has also helped clear up my skin by unclogging my pores. Sublime contains glycolic acid and salicylic acid which are natural fruit ingredients with exfoliating properties that encourages the sloughing of dead skin cells improving the tone and texture of my skin. My skin looks radiant and more youthful.

It is my honest opinion that this anti-aging serum by Sublime works very well and has become part of my skin care routine. If you haven't tried it yet, what are you waiting for? Your skin will thank you!

After dying it the wig became super dry. It also looked better in it's original color. I'm purchasing this wig again and will not be dying it. Also I've found a way to make the part look very natural. I cut a brown paper bag and put the stip underwig were the lace part is. product_title: Braun
review_headline: The best shaving system you can buy.
review_body: This is a GREAT shaver system. I owned a previous Braun for over 10 years, never really used the cleaning part or took care of it well, but it lasted for over 10 years and worked very well until the charger port broke on it. So it was time to get another one. I did a lot of research and based on how long the last one lasted me and how good of reviews this one got, I broke down and just got this one and I'm very happy I did. So far, I've had it for a few months and it's been very solid. It just works very well and does exactly what you want it to do. I do use the cleaning and charging station and it works nice. I'm not a huge fan of the tilt because if it's not in there correctly, it doesn't hit the charge knobs inside. But that's a very minor complaint. Other than that, I'd highly recommend this and have no complaints.

product_title: Godefroy 28 Day Mascara Lash & Brow Tint Single Brown (6 Pieces)
review_headline: Works great, but does sting if you get it in your eyes (which you will)
review_body:
I am naturally blonde, with lashes that are almost invisible without mascara. However, I have 2 big problems with most daily mascaras on the market: they look too clumpy and unnatural, and I don't like having to mess with them every morning. This product does a great job of fixing both of those issues on a semi-permanent basis.

Like the title implies, you can get away with applying this roughly once a month. While it won't give as intense of a look as if you applied traditional mascara, it does provide visible color and definition, even on my pathetic little lashes. It doesn't look like I'm wearing mascara, but it does look like I actually have eyelashes!

The only downside: it does sting quite a bit if you get it in your eyes, and I have yet to determine a method that prevents me from getting it in my eyes. Since it's a 2-step process and requires you to paint on your eyes with quite a bit of precision, there are lots of opportunities for a little bit to slide off the lash and into the eyeball. I would be lying if I said this doesn't HURT-- enough that when it happens, I am forced to rinse it off immediately. If it hasn't sat long enough, that means I have to repeat the process. It doesn't do any serious damage to your eyes, though. It's just inconvenient and painful.

Despite that disadvantage, I will keep using this product. If you're lazy like me and hate doing daily make-up, give it a shot.

product_title: Fantasea Facial Cleansing Sponge * 12 Per Package
review_headline: Great value, good alternative to a wash cloth with one minor issue....
review_body:
These are a great value considering you pay the same amount at the store for just 3 sponges. I have really sensitive skin and have to be very careful about what I use on my face. After trying several different types of facial cleansing products, I have found these to be one of the better choices.
They last quite a long time, don't flake apart in pieces, rinse well and are just the right size. My only complaint about this particular brand is they are not quite as soft as other facial sponges I've used. The texture is more coarse like a kitchen sponge which can be irritating if you scrub too hard.
They do hold up so well that you could sanitize them when they get yucky, but I feel like it's not worth the effort given the price is so reasonable. This 12 pack lasts several months.
One nice side benefit is that, when it's time to ditch one for a new sponge, the old ones get put to good use around the house for all kinds of projects such as:
Detailing the car interior
applying wood stain
Polishing jewelry
Cleaning hard to reach spots on household surfaces
Cleaning anything where a Q-tip is too small but a normal sized kitchen sponge is too big
I'm still finding uses for these things!
Hope this helps ;)

product_title: Ultrax Labs Hair Surge | Caffeine Hair Loss Hair Growth Stimulating Shampoo
review_headline: This product is as close to magical hair recovery as you can get!
review_body:
There is a reason this shampoo was rated 2015's top shampoo for hair regrowth stimulation, because it actually works. Created for both men and women this product helps strengthen and thicken already present hair while stimulating the growth of new hair.
It contains three powerful ingredients: Caffeine, ketoconazole, and. The caffeine helps extend the life cycle of the hair follicles, ketoconazole which is the same anti-inflammatory and anti-fungal ingredient in dandruff keeps hair healthy, and Saw Palmetto which turns testosterone into DHT, a major cause for male and female baldness.

There is no magical product that will make your hair stronger and more full overnight, but with directed use this will give you those results!

I love that it's all natural and smells amazing. For anti-aging products you need to give them six months, that's the amount of time it takes for complete cell turnover in your skin (sloughing off the old cells) and to see ultimate results. I'll update this review in five months on the final results. But so far, I love it.

review_headline: Love this hand cream, hate the scent
review_body:
I love this hand cream, it has a great texture and it's not easy finding a reasonably priced hand cream with sunscreen. We women takes such good care of our facial skin, but our hands get neglected--if you truly want to know a woman's age, look at her hands.

I took off one star for the scent--other reviewers called it a light scent, but it's not light to me. I love scented products and never shy away from something with a lot of fragrance, unless it is a spicy fragrance that contains amber, sandalwood, patchouli, etc. Those scents do not agree with my nose at all, and one or more of them are in this lotion. A nice neutral-y hand lotion fragrance would have been much better, as I smell this scent for hours after I put on the lotion. I was hoping I found my holy grail hand lotion, but I will keep looking because I just can't stand the scent of this one.

product_title: Biotene PBF Oral Rinse 33.8 oz
review_headline: Not sure if it's doing anything...
review_body:
Meh, I don't know.. I've never used a mouthwash before because they all have alcohol and sugar in them, which defeats the purpose of rinsing out your mouth since alcohol/sugar = dries out your mouth = bacteria loves a dry mouth = breathy. People rinse their mouths out with alcohol and dry out their mouths even more...and then they think they need mouthwash more. But I had heard Biotene does not have alcohol in it and it's supposed to help clean your teeth and gums between dental cleanings, which I thought was a bonus since I don't enjoy flossing.

Honestly, I don't think it's doing anything. I feel nothing different, see nothing different. Probably won't get it again. I'm not addressing a dry mouth issue like a lot of reviewers here and I don't have plaque build up so maybe I'm just not a good judge of this product.

product_title: W7 In The Buff Lightly Toasted Eye Colour Palette
review_headline: This is quite a good dupe of the naked 1
review_body:
This is quite a good dupe of the naked 1!! Naked 1 is highly pigmented buttery eyeshadows that go on really well but for close to $60! W7's eyeshadows have a similar colors with good pigment, and for the price you can't go wrong! The lighter colors need a little extra layers and more blending to show the actual color, but the dark colors are really good :). Its more powdery then buttery, like drug store eyeshadow. The dark colors have a good pigment, and do a great smokey eye! The light colors have glitter, and give a nice shimmery eye for night time.. OVERALL: I love the colors, the price, and the application. My package arrived to me 12 days earlier then predicted. :)

The only thing is i wish it had more matte shade, there are only 2 matte shades the rest of shimmer/glitter.

review_headline: This First Time Retinol User Is Impressed
review_body:
I'm still new at this being in my 30's thing, but I started reading up on how my skin care regimen needed an upgrade from my teens and 20's. Everything I read said add retinol to your regimen. I did some research before settling upon this product. While I wasn't expecting results so quickly, I'm pleasantly surprised by the difference in my skin. My tone and my pores look fantastic. My skin absorbed it quickly and I've had ZERO breakouts from it. I did notice it doesn't do away with the dry patches on my face though, so I still use my old moisturizer in the mornings, and use this stuff at night.

After a week on this I went ahead and ordered the Hyaluronic Dew Serum and WOW. I'm also doing bentonite masks twice a week, but otherwise I just cleanse and moisturize. My skin has never looked this good...EVER. I know a lot of people got these products for free, but I bought mine and still love them.

review_body: Yes, it works like it's supposed to, but the pain is just too much for me.  The hair does seem to take longer to grow back; of course, the root is gone, duh.  Seriously though, I could not tolerate the discomfort for more than a small section at a time. product_title: Gillette Fusion Proglide Irritation Defense Men's Shaving Gel 7 Oz (Pack of 6)
review_headline: A little expensive, but a good product.
review_body:
Overview: This razor is good. The flex ball and the blades are a noticeable improvement over standard disposable razors. Much better than the "power" version (http://amzn.com/B00J3MPS4E )

DISCLAIMER: I was given this product by the brand to test it out and review it, I did not purchase it from Amazon.

Before this razor I was using the power version of this razor. I like this version much better, the vibrations really did nothing for me. This product is exactly like the power version sans the gimmicky oscillations.

The things I like about this razor:

1)The blades really glide along your skin, and they appear to last for quite some time. Though I am an Asian male, so at most I shave once every other day. And when I do shave, it's not much.

2) The flex ball really does help the blades follow the contour of your face. Combined with the blade design this makes the shaving experience really smooth.

Things that I don't like

1) 5 blades is a little too much for me. Maybe this gives a smoother shave, but it's a little wide for my face.

2) It's a little pricey. This was given to me to test for free, but I don't know if I would ever go out to buy one of these at $8-10. The refills are pretty costly too.

review_headline: It left my hair feeling like it lacked moisture
review_body:
I just received my steamer on Saturday and the used it for the first time yesterday. So far I am not impressed. It left my hair feeling like it lacked moisture. I will give it 2 more times but 3 strikes and you're out!

product_title: Kenzo Power Eau de Toilette Spray
review_headline: Ya want masculine???  Don't look here.
review_body:
They call it "masculine" but then they say it's "a fragrance of opposites" ;
well, I'd say that second phrase about sums it up: it's OPPOSITE to anything approaching masculine.
I have owned several other Kenzo men's fragrances, like Homme and L'eau Par Kenzo .... and I appreciate using them for a change once in a while.
But even those fragrances are definitely never mistaken for "masculine" scents; they're definitely rather feminine. (thereby somewhat "opposite").
But man! This Power scent is SO flowery and feminine that I'll definitely never wear it again: they'd take away my man-card if I did !
About as masculine as a transvestite channeling Jessica Rabbit.
I'll likely give it to my wife to wear ... who said she rather likes it (on HER!).
Take a look at the ingredients and tell me if ANY of those fragrances suggest a masculine scent.

Really disappointing !!

product_title: Curel Itch Defense Soothing Moisturizing Spray, 6 Ounce
review_headline: As good as the lotion, easy to apply
review_body:
Every bit as good as its counterpart, Curely Itch Defense Lotion, in that it soothes and eventually calms the need to itch. For a product line that is not overly expensive, this latest addition is another sure winner, with the added plus that now it can be used via spray. The size of the container is not very big, but the very convenient way in which it can be used makes it a standout. Have no reason to believe that this method of using the product is less effective than the lotion version, as I have already have experienced the efficient way in which it helps against itching. Would like to thank Amazon, for delivering this Curel Itch Defense Soothing Moisturizing Spray, 6 Ounce, right to my doorsteps.
For someone who regrettably always seemed to have a tendency for dry skin, I find this product immensely helpful to combat this problem on a daily basis. Yes, perhaps a little more expensive in the long run, but also much easier and as equally effective, in this spray bottle. 4.5 Stars.

review_body:

product_title: Burt's Bees Basic Face Care Kit
review_body:
For the most part, I really liked Burt's Bees Basic Face Care Kit. The Cleanser had a nice, fresh smell neither it nor the moisturizer left my face feeling sticky or greasy and oily. While I didn't use the facial wipes too much, they're great for when I'm just too busy to go through my whole facial routine in the morning.

The reason that it's getting four stars out of five is that for some reason, the cleanser burned with the fury of 1000 suns when I first put it on my face. In fact, I thought I was having an allergic reaction due to the burning. It calmed down some once I put on the moisturizer, but still, it had me worried for a second there.

ETA: At first, I gave this product 4 stars. However, after using it for two weeks, I decided to rate it 2 stars due to the cleanser. I'm someone with somewhat oily skin. So, I have no idea how the cleanser made my face peel the way it did. But it did. It dried my skin out so much (and, again, I'm someone who has the opposite problem. The cleanser also made me breakout. The breakout when away somewhat quicker than I'm used to, but still. I'm not going to use a cleanser that makes me breakout just b/c it somewhat cleans my face and makes my breakouts less noticeable if it's going to make me breakout more.

product_title: Remington F5-5800 Foil Shaver, Men's Electric Razor, Electric Shaver, Black
review_headline: Overall good, some cons compared with my old MicroScreen 3.
review_body:
I replaced a Remington Microscreen 3 that had a battery that was starting to go (down to four days between charges), and needed new screens and blades. Since I could not find one of those, I decided to try this. In general I would both recommend it and buy it again.
Pros: Very close shave, closer than the MS3. The "Interceptor" technology has prevented my having to use the trimmer on the long hairs that always seemed to pop up - in fact, they no longer get long enough to be noticeable - this is a very big plus that overcomes my "cons". Good charge retention, so far, and the charge indicator is nice
Cons: Bigger than the MS 3, so more awkward when traveling. The trimmer is at a very awkward angle to use on touching up my beard and mustache, so I put the razor down and get out the beard trimmer (not a daily event, so not so bad). There is less "precision" on where the shaving action happens compared with the MS3, so I for the occasional hair starting to pop up near my mustache I have to resort to the beard trimmer's shaving head - or risk shrinking the size for mustache and beard.

product_title: Coastal Scents Contour and Blush Palette
review_body:
I was skeptical, but I wanted to try my hand at contouring so I figured this would be a good place to start. I didn't expect the colors to be as great as they were but for me, they did go on very pigmented but unfortunately didn't stay on too long. While all of this isn't too bad and pretty acceptable, all things considered, the big downfall was how badly it broke out my skin. I am acne prone (cystic, no less), but I have it under control and it isn't too easily irritated. I didn't go at my skin super heavy with this since I am new to contouring. I tried the dark brown and thought nothing of it hitting my main problem area (which hasn't bothered me in a while). I did it for a few days, getting the hang of this technique and started noticing the bumps :( Since nothing else has been different for me, I can't attribute it to anything else.

I will still use this LIGHTLY around my face, mostly the white as a highlighter but around my eyes and brows. I'm pretty afraid to try the rest in heavy doses. I do have an event coming up so maybe a few trial runs with it and maybe for the actual day...but nothing too serious or often ever again. Hate to let this go to waste even though it was inexpensive, it was a decent enough palette.

Seller shipped fast & I was also afraid of it arriving broken but alas, it did not!

product_title: Alpha Hydrox AHA Enhanced Lotion - 6 fl oz
review_headline: Let me start by saying this product is perfect for those with acne prone skin
review_body:
Let me start by saying this product is perfect for those with acne prone skin. I had a HORRIBLE breakout that pushed me over the edge mentally to find something that would help. After reading up on exfoliation I found that physical/mechanical scrubs are NOT good for people with acne prone skin and chemical exfoliants ARE good!

Here's a few ways I use this product with results almost instantly but realistic results in 1-2 weeks.

1. After cleansing I add a tiny drop to my normal moisturizer and mix it all up and apply. This can be added after you applied Benzoyl Peroxide if you're treating acne as I am. You can do this 2 times a day since you're using just a tiny bit (pea sized or smaller)

2. If you have a pimple forming you can catch it and stop it by putting this right on the area 1-2 times a day. It's shocking how fast this works when your pimple is just forming. I had a cyst forming that freaked me out...put this on and it was gone within 3 hours.

3. If you have a stubborn pimple you can first put BP on it and then after a few minutes add a little of this on top. It seriously helps the healing process and makes everything go away much much quicker.

My face is glowing. I'm 28 and have had bouts of mild to moderate acne since I was 15, so you can imagine how nice it is to look at yourself in the mirror after 13 years and see a face that doesn't make you upset. My face feels ridiculously smooth too.

Lastly I don't use this every day, or if I do use it everyday I take a mini break after 3 or 4 days.

I hope this helps someone because I know how frustrating problematic skin can be! It really hurts you mentally and this stuff along side of a GENTLE cleanser, BP and regular (oil free) moisturizer has really changed my skin and my life!

product_title: Revlon Rvdr5033 1875w Compact Stylist Dryer, Black
review_headline: Not sure if the one I had worked right at all.
review_body:
In Dec 2014 I had bought a Revlon RV544PKF and we liked it so I thought another Revlon was a good bet but we needed a compact model. Apparently I was wrong.

The one of these I got on high overheated quickly for no reason and then began cycling. The fan went from high to low and the heater went off. After a minute or so it would turn the heater on and the fan back to high and start the cycle over again. Disregarding the defect of overheating too easily because that was an obvious defect, the way it responded to being too hot makes no sense. Turn the heater off sure, but switching the fan to low is just dumb. Just as dumb was that if you pushed the cool air button the fan also switched to low along with the heater turning off. Was it totally wired wrong? Seems unlikely so I returned it and bought a compact Conair Travel Smart that works fine and the cool air button just turns the heater off makes sense.

review_body:
I have never purchased fractionated oil before, so I was not sure what to expect. I regularly use coconut oil on my skin, and I love the effects of it. Usually, the coconut oil I use is partially solid, and I have to rub it between my hands to turn it into a liquid to apply to my skin. I like that this oil is already in liquid form and easy to apply. Also, the pump top makes for less mess than the usual jar I use. The first thing I was shocked my when using this was the lack of any scent. It has no smell to it at all, and I was anticipating a coconut scent. After reading some stuff online, I guess coconut does not have much smell to begin with, and if there is a strong coconut scent it is probably artificial.
The oil applies easily to skin and is not as greasy as regular coconut oil. It seems to soak into my skin more quickly also. The only reason I did not give this 5 stars is because I love the smell of coconut and was left wanting that with this product. Other than that, I love the way it makes my skin look and feel.

review_headline: Bristles didn't grab my fine hair
review_body: I really liked the concept of this dryer/styler. The 2" brush was exactly what I was looking for to give volume to my  then medium length hair. I'm diagnosed with  fibromyalgia, and holding my hands above my head while juggling a brush and traditional dryer is difficult. Letting this styling tool do all the work seemed perfect. My problem came with the brush bristles. They just wouldn't grab my fine hair. I have a similar tool with a smaller barrel that doesn't rotate, and it has stiff wiry bristles that work perfectly. How I wish these were the same! The Infiniti's are a soft plasticy and plush, and are spaced very closed together. They just glided over my hair. With a little manipulation, I could get it to grab a bit, but then my efforts often became a tangled mess. Sadly, I returned it.

product_title: USpicy makeup brushes
review_headline: A brush for every possible makeup application - all in a nice vinyl pouch
review_body:
My daughters have been trying to convert me from foam makeup applicators and powder puffs to makeup brushes for several years, and just recently I decided to give them a try. I have to admit that brushes make application easier and blending smoother, and that brushes last a lot longer too. It's also more economical to wash and dry brushes instead of replacing foam ones every few months.

This USpicy makeup kit is certainly one of the most complete ones I've ever seen! It contains 32 different types of brushes - everything from lipliner brushes to eyeshadow and powder brushes, two sponge applicators, and even a mascara brush and eyebrow/eyelash comb. Some brushes are very thin tipped, some are angled for precision and some are large and fluffy, making any kind of makeup application easy and efficient. Each brush has a wooden handle, and firmly affixed, soft natural hair bristles. I found these brushes a pleasure to use, and I felt like a professional makeup artist as I selected the brushes and made up my face.

The set comes in a vinyl roll-up case that keeps everything neat, protected and organized. It's about the size of a clutch purse when closed, and would fit neatly in a suitcase, briefcase, or vanity drawer. I do wish the case had a snap closure instead of the tie laces, but overall this is a very complete, high quality set of brushes that should last a lifetime.

I received a complimentary makeup brush set for testing and review. I wasn't asked to leave a positive review, nor was I otherwise compensated for giving my honest opinion of the product.
