review_body: I bought this product because of its rave reviews, however it does not reflect my experience. I have 3 main issues with this product, 1) If directions on a face cream say "let it dry", the warning bells should go off. It goes on nice but then starts to have this tacky feel to it, like a face mask thats ready to be peeled from your face. It does take a long time before the feeling goes away. 2) The smell is not horrible, but it does not make you feel refreshed or slightly pampered. 3) I have seen no changes to my face! It claims that it at the very least it "brightens" your face, but honestly I found better results with some $3 face cream from Dollar General. So overall I will finish this tube and try another product, never to come back to this.

review_headline: Buyer beware! This product only provides UVA(burning rays) protection not UVB(skin wrinkling, aging and brown spot rays).
review_body: This product does not provide broad spectrum protection, only UVA.  Only the burning rays will be screened, not UVB. UVB causes brown spots, skin wrinkling and aging. Feel this product does a disservice to consumers. It is widely known that broad spectrum protection is the sunscreen standard and has been for many years. When I spoke with a Eucurin product representative by phone today she stated that they briefly made it  UVA and UVB effective and due to complaints re product consistently they returned to UVA protective only.

product_title: Wahl Ear, Nose and Brow Trimmer #5545-400
review_headline: Best Nose and Ear Hair Timmer I've Owned
review_body:
Every trimmer I've owned (3 prior to this one) sounded like it's gears were made of plastic and they were about to die right out of the box. So this trimmer got four stars from me just for sounding like it wasn't on it's last leg. Actually it sounds strong and power delivery is consistent - 5th star earned. Other trimmers seemed to spin slower or faster depending on the angle at which I held them! This trimmer says it can operate in the shower, but I just have this thing about not taking electrical appliances in the shower with me. I know it's a low voltage, but still not going to do it.

Pros:
Runs strong at a consistent speed and at all angles
Has 3 different attachments - Ear, Nose, Brow
Easily removable top piece for cleaning
No pulling or tearing of hair, as advertised
Good value at under $8
Reputable name - Whal. I have a Whal clipper for trimming my hair that is now 20 years old and still works great

Cons:
Plastic is a little cheap looking, but then it's less than $8
Would have been nice if they had provided a case to keep trimmer and all attachments together

Summary:
Quality brand name product that does what is says it will do (though I didn't test in water) without pinching, pulling hairs or nicking, for a really low price. I am very happy with this purchase.

review_headline: Omg! Best hair remover ever. No burns!!!.
review_body:
I am a 17 year old male. I just got this and just used it. I was super nervous so iw arched a video then tried this.
I applyed it with my hans to my thighs for 10-15 minutes and the hair came off, end of story.
Then I used it on my face, 10 min later the hair came off, end of story.
Then I decided to try the private area. And it worked perfect. 10 minutes and it was all off with no burn.
The hands werebunaffected through the entire exposure and 1 hour later so... However if you try and reapply in under 24 hours it will burn, and I mean burn, but the shower stopped it instantly so I was very pleased.
This obviously is for guys and everyone does have a different sensitivity.
Girls, I don't know as you would want to risk it, it tinggles open cuts and will make them all white, so... Be carful.

product_title: Doxy Massager - Black - US Plugged Hand Held Personal Vibration Therapeutic Massager Full Body Massage 30% More Powerful than Hitachi Magic Wand Original HV 250 HV 260 - Great Valentines Holiday Gift - Includes AfterGlow Tissues 20 Pack - USA & Canada Model 1 Year Warranty
review_headline: when I heard about the Doxy from Oh Joy Sex Toy
review_body:
(Note, I didn't receive the "after glow" wipes, just some lube. Kind of a bummer since both were supposed to be included.)

As a big fan of the Hitachi magic wand, when I heard about the Doxy from Oh Joy Sex Toy!( http://www.ohjoysextoy.com/doxy/ ) I was really hyped about it. We got it as a valentines present to ourselves when My Hitachi started dying.

Construction & Modes: Winner: Doxy!
First off, this is way better constructed than the Hitachi. It's much smoother and less hard-plastic-edges. Much more streamlined controls with PVC push buttons for adjust-ability. Though technically the switch on the Hitachi is easy, the buttons are much harder to accidentally turn off while using it. Doxy has as variable speeds and pulse built in. The pulse function is eve adjustable, it pulses with a step up in rpm each time. Hold power for 3 seconds (while off) to go into pulse mode, and adjust your speeds with the plus and minus button. Otherwise, directly on, it starts out around 5000rpm and you can adjust down as low as 3000rpm or as high as 9000rpm. The Hitachi is a switch of (low) 5000rpm and (high) 6000rpm. The Doxy beats out the hitachi hands down on this front. Much more choices and easier to use. Both the Hitachi and Doxy are wired toys, which means more consistent power, but you may find the cords annoying a limiting. I don't mind throwing an extension cord near the bed to use them. The Doxy also has a longer cord, which makes it less cumbersome than the Hitachi. The Doxy also has a bigger "head" than the Hitachi. The larger head offers almost full coverage for sensitive bits and is very pleasant.

Massager (literally): Doxy!
The Doxy also beats out the Hitachi as a massager. The soft PVC head of the Doxy is deeply preferred as a sore muscle massager. The directions say to not use it near your throat or neck. which is a downer. My neck is what hurts. But it works great as a back massager. The hard, slightly porous head of the Hitachi was always too rough for that. (Medical association also recommends not using vibrating massagers on your calves, as it can exasperate some preexisting conditions in a very bad way.) However, this soft PVC head is what makes it loose the next round, as a "Personal Massager".

"Personal Massager": Hitachi!
The soft head of the Doxy sort of diffuses the vibrations of the massager. 6000rpm on the Hitachi feels much stronger on the hard, unforgiving head of the Hitachi than 9000rpm with the Doxy. And as a long time Hitachi user, I have come to really like the high (6000rpm) setting on it, though for years I only ever used low (5000rpm). The Doxy, with the very nice and forgiving PVC head, just doesn't pack the same punch as a Hitachi. The Doxy just doesn't "bring it home" Like the Hitachi. However, if you do NOT like high power and prefer softer, more diffused vibrations, than you should definitely get the Doxy. If you don't know for sure, head to your nearest "adult novelty store" Lots of them have "tester" areas where you can see what kinda vibrations you like. Try holding it and putting it on your wrist, to see if "hard" ones are too much for you. I do find the diffused vibrations of the Doxy are much more sensual, however. The Hitachi feels more mechanical, technical.

Price: Hitachi!
I haven't found a Doxy cheaper than $140USD. On Ebay, some ship from the UK for what translates to be the same amount of money, anyway. You can still find a Hitachi for 50 dollars including attachments. I got this one http://www.amazon.com/Magic-Wand-Massager-Including-Attachments/dp/B003BYRTGU/ about 5 years ago for $30USD. There's also lots of off-brands which means there are lots of attachments you can get for these puppies. The Hitachi or "Original Magic Wand", is still considered the best to get in terms of power and construction. Despite the Doxy being made better, the Hitachi is a very sturdy device! You can get a Hitachi and the rpm adjuster for less than a Doxy. Hell, you can get two hitachis with attachments and the adjuster for cheaper than a Doxy. If you are looking for something with a kick for a good price, you should still choose the Hitachi over the Doxy.

Included: Lube & Wipes.
I didn't get the wipes so I can't review them. Lube is a water based niceness. It's not the best lube, and I can't use many non-organic lubes, so I haven't used it for intended purposes. But betwixt my fingers, it's a decent lube. Lasts a good time, reduces friction, and minimal smell. Pretty middle-ranged lube. As water based, it's safe to use with any of your toys and condoms. Please ONLY use water-based with toys and condoms or you will melt your toys (very literally) and get pregnant.

Possible Upgrades: Also changeable head covers for the Doxy, choices between soft, medium, and firm/hard. Would also be a great way to add attachments. If they could also get it to go 1000rpm to 10000rpm, I would be very impressed, but I don't think it's necessary. A remote app for couples would also be hella awesome.
The price of the Doxy will eventually go down, but I think it's worth $100ish bucks rather than $150. If they added the upgrades, I'd call it worth $165~200.

TL;DR:
Doxy:
Pros: Made better, more adjustable, good massager, long cord, sensual.
Cons: Diffused Punch, expensive.achi is a very sturdy device! You can get a Hitachi and the rpm adjuster for less than a Doxy. Hell, you can get two hitachis with attachments and the adjuster for cheaper than a Doxy. If you are looking for something with a kick for a good price, you should still choose the Hitachi over the Doxy.

Included: Lube & Wipes.
I didn't get the wipes so I can't review them. Lube is a water based niceness. It's not the best lube, and I can't use many non-organic lubes, so I haven't used it for intended purposes. But betwixt my fingers, it's a decent lube. Lasts a good time, reduces friction, and minimal smell. Pretty middle-ranged lube. As water based, it's safe to use with any of your toys and condoms. Please ONLY use water-based with toys and condoms or you will melt your toys (very literally) and get pregnant.

Possible Upgrades: Also changeable head covers for the Doxy, choices between soft, medium, and firm/hard. Would also be a great way to add attachments. If they could also get it to go 1000rpm to 10000rpm, I would be very impressed, but I don't think it's necessary. A remote app for couples would also be hella awesome.
The price of the Doxy will eventually go down, but I think it's worth $100ish bucks rather than $150. If they added the upgrades, I'd call it worth $165~200.

TL;DR:
Doxy:
Pros: Made better, more adjustable, good massager, long cord, sensual.
Cons: Diffused Punch, expensive.

product_title: Jurlique Essence of Rose Roll-On Fragrance, 0.37 Fluid Ounce
review_body: I ordered this product after reading about it in Prevention magazine. Rose essence oil is known for its calming and soothing effects, definitely something I could use. I also liked that it came in a small, compact, mess-free roll-on I could carry in my purse. However, the order took forever to arrive. That's my first complaint. The product was in stock yet it took over a week to reach me. When I finally did receive it and applied it to my wrist, I could barely smell anything. So that's my second complaint...nothing was coming up roses! You can probably guess my third complaint. I washed my hands once and the faint scent I barely had after applying the rose oil was gone completely. Even cheap perfume has a lingering scent after a couple of hand washes!  I'm completely unsatisfied with not only this product but also with the entire experience of ordering it. If I could give zero stars I would. Don't waste your time and money on this. A better and cheaper option would be to go to an Indian grocery store and pick up a small vial of rose oil or a bottle of rose water which you can put into a small spray bottle and use. Stay away from this junk!

product_title: Giorgio Armani Emporio Armani Eau De Toilette Spray for Men
review_headline: Will take you back to your glory days.
review_body: This was a gift for my boyfriend.  He had been looking for the Emporio Armani cologne the past 2 years, but couldn't find it in any of the department stores (Macy's discontinued it, couldn't find it at others).  He was about to purchase it at one of those generic perfume stores, but I vehemently advised against it because my sister-in-law received watered-down products from those types of stores before.  When finally, we came across a "Perfumania" and they had a sample.  It smelled different at first, but after aerating a few minutes, the true smell came to life.  He told me all the memories came back to him, it was like a time machine to the past. He sniffed the sample paper until the scent no longer was there. I could tell he was excited because he was sniffing the sample every 5 seconds and almost looked like a drug addict getting high off of his next fix of nostalgia (and maybe a bit of help from the chemicals).  We're on a tight budget, so he didn't want to splurge on a seemingly frivolous addition to his toiletry kit; but seeing how happy the scent made him, I couldn't NOT do anything about it.... So, I found it on Amazon. We had a gift card (Xmas present) and my Chase rewards paid for a portion, so in the end I only paid about $15 for the remainder.  I was skeptical about purchasing this online and not directly through Armani or an official store, but this was a great gamble! The product is just like the original and he is extremely happy with it--as am I. He smells great, it masks any foot odor (ladies, you know what I'm talking about) and it brings back the memories of when we first met.  Great plus: it's 3.4 oz, so you can bring it on the plane! He leaves tomorrow for Chicago and was worried they may confiscate it because it appears larger, so I just printed the receipt w/the information about the container so that he can show the airport workers. This may be overkill, but all the work we did to find it, I don't want it to be confiscated at the airport. Long story short....it's great!port. Long story short....it's great!

product_title: Vitamin C Serum - ORGANIC - The #1 Anti Aging Serum For Younger Skin As You Age - Anti Wrinkle Serum - GUARANTEED - Receive Our Top Rated Ebook When You Order FREE (Limited Time - $7.99 Value) - 100% MONEY BACK GUARANTEE
review_body:
I have only been using this product for a week and so far it is wonderful. Of course I can't comment on the anti aging aspect because it is still too early to tell, but I can say it has helped with fading some scars I had. I have the occasional break out so I have lots of tiny scars over my face which have seemed to fade. I also tracked a big scar I had on my cheek that has been swollen and red for a couple of months, but after a couple of days of using this the bump has gone down and a lot of the redness has decreased.

One drawback I have about this product is that it is a bit difficult to apply. It is so liquid that I feel like I'm wasting a lot of product and it makes it difficult to apply around my eyes (which is where my wrinkles are). This is concerning since the description on the amazon page says to avoid direct contact with eyes. So the product doesn't seem to be something I want to use to fight wrinkles around my eyes.

The final drawback I have is about all the claims made on the amazon page, their own website, and on the bottle itself. As a scientist I want to know how the experiments were performed, what their controls were, etc. in order to judge their claims. Also phrase like "anti-wrinkle peptides" and "sunburn cell reduction" annoy me. What is an anti-wrinkle peptide and where did it come from? The only ingredient that might have peptides in it is the witch hazel (based on the active ingredients listed on the amazon page). What is sunburn cell reduction and how do you measure it? Seeing these claims without any information makes me leery of the product.

I received this product in exchange for my unbiased opinion on it. My thoughts on this product are my own, and I was in no way compensated or reimbursed.

product_title: Shea Moisture Raw Shea Butter Moisture Retention Shampoo with Sea Kelp and Argan Oil 13 Oz (Pack of 2)
review_body:
After months of trying all kinds of remedies to repair my chlorine-damaged hair, I finally found the perfect solution: Shea Moisture Shampoo. Before I started swimming every day, I used home-crafted soaps because I don't want all the nasty chemicals that normally come in soaps and shampoos. But after just a couple weeks of swimming every day, my hair became dry and brittle. I tried everything--regular applications of Argan Oil and other repairing oils, egg and mayonnaise conditioners and commercial, high-end conditioners (even though I don't like the chemicals in them, I was desperate to save my hair!) But my long hair was getting worse (and shorter with breakage) every week. Then I saw this shampoo mentioned in a natural health blog and decided to try it.

The smell is rather strong, but pleasant (I hate, HATE fruity or vegetable-smelling soaps and lotions.) I like the herbal/floral smell of this shampoo. There are no added fragrances, it all comes from the natural oils and butters in the shampoo. If you rinse well, there is almost no smell left in your hair afterwards. The shampoo ingredients are mostly just oils and butters. The cleansing and sudsing is created with oils interacting with decyl glucoside, a natural surfactant that has no known harmful properties.

When I first started using it, I did two washes, rinsing in between. But I needed to use a LOT of shampoo in order to cut through the chlorine and get any kind of sudsing action. At that rate, this bottle wasn't going to last long. What I do now is my first wash is with a home-made shampoo bar to get the chlorine out, then I follow with the Shea Moisture Shampoo for moisturizing. No conditioner needed. I use a few drops of Argan Oil on my towel-dried hair for detangling. The result is clean, soft, tangle-free hair.

The price may seem a bit spendy, but after 6 wks use, I've used a little over 1/2 of the bottle, so I figure it will last me 2-2.5 months, which really isn't bad. And I've saved tons of money not having to get my dried, damaged ends trimmed every month.

I really, really like what this shampoo has done for my hair. I especially like that it has no harmful ingredients and is environmentally safe. I highly recommend this for anyone who struggles with dry, brittle, damaged hair.
(P.S, I am Ross' wife. Ross' hair does just fine with whatever.)

product_title: ANUVA ANTI AGING TREATMENT LINE
review_body:
I have always had thin, fine hair so now as a middle aged women I am really starting to focus on my hair care as part of my anti-aging fight. The pamphlet that comes with this product is very informational and written in easy to understand language regarding not only instructions on how to use the product but a lots of other great information complete with color pictures that were all relevant to taking care of your hair.

The different blends of natural ingredients in these products were pretty cool. The unique ingredients such as turkey tail mushroom, wild yam, saw palmetto berry and many more was exciting to my senses. I liked the smell of all the products. The fragrance hung around a bit which was nice.

I have been using these products for about a week now. The package says you get results in 30 days but I am seeing results now. My hair seems stronger and softer than it did before. My coworker commented yesterday how healthy my hair looked. I have been alternating using the two bottles of liquid drops in the morning. The droppers make it very easy to use and leaves no greasy residue.

product_title: Gelish Complete Starter Kit, 8 Count, 8 Count
review_headline: Great for the penny saver with great nails!
review_body:
I love gelish! It's the most common shellac used in salons so it was the only brand I would buy. Here's my pros and cons.
Pros:
Great final product. As shiny as you see them in the salon. I love how shiny this polish is.
Doesn't chip easy. This stuff usually lasts a solid two weeks. Sometimes a little less if you're hard on your nails. I got a good 10 days out of each application.
Nice colors that come in the kit. The two color that come in the kit are really cute. Especially the glitter.
Cons:
Level of difficulty. The top coat leaves no room for error. It has to be applied correctly. So it will take practice.
Difficulty of removal. Shellac is not easy to remove. Pick it off and you'll be damaging your nails.
Size of lamp. The lamp is tiny. And takes about 3 cycles to actually cure the polish.
Foundation can burn. In the curing process it can actually burn pretty badly for a few seconds. So just be prepared.

I like this product. It's saved me quite a bit of money and kept my nails looking nice!

product_title: Conair Flex Trim Beard and Mustache Trimmer
review_body: This does offer a really good shave from what I can see and hubby says he doesn't experience razor burn. Our button stuck a bit, but I believe it is because it is new. After using it over and over I'm sure the sticking will stop. The good news is the button is sturdy and probably won't break no matter how often he uses it. Our experience in the past with the Conair razors is that they last a long time and usually hold up to multiple uses. My husband has a medium beard and mustache and does not have real thick, course facial hair. You may want to check other reviews to see how it holds up to thicker hair. Because of the angle of the blade and multiple adjustment settings, my guess is it will work well with any hair thickness. It also has a way to use it for fine line trimming, like the hairs on your neck, etc. Just remove the comb. It comes off easily and goes back on with little to no trouble. I would suggest keeping it clean to resist clogging. It has a pivoting head which helps under the chin area and other places not in a straight line. Everyone has their own unique face type and the chin area can cause problems if the blade is not flexible. We did not see any problems with this and it made my hubby's shave cleaner and easier. This cuts down on the time it takes him to shave and trim his mustache too, which is great if you are in a hurry. It does not come with batteries and requires 2 AAA. I would keep backups if you are traveling. Hubby also liked how the angle and sharpness greatly reduced pulling on the hairs.

product_title: MUJI Makeup Facial Soft Cut Cotton Unbleached 60x50 mm 140pcs
review_body:
From a vaper's perspective:

Pros:

- Free shipping to prime members, as an add-on item.
- Authentic organic Japanese cotton (you can even see specs of the seeds in the cotton and Japanese writing on the package, see images).
- Ridiculously large amount. About the size of a ziplock freezer bag full of roughly 2" x 2 1/2" sized squares, 1/4" thick.
- Super fluffy and absorbent. Wicked flawlessly. No weird tastes.
- Probably the best $.0x per pad ratio (about $.054 a pad, currently), especially if you have prime and factor in shipping costs.
- Does not actually ship from Japan, or China. It's a prime add-on item, so it is probably imported to Canada or the US. Got to me in 2 days with prime.
- Unbleached. It is an off-white color and there was no weird taste upon the first few pulls.
- There's 140 pads. That means even if you re-wicked dual coils twice a day you'd get nearly half a year of vaping from one package. More than likely, much more since the cotton is so thick, you would more realistically get 8 coils worth out of a pad instead of 4.

Cons:

- If you have prime, but are only ordering this (or if you don't have prime at all) you will pay some shipping costs.
- English labeling and text on the back or something would be helpful, I'm sure it would demystify the claims of the amazon listing vs the actual manufacture claims, but they all seem to be legit anyway.
- I have no idea where to put this huge bag now.
- Because of the price, it will only encourage you to build more setups because you have extra materials.

Overal:

Look no further for your cotton folks. This pack will hold you over for a long time, even for avid daily vapers. Buy some kanthal and some other stuff with it to nab the free shipping.

product_title: Trichloroacetic Acid Solution TCA 20% Chemical Skin Peel (1 Ounce)
review_body: I really like this product. I used it on my forehead and applied it with a fan brush. I left it on for about 3 minutes but it never frosted.  It  stung so bad so I applied the baking soda pronto! Unfortunately, it pooled between my eyebrows. The skin there started to peel the next day and, stupidly, I peeled that skin. Not what anyone should do! That skin got red and crusty and hurt like heck. I used a triple antibiotic and it took over a week to heal. The skin looks beautiful and young again. Brown spots are almost gone! Deep lines are a lot less noticeable. So I used it on my forearms. Two layers on one arm. Another big mistake! That skin turned a very dark brown (I am light) This time I didn't peel the skin. I am shocked that the brown spots either disappeared or lightened dramatically. Learn from my mistakes and don't peel your skin! I just applied it again tonight onto the last of the spots on my forehead. I would absolutely purchase this product again.

review_body: I bought this at a mall kiosk because it was time to replace my Chi (only because the cord became damaged). I decided to try this out because after telling the sales girl "no" 4 times I got a slightly better price than I would have paid for the Chi. I was initially impressed, but quickly realized that this flat iron sucked the moisture from the ends of my hair super quick leaving me with super dry, split ends ! I never had that problem using my Chi (which I've owned 2 Chi irons for well over 8 years combined). The next thing I noticed is that after only 4 months when I turned on the iron it would start to crackle and pop. There is a lifetime warranty, but with how horrible it has made my hair feel and how quickly the wiring has gone there is no way I'll cash in on that. It does work a little quicker than the Chi, but for the negatives I've experienced I'll stick with the brand I've had no problems with. Back to Chi I go!

product_title: Omega 226 - Razor and Shaving Brush Stand-CHROME
review_headline: Definitely works with the Merkur Futur
review_body: I've been looking for a razor and brush stand that would hold my Merkur Futur for a while. I tried 2 other ones that I purchased on Amazon (don't remember their names) unsuccessfully. I was ready to give up, because I wasn't interested in paying a couple hundred for the Merkur branded stand. Found out about this stand from a razor forum where somewhere recommended it. I ordered not from Amazon but from a certain auction site that we all know and hate from an authorized Omega dealer. The stand works! And it is stamped with the name on the back - I've read some reviews on here where folks said their stands weren't stamped so they were worrying about authenticity. I would recommend.

product_title: InstaNatural Argan Oil Hair Mask - Best Conditioner Treatment for Soft & Silky Hair - With Organic Argan Oil, Organic Jojoba Oil, Coconut Oil, Vitamin B5 & Green Tea - Provides Deep Moisture - 8 OZ
review_headline: Leaves hair soft and not greasy
review_body:
After one use I am hooked. My hair and skin suffer a lot during the winter and I wish I had discovered InstaNatural months ago. I used this hair mask today and I am extremely happy with the results. Background: I have medium length dark brown hair, 75% has been bleached very blond to allow for bright colors to be added which has made my hair damaged and mildly frizzy, and I suffer from moderate dry scalp during the winter months(no dandruff shampoo or other treatments have helped). I followed the directions on the label and massaged into scalp to the tips and let sit on my hair for 15 minutes. A little goes a long way and I barely made a dent in the product. Rinsing took as long as using regular conditioner. I let my hair air dry just to see the full effect.
The mask left my hair shiny, soft, and with minimal frizz! My scalp flakiness has decreased by 80-90%. The portions of my hair that are dyed bright colors seem more intense and my ends are soft, not dry and brittle. I am looking forward to testing this against this summers enemies, sun and ocean water!
Another plus, according to the Amazon description and their own webpage, InstaNatural has a crazy long return policy.

product_title: Blue Weekly Pill Turtle XL With Reminder Clock
review_headline: Please remind me to stop and check the display...
review_body: This was not quite what I was expecting.  I, like many people, NEVER need to be awakened to take my pill. Rather I'm supposed to wait until after I've finished sleeping and then take it.  Therefore, I was hoping that this device's 'flashing reminder' was, for example, an ATTENTION-GETTING little red light that could be seen as one walked past.  Moreover, I hoped that the user could choose between having either an audible alarm sound or a visible flashing light. Such would be wonderful for the deaf as well as those who are hard of hearing.  For most people, I do expect this device works out quite well in keeping medication administration times very regular (Provided they keep this device reasonably nearby their person at all times and remember to habitually, AND without fail, check to see if the little black flag at the top of the display is blinking), .  Perhaps there is someone who sells some sort of alarm with a flashing reminder light that can catch the user's attention in an instant, thereby reminding the user to go look at the unlit display on the 'Turtle'.

product_title: Razor Renew Long Sharpens Smooths Razor Blades
review_headline: Great for him, her AND the kitchen
review_body:
I purchased the Razor Renew strop as a gift for my husband (and quite frankly, myself too) so we wouldn't have to spend so much money on those expensive razor blades. The strop arrived with a clear and concise set of instructions and is made of a fine quality leather with a heavy duty stainless steel clip. We have only purchased 6 razor blades in the 7 months (we usually go through that many in a single month) since we got the Razor Renew and what's even better is that I no longer have to worry about knicking my ankles and knees when I shave because of a dull blade. It also works like a charm to keep my kitchen knives sharp.
The Razor Renew is a superior quality product that goes over and beyond what we expected of it. We are sure to have it for many years to come and have a lot more money to spend on anything but razor blades.

product_title: Heritage Products IPSAB Toothpowder Cinnamon -- 4 oz
review_headline: If you can tolerate the saltiness, you may enjoy it..
review_body:
This tooth powder has been popular throughout the years for being free from all of the nasty chemicals and even animal bi-products. For that, I love the tooth powder. However, I cannot get to like the flavor. IPSAB is so salty it's unbelievable. Considering it's purely baking soda and salt, it's to be expected. I was hoping the cinnamon, Xylitol, and prickly ash would help mask the saltiness a little bit. Unfortunately that's not the case. The cinnamon flavor in mine is barely noticeable, I can smell it more than taste it.

The powder leaves my teeth feeling smooth and polished well, but it also leaves my gums and mouth feeling rather fatigued. I feel this is due to too much salt, it's just overpowering. Unfortunately I will not be buying more of this particular flavor. The cinnamon just needs more oomph in the flavor department. The mint is a bit better in this area.

product_title: PROFESSIONAL STRENGTH - Best HYALURONIC Acid Natural Moisturizer For Your Face, Anti Aging Organic Vitamin C Serum + Vitamin E + Aloe, Best Anti Wrinkle Skin Care Product! 1 YEAR!
review_headline: Quick and Easy way to help hydrate your skin and help decrease the signs of aging.,
review_body:
I'd tried Hyaluronic serum before from other companies. Iâm always curious to find out how other products perform, especially with facial products. I have been blessed with generally good skin. However, as I spend more time outside in the summer at swim meets I've noticed the sun starting to take its toll on my skin. Azure Naturals sent me a bottle to try and offer my honest opinion. I'm totally hooked now! I love the pump so I get just the right amount. It is nice and cool going on. I put in on right after I get out of the shower while my skin is still moist. I also use it at night to help hydrate my skin overnight.

I've noticed a difference and others have too. As the end of summer comes to a close, my friends are asking how I managed not to get so parched being out for hours at the swim meets. This is my secret! Well, it's not so much a secret any more.

I also use it on the tops of my hands at night. Along with a nice moisturizer and gloves, I put it on while watching TV and relaxing in the evening. I've seen a big different in my hands. They're more supple and bright.

I was only using it on my face, but after a week I started putting it on my neck and chest as well since those are areas that are often overlooked and can show signs of aging.

I really like this product and know that seeing results after 2 weeks is just the beginning. It can take 4-6 weeks to see improvement and up to 6 months to experience the full benefit of a daily routine with Hyaluronic. Give it time. Your patience will be rewarded.

My hair dresser uses one that looks very similar (I bought the 2.5" brush), and it's so much easier to style long hair smooth and silky with this! The brush actually holds the hair in place when you wrap strands around it, so you can straighten the hair with the dryer running along it. It works! Great price for a great product.

review_headline: THREE helmets and ALL DID NOT WORK!!!-AT ALL!
review_body:
PLEASE DO NOT WASTE YOUR MONEY! I have received THREE different helmets. All of which were faulty. This company clearly took no care in developing this piece of junk. They also will NOT REFUND YOU! Do not be deceived. Although I have a legal warranty document stating they will refund the product (which they have in fact changed so if you buy one now yours will not say this), there are loopholes and they will never refund anyone.
I used this product for almost a year with the 2nd helmet I received. It did nothing but the most important thing to note is that this product is made SO poorly it will not work for you long term. I have spent enough time at the post office only to receive a NEW helmet which doesn't work. That is TWO I have received that never worked at all.
I am sad that this company is exploiting people's sadness. If there were a cure for hair loss we wouldnt know about it.

product_title: DaLin Full Nail Art Polish Wraps Stickers Nail Decal Decoration, 5 Packs in Different Color, Each Pack include a Nail File
review_headline: I applied a quick dry top coat and it caused some puckering at the edges you may have better success using a standard top coat
review_body: So this is my second experience with nail wraps and it was definitely different than my first with Sally Hansen polish strips. These wraps are similar to vinyl and stiff with a moderately stick backing. I found soaking them in warm water made them more pliable and easier to apply. I applied a quick dry top coat and it caused some puckering at the edges you may have better success using a standard top coat. All in all these held up for about 3 days and probably would have held up longer if a more experienced hand applied them and sealed the edges properly. For the beginners and those hard on nails not the better brand and i would suggest applying a tacky base coat for long term use 1-2 weeks.

product_title: Herbal Essences Color Me Happy Cleansing Conditioner
review_body: I have used WEN in the past and liked it, but not the price. So I decided to look around and see if others were making/selling cleansing conditioners. This was the first one I found so I tried it, having colored treated hair I prefer having something that is made for it. I love this stuff. It is so easy to use, saves using separate shampoo/conditioner combos and takes less time. I use this daily and it makes my hair very soft and shiny, and doesn't leave a coated feeling. I have very short hair, also very fine, thick and color treated and this doesn't make my hair at all greasy, and I have had oily hair my entire life, being the reason I must shampoo daily. The scent is light and not at all over powering like the Loreal cleansing conditioner is. I highly recommend giving this a try. I truly prefer it to WEN, both for price and it is just a great product.

The nice thing about large image plates like this is they will fit all nail lengths and widths, even my super gigantic and wide thumbnail! To give an idea of the size, I am only able to fit the head area on my thumbnail. The images are quite large, so you will not be able to fit the entire body, or the entire lamb etc on your nail. Just parts of it. My one wish for this set would be a little smaller scale of the images, but it's such a unique set that I'm still giving it 5 stars. The leaves on the bottom right are very pretty and almost look like feathers when stamped on the nails. Nice, fine detail overall.

product_title: Youturn Natural Seaweed Powder & Kelp Powder - Use As Cellulite Treatment, Seaweed Face Mask, Or Organic Body Wrap - Contains Caffeine, Retinol, & Hyaluronic Acid - 16oz
review_headline: My face has never felt cleaner. And a little goes a long way!
review_body:
My skin is softer and smoother and my pores are definitely smaller. Probably because they're free of all the pollutants and other crud that this mask helped to extract. (Okay. That was gross but I am totally serious.) Don't let the aroma scare you away. It's a seaweed mask and thus smells like the ocean. There's a reason that spas everywhere offer seaweed facials and wraps. They work!

My face has never felt cleaner. I even let my 12-year-old daughter try it a few days ago. At first, she was unsure but she liked the result afterwards so much that she just asked me if we could do it again. It's an excellent way to prevent future breakouts. And you can't put a price tag on that for a 12-year-old or her (cough)-year-old mother.

I really like that it's in powder form so you can control the consistency yourself. And I've read about some users adding essential oils to it instead of water (which is what I used) to boost the aromatherapy experience. In any event, I'll be using this jar (and sharing it with my daughter!) for a long time because it's very concentrated thus making it a great value for your dollar. A little goes a long way.

review_headline: I do LOVE this cream strictly as a moisturizer
review_body: I bought this product for it's lifting and firming properties. While I can't say I've noticed any difference in the firmness of my jawline, I do LOVE this cream strictly as a moisturizer. Yes, it's pricey, but it's so rich I have to use very little at a time. The fragrance is subtle. It doesn't irritate my eyes (and NO I don't use it in my eye area) like so many moisturizers do. Plus it absorbs immediately. I do not like creams that just seem to sit on top of your skin and "pill up" when you apply makeup. I would definitely recommend this as an excellent moisturizer, but just haven't seen any "lifting and firming" results on my 47-year-old skin. I am at the bottom of my first jar and I do plan to re-order.

product_title: KÃ©rastase Densifique Hair Treatment Set, 30-Pack
review_headline: The closet youâll get to minoxdil in terms of hair âregrowthâ without tight skin, dark puffy eyes pimples and ozzing skin
review_body:
Stemoxydine no matter the brand works if youâre patient enough to regrow youâre hair. Although a completely unique mechanism, it's the closest youâll get to minoxdil in terms of hair âregrowthâ without tight skin, dark puffy eyes pimples and ozzing skinâ¦sound familiar? Anyways, Iâm not talking just maintaining hair growth but actually REGROWING hairs in vacant zones. Biggest downfall is the product takes too long to see visible results. Not sure about 1,700 new hairs in 3 months but development continues on its own without further use. Everything else out there is just a scam (L-arginine, Har Vokse, Copper Peptides, Nanoxidil, Growth Factors, even Phytolium 4) Iâll try to make this review as informative as possible.

After trying Densifique, Neogenic (currently on Redken Cerafill) Iâd have to say the Kerastase range was the most effective in hair regrowth and some thickening. (To be honest minoxidil significantly outperforms this product, its just butchers the skin in exchange). Densifique smells great, each vial contains 6mL x 30. I made my routine 2mL per mornings and night lasting me waaaay over a month. The key here is to more apply in attention (thinning or bald) areas. Let that dry then apply more product. Donât just exhaust it everywhere to get it over with! I take the time to get the product in the areas I really needed it. I used on the beard and I nearly have a full beard. The hairs are so slow in transitioning to terminal no matter how much of the product is applied. However the key is just to get new growth going. Two months into my journey I see the tinniest hairs getting the strength to grow! 4 months later the baby hairs continued to get thicker and thicker even without the product. Would I recommend this product? Yes, but donât expect any overnight miracles. I was frustrated with the lengthy time it took but it works!

product_title: NYX Cosmetics Professional Makeup Color Mascara
review_headline: I really wanted to love this
review_body: This mascara was just okay for me. The consistency of this is quite watery. So when you apply it, it is hard to see and when you try to add more it sweeps away the color that was previously applied. (Strangely, after it dried this color was the hardest to remove...go figure). The applicator brush is very thin and straight. I found that to get the best results, I applied this just the very tips of my lashes. Then you could see a little splash of color. Strangely, on my bottom lashes it worked perfectly, perhaps because they are not as thick as upper lashes. When applied the color looks more on the yellow side than the greenish color portrayed on the bottle. For the price point this mascara is still okay. I am going to play around with different techniques and maybe a lash primer to see if I can get better results.

product_title: Paul Mitchell Platinum Blonde Shampoo Shampoo For Unisex
review_headline: Color is nice, but not the feel
review_body: This shampoo does a decent job of keeping my heavily - highlighted hair from getting brassy. However, even when I use a heavy-duty conditioner with it, it leaves my hair feeling a little dry, stringy and lifeless. I've used the same conditioner with other shampoos and had better results, so I know it is this particular product. Also, while I wouldn't say it smells "bad," it's not exactly a very pretty scent, either. I guess what it comes down to the product does what it's meant to (keeping cool tones in light hair), but I can't say anything else positive about it really. I found a Pantene product at Walmart for around $6 that works just as well (it is labeled for silver hair and doesn't mention blonde, but with the deep violet color it does the same thing) and leaves my hair feeling nicer.

product_title: Maybelline New York Eye Studio Lasting Drama Gel Eyeliner, 0.106 Ounce
review_headline: The best eye liner I've ever used for a fraction of the cost
review_body: I've used pencil, liquid, and powder liner in the past and had issues with all of them--the pencil would smudge under my eyes, the liquid would crack, and the powder would get displaced. I decided to try gel, and I was really happy with this product. The brush is the right size and firmness so that you can achieve either a subtle line or you can layer on the gel for a more dramatic eye. The gel stays in place well without smudging or cracking. If I don't remove my makeup, it can easily last through two days of wear. A very versatile product--this is the best eye liner I've used! The brown is also a very nice color--not too dark but also dark enough that it looks natural. I'd try this before testing out more expensive options.

product_title: Crest 3D White Glamorous White Whitestrips Dental Teeth Whitening Strips Kit, 14 Treatments - Lasts 6 Months & Beyond
review_body:
Not the top of the line, but these are MUCH better than the Classic. They grip onto your teeth so you have to really pull to get them off. The gel works just as well as the Classic but because it stays on better, it has more time to work. With the Classic I always felt like the gel would foam up and slide off my teeth, and I'd have to spit it out. The Advanced Seal keeps it all on the teeth where it should be. These are definitely worth the price difference over the Classic!

I generally don't use the entire box, I'll use maybe 4 strips and space them out every 2 or 3 days because my teeth will get sensitive. 4 strips is about all I need to boost the whiteness back to where it should be. I drink coffee or tea daily, and wine on weekends, so my teeth stain over a matter of months. I only need a few strips to bring them back to white and I save the rest for the next round of whitening.

review_body:
I guess I should start out by saying that I was worried about this product and its consistency, because I have terrible acne and am generally pretty oily. When I first opened the bottle and saw the consistency I became even more worried. BUT I WAS WRONG! I've been using this product for a little over 2 weeks now and WOW! Not only does it do what it claims to do, but I feel that it gives my skin a "matte" finish which is something that doesn't happen for me. Even when I use powdered make up that claims to give you a matte finish, after about an hour or so I am oily and shiny again. Not with this product. And that wasn't even one of their claims. Huge bonus! My acne cleared up dramatically. No sign in wrinkle reduction yet, but I'm sure that takes more than 2 weeks. One thing I did notice is that the appearance of my acne scars has gone down. I can still see them, but they are virtually invisible now under makeup, whereas before... there was nothing I could do to cover them up.

One tip... I found it best to use a toner right before. And after applying the product, waiting about 10 minutes before you start applying your make-up to get the matte-primer effect I was talking about!

product_title: Rocky Mountain Barber Company Boar Hair Beard Brush for Men
review_headline: Rocky Mountain 100% Boar Bristle Beard Brush: Pffft... there's no other brush for me now.
review_body:
TL;DR at the end.

This brush is stupid good. First off, aside from the benefits to your beard and skin from brushing and the benefits of boar hair over other hairs (not really gonna get into that as that stuff is covered at great length elsewhere and you should know this, bearded person!), the brush is just designed really well and has great packaging/a great look.

The Brush:
The brush itself is really sturdy and well made. The grip/handle(is that what you call it?) is a nice solid chunk of wood with a nice look and finish.

The bristles are tightly packed (this is the one thing I might change about the brush as I feel that as my beard gets longer and thicker I might need something with a little breathing room between the bristles) so it really gets a hold of your hairs and moves them along in the direction you're brushing. It's not so tight that it snags your hairs though so don't worry.

The contour. Oh my! I looove the contour of the bristles that they put on this thing. It's just absolute heaven to brush with this onyx badboy as it basically hugs your face, embracing your beard (as well any beard should be!) as you groom your beautiful jaw mane. I think I might over brush a little much just because it's that comfortable and soothing to brush with this brush that I get lost in it. Almost hypnotized. A lot of other brushes are just the flat boring military style brush and they suck. Sure, they get the job done but it's like comparing a 5 minute truck stop handy to a talented hummer. If you can have the one, you're NOT choosing the other.

The Packaging:
Ok, so one thing I'll give the beard care product community in general is... they know their audience. The know manly. They know what's visually appealing to men and they milk it with impressive splendor. Except for a lot of the brushes out there. One of the most popular sellers on here is that boring ass military style one I mentioned in the previous paragraph and I see a lot of other plain humdrum brushes. While I do see SOME that have decided to put some thought into their design(oh, and the combs... ), something about the rocky mountain look just really sticks out and appeals to me.

The brush itself is sleek, contoured(bristles), smooth with a nice woodgrain finish and a prominant logo which, normally I say "Ick!" but I dig their logo. It's a nice design. By itself the brush is a nice enough thing to see on your counter but they went the extra mile with some very nice packaging.

The Box:
It's sturdy... like, nice and sturdy. It's cardboard but it's quality and will serve as a nice display/storage box that you can leave out on your counter with the brush. Inside the box is a foam padded rectangle with a smooth felt side for you to place the brush on bristle side down on which frankly was unnecessary but it's a testament, imo, to how much thought they put into their product from design to packaging and I love them for it. I understand the importance of function over form but dammit, I want both!!

Well, I got it.

Overall TL;DR: It's an awesome brush that looks beautiful and functions even better. The contoured bristles are awesome and really hug your face in a way other brushes don't and actually let you brush more of your beard at once in single strokes. The look and packaging are above and beyond so much that it's pretty much like you get a free display case and counter top decoration with your order.

Don't be foolish and get another brush when clearly, this is your only option.

review_headline: Love it!  Really cool how this color changing polish works!!!
review_body: This is SO cool.  It is amazing how it goes from very pale green to very dark green so quickly.  When my hands are cold or even cool, it is dark green.  When they are warm it is pale green/almost white.  And sometimes only parts of the nail (tips mostly) are dark green.  And so far the manicure has lasted a week - similar to other gel polishes I have used.  Just dipping a finger in cold water turns the polish dark green. review_body: I prefer using this Kojie San Kojic Acid Skin Whitening soap.  I tried another professional strength kojic soap and was not as impressed as I am with Kojie.  Honestly, I used this soap 2x's a day for 3 weeks.  I noticed a difference in my skin's texture, smoothness, clarity, pore shrinkage, and lightening of brown spots that were very noticeable before and now it has been lightened by 1-2 shades.  I am confident that with continued use, it will be completely faded.  I gave it four stars because I am impatient and want these dark spots (used all types of lighteners before and was disappointed with the results) to disappear!  I will keep using until discoloration is gone!

product_title: Remington WDF4840 Women's Smooth and Silky Foil Shaver, Purple
review_body: I purchased this shaver when my cheap Panasonic Wet/Dry died. Thought I'd try something a bit more expensive, since my Panasonic lasted only three years before it died. I knew what to expect as far as closeness of shave, etc. I did not expect the razor burn! I used the Remington exactly as I had used my Panasonic, with some shave gel to help prevent burn. I could feel the Remington tearing my skin and pulling out the hair as I shaved. It left my skin more inflamed than I have ever seen, and took a lot of lidocaine and lanolin to extinguish the flames. I will return to my Panasonic. I was not a fan of the trimmer attachment on the Remington, and prefer the extendable trimmer on the Panasonic. The Remington is not good at trimming in tight spaces, if you know what I mean.

review_headline: Great for holding hair without pulling it out
review_body:
These are great for thick hair. You can loop them around to get a better hold and fit, without making them so tight that they pull on your hair. Rubber bands have good hold, but tend to be so tight that they pull out some hair with each use. These are much more gentle on hair. Both my daughter and I have been using these for a few weeks now and they have been my go-to hair ties. They hold hair, but aren't uncomfortable like traditional hair rubber bands can be. product_title: Heritage Products Rosewater, Rose Petals, 8-Ounces (Pack of 3)
review_headline: The BEST For Parched, Dry, Brittle, Damaged Hair!
review_body:
WOW this stuff is great! I did an at-home keratin treatment a few months ago and ever since, my hair has been extremely dry, brittle and impossible to detangle. I've done loads of research and become a product junkie in the process of searching for something to return my hair to it's pre-keratin state. High-end, low-end you name it! I've tried it. I have sprayed this in my hair twice a day since I bought it three days ago and oh my goodness it has done WONDERS for my hair! It finally feels like normal hair and not some crispy crunchy stuff on top of my head. My hair is super soft, shiny and very easy to detangle. I have also noticed significantly less breakage. I think the texture of hair that grows out of my head is 3c and the length of my hair is more loosely curled and wavy (3b maybe?) from straightening it and damage from the keratin treatment. No matter what I do, if I wear my hair curly it ends up all fluffed up by the end of the day. I don't mind that, but if I spray this in it while it's all fluffy it'll curl right back up onto nice, defined curls which water alone doesn't do!! I plan to use it when I straighten my hair as well, it is replacing my chemical-laden leave-in conditioner. I'm going to just spray it in my damp hair after washing it, put a heat protectant serum on top, let it air dry, then flat iron. I'll come back and update when I've been using it for a couple months.

In conclusion:
-This rosewater is AMAZING. It has brought my extremely damaged hair back to life.
-It smells heavenly
-I bought it at my local Whole Foods
-Costs $8.99
-I used it by mixing 75% rosewater and 25% distilled water in a spray bottle (I did this because the one that I bought did not come with a spray top and I also read that rosewater strengthens your hair in some way and I just wanted to err on the side of caution and dilute it a bit. Since I'm recovering from protein overload my hair certainly doesn't need any help in the strength department.)

product_title: Aria Starr Beauty ORGANIC Argan Oil (4 OZ) For Hair, Skin, Face, Nails, Beard & Cuticles - Best 100% Pure Moroccan Anti Aging, Anti Wrinkle Beauty Secret, EcoCert Certified Cold Pressed Moisturizer
review_body:
This is an awesome oil! It's a bright, clear, pale straw-colored clean oil with a very mild, almost-not-there fresh scent. The dropper bottle is easy to use and the oil seems like it's high quality.

The first time I tried argan oil, I put a number of drops on one arm, and initially was not too happy because it left my arm feeling slightly oily for a long time. I wiped the excess off and it was fine. Later that night, I noticed the skin of that arm was deliciously soft. Smooth, pettable soft. *Perfect* soft.

I've since decided that the oiliness was my fault; I simply used too much. That's great, because this is an expensive luxury oil and if a few drops will cover a large area, that's perfect. My next discovery: after getting out of the shower, while your skin is still slightly damp, apply some argan oil. It will help retain some of that moisture, and the damp will help you spread a small amount of oil more easily. It made my skin feel amazing. Dare I suggest this treatment if you have a romantic evening planned?

product_title: GIGI Kit Honee Strip Free Hair Removal System
review_body:
I didn't want to buy a whole home waxing system with the warmer and whatnot so I thought this kit would be great to try first. This was my first time waxing at home and my second wax altogether (first was a Brazilian) and I'd say it worked okay.

The process of waxing both my legs took about 2 1/2 hours and I did it on my own. My pain threshold to waxing seems to be rather low so the process was pretty painless for me. Maybe once or twice did I actually mumble an "ow" but that was towards the end when I was getting lazy and applying the wax on too thick. I had to go over a few spots at least one more time towards the end to get all the hair off but that's to be expected especially since those hairs were short. I also had to microwave the wax for 15 seconds 5 other times because it kept hardening and I figured I would need to since I didn't have a warmer to keep it a stable temperature.

The extra bottles are not needed as you can easily take off any remaining wax with baby oil and get off as much as you can with the strips. I'd say go for the wax only and buy some wax sticks and cloth elsewhere.

All in all, the process was just too messy to ever do again at home but since I don't want to pay exorbitant amounts of money to wax my legs, I'm going to try some cloth free systems for next time.

product_title: 20 Feather Razor Blades NEW Hi-stainless Double Edge
review_headline: Sharp and long-lasting. An excellent value.
review_body:
As a regular Derby and Wilkinson user, I kept promising myself that I would try a Feather blade to see if it lived up to its legendary status with my face.

What I discovered is that the shave itself is about the same from all three blades to me, but the Feather blade holds its sharpness longer. I would replace a Derby blade every other day, but a Feather will last me a week to 10 days. So, even though they're more expensive, they're a better value because each blade shaves for much longer.

With all blades, your mileage may vary, so find a 5-pack before purchasing this (or a sampler that includes a Feather) to be sure the blade is good for your face.

review_headline: Head doesn't last 3 months, charger base is down after 8 months...
review_body:
I would give it 5 stars if none of these problems happen to me.

This is absolutely the most expensive toothbrush in my life, so is the maintenance of it. Because I thought this is it, the ultimate toothbrush that will stay with me for years.

However it turns out that the head doesn't last 3 months (they are pretty expensive too), maybe around 2 months, and it gives me an annoyingly loud and harsh sound every time I turn it on.

Then there's the pain in the ass, after almost 8 months of use, the charger base stops working. I didn't use it very often because I'm travelling a lot from home (I think I only used it for 4 months and it is not plugged in most of the time!!!). I don't know where to get this repaired or replaced... Anyone??

As for a toothbrush, it does work a lot better than the others, it looks great too. I don't know, maybe I'm not that lucky, but it seems like the quality control is poor...

If you don't notice a difference drink plenty of water and review your nutrition.  Sometimes things you eat can nullify the beneficial effects of this and other great herbal combinations. All of the negative reviews I've found I could personally see their errors.  I think others who have used this can see the same errrors.  This stuff is great!!! 12/18/2015   I'd just like to add an addition to my original comments above.  I've been using this stuff on and off for the past 3 years.  I've noticed as long as I'm taking this stuff regularly I don't get sore muscles after sports or strenuous work.  I may feel a little stiff the next day but it goes away quickly.  If you buy Dr Christopher's book the "School of Natural Healing" it gives all the formulas with their proportions in the back of the book.  A lot of times I buy the formulas but sometimes I make them up myself with variation (of course) according to what my body needs.

review_headline: The whitestrips were very easy to work with and I didn't feel any sensitivity ...
review_body: The whitestrips were very easy to work with and I didn't feel any sensitivity to them at all when I wore them for 30 min. I thought the grip was pretty strong on my teeth and was able to stay on for the whole 30 min. I did find that the sides weren't as sticky but I assumed that to be from limited contact to the teeth as it stretched across. Unfortunately I didn't notice a huge difference in the whiteness of my teeth. There was some whiteness but I was expecting a greater difference. I would recommend this product if you are looking to whiten your teeth but don't expect amazing results. If I were to try whitestrips again, I might try another kind to see if I could get a greater difference in whiteness. But it is a great product and it arrived very quickly and the packaging wasn't damaging or anything so it wasn't a bad purchase.

product_title: Pantene Pro-V Conditioner, Repair & Protect with Keratin, 12 Ounce
review_headline: Satisfying results on my processed hair
review_body:
I have fairly short (ear lobe length) hair I had been coloring brown for a while, and recently decided to go platinum and had it bleached, so it's been through a lot of processing. Needless to say, I need to use conditioner after every shampoo to have my hair be soft enough to brush out after the shower instead of feeling like tangled hay.

I've been using the Repair & Protect Conditioner for 3 weeks as a daily conditioner, and am very pleased with the results. It is easy to apply, not too thin or too thick. It rinses out easily, not leaving a thick or greasy feel behind, including on my neck & upper back which often happens with thicker repair-type conditioners. And finally, my hair is soft for both brushing out and for styling, looking smooth and healthy throughout the day, despite the processing I've put it through!

The fragrance is light and pleasant. The bottle cap is the flip-open style, and is easy to open. The bottle has a slightly matte finish, so it doesn't get all slippery in wet hands. These may seem like extras, but details like this are important when it comes to a product I use every time I shower.

review_body: I received a free box of Vidal Sassoon Salonist Hair Color from the manufacturer to try out but I am not being paid to write this review. I absolutely loved this hair color. I've been dying my hair at home for many years and this product is by far my favorite. I LOVE that it comes with an applicator brush and mixing tray. I wish all hair color kits came with these. They make it a million times easier to apply the color exactly the way you want it. This dye kit has a 2 step process when others only have a one step but the the two steps don't take any more time or difficulty than other kits. The conditioner that comes in this kit smells AMAZING and made my hair feel very soft. The dye did not dry out my hair at all like some other brands do. The color looked great and lasted much longer than other brands. With other brands my gray hairs will show back up after only a week or two but with Vidal Sassoon Salonist Hair Color my gray stayed covered for many weeks. I am a big fan of this product and do not plan to use any others ever again.

product_title: L.A.B.2 Just Face it Kabuki Brush, 1.619 Ounce
review_headline: Just Face it Kabuki is just better
review_body:
I have been using my cheap kabuki brush for a long time; I have liked it and it has served me well. After awhile, as I have read, bacteria forms on the brush. Anyway, it is time for a new one, so here we are.
The brush bristles are called, \\"Fiberluxe Technology\\", so from my vantage point, I am throwing away a kabuki brush with bristles that catch, as if uneven, when I brush them on my palm swishing around back and forth; vs. the new one (L.A.B.2), which has a smooth-bristle action. The bristles feel very soft, and the application of blush and highlighter is not heavy or blotchy.

I have darker age spots that usually get discolored when I am applying blush. The highlighter was too shiny before as well. So, I learned a new trick, as the box says to lightly tap off the excess product before applying. The soft, even bristles do help the application.
As you can see, this brush is short. The handle is maybe 1/3 the size of conventional ones. It didn't diminish my experience with this product; it is supposed to feel natural.

It did for me.

I recommend this product.

product_title: Philips Sonicare Healthywhite Rechargeable Electric Toothbrush
review_body:
Context: I do one thorough cleaning at bedtime with flossing. I do quick cleaning after meals and after getting up in the morning. I've brought it on two trips - a 2 week trip and a 1 week trip without bringing the charger. I've had it for 3 months now.
This is my first sonicare. I got it because my dentist stated that I'm brushing too hard and wearing down my gums.

Pros:
-Convenient - Should've gotten this thing years ago. Just slap a dab of toothpaste, and I use the traditional mode of 2 minutes. (1 minute for behind the row of teeth and 1 minute for front of row of teeth and repeat for the other row. I then add in 1 minute to brush the molar surface)
Cleans easy and place back into charger.

- Easy to remove brush and clean buildup at attachment site

- Easy to pack in its plastic case and throw into my toilet bag.

-Easy on my gums

-Easy for superficial cleans where I sweep over the front/back of each row of teeth and molars and tongue in the morning to wipe off the " ager sleep morning goo" and after meals.

-Didn't have to worry about it holding a charge for 2 weeks of vacation.

-Great investment in terms of time and money.

Cons:
-Haven't found any yet. I know other reviews didn't like certain features, but this is my first one, and I'm fine with the modes it offers. I only use the traditional mode.

product_title: Remington F5-5800 Foil Shaver, Men's Electric Razor, Electric Shaver, Black
review_body: Well this is a little hard to review, because I am a wet D/E shaver. And I love to shave with my D/E razors. My first electric razor was a Remington corded in 1957. There I gave away my age. I am 74. I am stumbling along thinking where to start.I am using a Razor Rock Stealth Slant for my #1 razor. I use many razors known & and unknown. Anyway what I will tell you now some people may think I am not very smart. I got the razor as advertised & reviewed. What caught my eye was the fact that you could wash it with water from the faucet. They also say that you should not shave with this razor in the shower. That is because you can use this razor plugged into a electrical outlet. Here is the problem for Remington. They don't want to electrocute yourself. I am not telling you to use it the way that I do. I'm just telling you how I use this razor.  I used this razor with a pre-shave lubricant when I got it. I was not impressed. @ this point I was going to send it back. I thought about it for a few days before I was going to send it back. Water washable head. That let me try it not plugged in to the wall. Plus This thing has a great battery. I prepared my face like I was going to shave with my D/E razor. I showered, CAME OUT OF THE SHOWER. Then I churned up some Proraso you could about use any soap Dove for one. Just in your hands with out a brush. The 5800 is not super aggressive so you almost have to use a clean up pass. I shave more in an up & down motion all over my face. After that I wet my face a little & re lather not to much. Now I use the circular motion like the rotary razors. My God this makes this machine my special shave day tool. I still use my D/E razors I still love them. Just to let you know I have used Philips, Panasonic, Shick electric, Ronson,Braun, Eltron & probably 3 more that most people don't know of. I have used Titanium, the Remington Diamond cutters & screens. I know that Remington has Titanium cutters that fit the 5800 system. I didn't like the reviews on those. But I may try them. I may think out of the box, but all I can say is that if this tool is used correctly it will reward you. Between my Razor Rock Stealth & the 5800, I can shave to any level of BBS.

I'm definitely noticing less hair loss (on my pillow, in the drain, etc) and my patchy areas are looking fuller. My hair stylist even noticed a difference! I see many other reviewers complaining about the price but in my opinion, it's beyond worth it!

I definitely recommend this product to anyone tired of hair growth pills and creams that don't work. Be patient with this product and you will see results!

product_title: Vidal Sassoon Salonist Hair Colour Permanent Color
review_body: I was  at first nervous about my Vidal Sassoon Kit.  I hadn't tried the brand in years and this kit had a lot of pieces, but after watching the video on the VS Site, I was ready to become beautiful. The kit contains a two-step process, one which involved "painting" the roots and hairline with a brush and then after 20 minutes, adding the color serum to the rest of hair.  Easy.  I had no troubles at all applying the dye and the odor wasn't offensive.  I did get some on my sink but it wiped up right away and it wasn't due to dripping, it was due to my clumsiness.  After another 10 minutes, I washed the product out and used the VS shampoo that is supplied in the box and the conditioner instantly made my hair feel soft.  I could tell right away getting out of the shower that my hair was darker than I normally do it but that is okay, especially during winter months.  After blow-drying some of the wet out, I could tell right away I loved it.  The color is a rich chocolate brown and VERY shiny.  My hair styled easy and the lingering scent was nice, not over-powering like some other brands.  I got compliments on my hair color at work too.  One person even asked where I get my hair done.  It was fun to see the puzzlement on their face when I gave them my home address. Thanks Vidal Sassoon!

product_title: Green Tidings All Natural Deodorant, Extra Strength All Day Protection; 2 Sizes; Unscented or Lavender (Vegan, Certified Cruelty Free)
review_headline: I am a customer for life! This is a game changer for me!
review_body:
I can't tell everyone how thrilled I am with this product! I have had quite an embarrassing issue with only one arm pit for at least 2 years now...Trying every deodorant on the market from natural to clinical strength...Nothing worked! The only thing I could do was reapply several times per day... This little gem actually worked!!!! I recently went Paleo and have been tring to switch over my personal products and toiletries as well. After reading an article on how bad the chemicals such as aluminum is in our deodorants, I found Green Tidings on Amazon and with so many good reviews, I figured I would give it a shot but not having high hopes. It may be pricey but so worth it for me. I will never use another deodorant again.

Please note this stopped any and all odors for me but did not stop the sweating under one arm. The instructions do say to wait a month for that...However, I read another article on how to detox your arm pits with bentonite clay...I use it for my face so I figured why not...It may just stop the sweating sooner than a month and rid the toxins from my body. Sure enough it did exactly that! I did that on Friday and for the rest of a very active weekend, no sweat and no odor thanks to Green Tidings! Kudos to you guys and your product! I can honestly say you have changed my life and I no longer need to be embarrassed or worry about the massive amounts of chemicals I was applying and reapplying daily.

review_headline: One Aloe to rule all problems.
review_body: I've had it for over one and half years and still have over half of the canister left. I started religiously using it a month ago as a cleanser to great results. No real acne, definitely has been healing my sun damaged forehead which has plagued me for years. I was thinking about getting an aloe plant once this runs out to eat and use but I'm not sure this will ever run out. A lot goes a long way, plus this is so easy to use. Maybe I'll get the plant just to eat/drink the aloe. It's great on sun burn, for healing damaged skin, not great for getting rid of dry skin. My choice for a cleanser/moisturizer in the summer. If you get an oily T-zone like me in the summer try this, just put it on before you go to bed and wash it off in the shower in the morning. It helps. I'll be buying another canister once I run out and maybe a plant too.

review_headline: I reduced this posting from 5 start to 4 stars because I believe the manufacturer has reduced the quantity in the bottle
review_body: 1/3/16 - SPOILER ALERT!!!!!!!!  I reduced this posting from 5 start to 4 stars because I believe the manufacturer has reduced the quantity in the bottle and I barely had enough to finish coloring my hair the last two times.   I am sick of a manufacturer taking a really good product and degrading it!!!  OLD POSTING FROM ABOUT A YEAR AGO.  Love Preference and this hair color.  I began using it years ago and have tried other brands over the years, but always come back to this brand and color.  Using this, my hair looks a little less bright than the picture on this box, but I think my hair looks a more natural blond than this.  No one knows I color my hair unless I tell them because this looks so natural.  When my hair was medium brown (a few years ago:)) I had to use a drabber to keep it from being brassy.  Now that my hair is mostly white underneath, I don't have to use the drabber and my hair is still the same color or close enough to the color it was when I had brown hair under it.  It is harder to color white or gray hair and some products just don't do the job.  This one does, although I leave it on longer than I did when hair was brown.  1/3/16 - SPOILER ALERT!!!!!!!! product_title: EmaxDesign Makeup Brushes 24 Pieces Professional Makeup Brush Set Foundation Blending Blush Eyeliner Face Liquid Powder Cream Purple Handle Cosmetics Brushes Tool Kit With Rose Red Case
review_body:
This 24 piece makeup brush kit has a brush for all your makeup needs. The lightweight handles are a pretty shade of purple that contrast nicely with the black metal ferrule. The bristles are light in color with a darker colored tip which makes the entire brush look very nice!

The case is a roll up type case with an individual pocket to hold each brush. The case is a deep rose color which also looks great with the color of the brushes! There is a magnetic snap that keeps everything closed up tight until needed. The case is supposed to be leather, I'm not an expert on leather but in my opinion it is more of a 'leather-like' material and not the real thing.

There is a very strong chemical/plastic type smell, I did notice it when I opened the bag. The company is aware of it as they have included a small card along with the brushes that recommend washing and soaking the brushes in a mild shampoo solution for 30 minutes before using for the first time to remove the odor. For regular cleaning wash your brushes with mild shampoo and rinse, then shape the bristles with a paper towel and let them finish drying with the bristles facing up in a cup so they keep their shape.

There are fans brushes, powder brushes, shadow and foundation brushes, eye & lip liner brushes, contoured brushes, brushes that are angled,... there's even an eyebrow & eyelash brush, this kit has them all! The bristles are soft and the colors are so pretty and girly. This kit would make a nice gift for anyone that enjoys using makeup!

Free product sample received in exchange for review purposes.

product_title: Revlon Colorsilk Beautiful Color
review_headline: The most GENTLE bleach I've ever used!
review_body: I can't believe my hair feels this good after using this dye TWICE on my head in two days. I usually buy Ion Color Brilliance(and a 20 vol developer) from Sally's, and it's always worked well for me. At least I thought it did. I didn't feel like going to Sally's and so got this instead. I started at a medium/dark blonde with light blonde highlights. This brought my hair up to a pale buttery yellow on the first use. Which was nice and I was satisfied with, however... I was WAY more satisfied with HOW MY HAIR FELT! It barely felt like it had been damaged and was still so soft! I couldn't believe it. I'm so pleased with this product.  The second time I put coconut oil on my hair a few hours before hand and then used the bleach again and it still feels SO great. It's a almost white now and will only need to be toned(I'll be using Wella White Lady) to look perfectly white like I want.I use a keratin packet and an argon oil packet afterwards and will continue to once every few weeks or whenever I feel like it's needed. I needed to get all the color out of my hair to go pastel pink. This product is fantastic and it'll be my go to from now on. It's more expensive in the long run than buying my bleach at Sally's, but I feel like the convenience and the quality of the product definitely make that worth it.

product_title: Laila Ali LADR5601 Turbo Ionic Dryer, Purple and Gold
review_body: I want to give this dryer negative stars, but unfortunately that isn't an option.  The comb design is horrible and completely broke after the second time I used it.  First it kept popping off, and then the dumb thing just completely broke even though I was using it gently and on fully combed through hair.  I like to switch between the high and low settings, but the lever that you use to switch settings is really flat and difficult to slide up and down.  Also, like some of the other reviewers, my dryer sparked...like it had some internal lightning bolt action going on within.  I loathe this dryer and will never purchase another Laila Ali product again.
