product_title: ASLAVITAL MINERALACTIV, Collagen Ampoules (Organic Goji Berry Extract/ 100% Natural Clay) (FOR EXTERNAL USE ONLY!)
review_headline: Great Occasional Treatment for Glowing Skin
review_body:
These Collagen Ampoules by Aslavital Mineralactiv contain a paraben free serum rich in goji berry extract and mineral clay. The serum is applied to clean skin and works at a cellular level to regenerate, moisturize, and tone skin. I was initially a little nervous about breaking the ampoule open but I followed the directions and wrapped it in a small washcloth with the breaking point forward. I had no trouble breaking the ampoule open and found that I really liked the scent of the serum. I poured the serum into my hand and used my fingertips to apply the serum to my face and then massage it into my skin. The serum makes my skin feel more moisturized and healthy. I would recommend using this treatment every few months to keep skin looking fresh and healthy.

I received this product at a discounted rate in order to provide an honest and unbiased review. All opinions expressed are my own.

product_title: Luxie Beauty Rose Gold Large Angled Face Brush 504
review_headline: This Angled Brush Gives Excellent Control for Contouring my Faceâ¦and No Shedding!
review_body:
This Luxie Rose Gold Large Angles Face Brush is perfect for contouring my face! I load it with bronzer, begin at the top of my ear and sweep down my cheekbone for perfect contouring that gives my cheekbones excellent definition. I just brush it across a tissue and can use this same brush to apply my blush with accuracy. I have never had an angled brush before and am impressed with how much easier it is to apply my makeup.

This brush is incredibly soft and pretty to use. I have washed it a number of times so far with no shedding (and I have done quite a bit of research before purchasing this brush, and shedding can be a problem with low-quality brushes). I recommend it.

review_body:
I received the wrong product. I have used Shave Secret many times and like it, and I wanted to try Shave Deluxe this time.
So I put in an order for a product advertised as Shave Deluxe, with a picture showing the label "Shave Deluxe" about which shavesecret.com states:
QUESTION: What is the difference between Shave Secret and Shave Deluxe?
ANSWER: Both have the same base blend but Shave Deluxe has two additional high quality cold pressed nut oils which have high emollient qualities to moisturize and condition.
But instead of receiving Shave Deluxe, I received instead Shave Secret. The price was higher for Shave Deluxe compared to Shave Secret. I am disappointed but it is not worth the hassle to me to return the Shave Secret and hope that I can somehow get the Shave Deluxe.

product_title: Brow Powder Duo
review_headline: Great product but the wrong color.
review_body: This was totally the wrong color for me.  The two colors have a red undertone and are therefore too warm for my more neutral brows.  However, the formula is very pigmented and once applied, it lasts all day.  I apply it with a Japonesque brow brush, which is stiff and helps me get the color precisely distributed.  I use both the Brow Wiz pencil and the powder which perfectly match each other.  I first sketch the outline along the upper line of my brows defining the arch.  I then fill in the bald spots with the pencil.  I then brush on the powder along my entire brow.  The powder blends seamlessly with the pencil, creating a very polished look.  I then go over both brows with a spoolie brush, making sure the powder is even.  Then I use the Anastasia brow gel to lock my wayward brow hairs in place.  These three products give me a nice defined brow that frames my entire face, making it look very polished.  I love these Anastasia brow products.  I especially appreciate that the pencil, powder and brow gel all match.  I definitely recommend Anastasia products.

review_headline: Good Product but maybe not for the darkest black hair.
review_body: I have been dying my hair for many years and it is blue black, about as dark as it gets. Ive used this product twice now and both times used the whole box which negates to 4 treatments. review_headline: Buy this now for a better sleep.  So much better than the Swift FX.
review_body: This unit is awesome.  I used the older swift unit and always had trouble trying to find a position that would not create noise.  The exhaust would always blow on something and make noise or blow cold air on my wife.  This new unit is so quite no matter what position I sleep in or what is near it and you don't feel a breeze more than a few inches from it.  It is much easier to handle when tossing and turning and keeps a good seal.  I can't say enough good things about this unit.  BUY IT!  You won't regret it.  The only negative (small one) is that the nasal pillows seem to be firmer than those on the swift, but not really a comfort problem after the first day.  Again, BUY IT!  You won't regret it.    Update: I have noticed a few issues.  Since the strap is a one piece unit, you can't place any additional padding which might help with imprinting on the scalp for us bald guys.  Also, it adjusts by spreading the straps apart.  I would like to be able to make it a little looser than I can currently make it.  If they offered one size larger and maybe a little wider straps to distribute the force, it would be even better.

product_title: Eyebrow Brush By Bella & Bear. Our Spoolie Is The Perfect 2 In 1 Angled Brow Brush Duo For Your Eyebrows And Lashes
review_headline: WONDERFUL EYEBROW AND EYELASH BRUSH BY BELLA & BEAR
review_body:
I am a fan of great makeup brushes. This "Iberian Lynx" brush by Bella and Bear suits me perfectly. The brush is double ended, one end being a spoolie , the other end being a slant tipped brush. The spoolie end is well made with many synthetic soft bristles to coax and curl your flirty eyelashes. You can also use this spoolie to help separate your lashes after applying mascara. If you are more of a natural girl, you can even use the spoolie end to put coconut oil or sesame seed on your lashes to help them grow and shine. The slant tipped brush with natural fibers can be used with brow powder to fill in sparse eyebrows. Full eyebrows is the key to looking youthful! You could also use this slant tipped brush to apply eye shadow as eye liner. It could be used wet or dry, depending on your preference. The Eyebrow Brush is well made, the brush ends are nice and tight unlike the cheaper made brushes I have used. To top it all off, the box this comes in is gorgeous, and it hold the brush between foam so the bristles and fibers will hold their shape forever. This would make a fantastic gift for anyone that loves makeup! I am thoroughly impressed and hope to purchase more brushes from Bella & Bear. I am including several pictures so you may see the quality and presentation of this brush.
I purchased this brush at a reduced cost in return for an honest and unbiased review. I am so glad to have discovered this brand of brushes.

product_title: Red by Kiss Handle-Less Dryer
review_body:
I bought this bc a hair stylist mentioned this dryer in a beauty blog post. She claimed it was convenient to pack away in her gym bag AND is now her go-to dryer while she's at home. After using for a few months, everyone else in my family keeps stealing mine from me too--despite my mom having the popular Conair Infiniti pro dryer. Here's why:

1. Handle-less makes this easier to hold than normal hair dryers (actually, normal hair dryers seem unwieldy after using this). NO JOKE. I wrap my hand around the barrel of the dryer (where it is labeled "Handle Less 1875W"). The barrel of the dryer is not hot to the touch.
2. This is lighter-weight than most dryers.
3. It dries my hair just as fast as my other dryers.
4. It suits my needs. I have lots of long straight medium-textured hair. After running styling cream through my hair, I use the dryer on the hottest setting and just dry my damp hair up-side down. Then when it's mostly dry, I dry the rest of it on a warm setting

I knocked off one star bc I wish this had:

1. A longer power cord.
2. A cool shot. There is a "cold" setting but sometimes it's just barely cool--not actually cold.
3. A nozzle that didn't fall off so easily.
4. An ionic setting--to help with frizz when I need it.

But other than the con's, I love this dryer. I highly recommend.

product_title: Aloe Life SG Mist Gel
review_headline: Aloe Life Cools And Helps Heal Hemorrhoids!!!
review_body: I have severe chronic hemorrhoids stemming from IBS. Whenever I have a bowel movement, my hemorrhoids (or piles, as the Brittish call them) flare up something fierce. I have found that what works best is mixing this aloe gel with peppermint essential oil on a piece of toilet paper and applying as you would a tucks pad. The aloe draws heat out of the inflamed area and the peppermint cools it -- dual action. I use this when wiping to cool and lubricate and I use 1/4 of a blue automotive paper towel instead of tp to make a pad to "wear" all day. Serves sane purpose as a Tucks medicated pad, but isnt toxic and actually works to heal, not just soothe. In fact, were it not for the root cause of IBS still being an issue, Im sure it would be healed already.

review_body:
terrible.

i just colored my hair tonight with this. my hair has been bleached enough to the point where it is already white, so it should have no problem taking the color of this, right? that's what i thought. upon looking in the mirror before i washed it out, i saw it had left purple specks in my hair, along with what looked like streaks of brown. i figured it was just my imagination, or because i had my glasses off.

i washed the dye out, dried it, and somehow it left streaks of brown throughout my hair, and the color didn't even take. my hair is the same color and it now looks like i have skids marks. i followed the directions perfectly so i don't know how or why it turned out so badly. i now have to re-bleach my hair and look for a better hairdye.

product_title: Trophy Skin Rejuvaderm MD Microdermabrasion System
review_headline: It works on the first use.
review_body:
There were accidently two of these delivered and the first one I opened didn't have the filters in the box. So check before you use the device.
I use to get microdermabrasion at the dermatologist and this device works but removes less layers of skin. I definitely think it is better than the non- diamond head devices on the market and I am hoping with continued use I will see more dramatic result.
I am a very pale skinned women of Irish decent and I didn't have any of the red marks or problems other reviewers mentioned, but perhaps that is because I was careful and moved the device over the skin rather than let it rest in any one spot. I followed the directions exactly.
Two hours after I used it I went out for dinner and movie with friends and noticed that my face felt softer and my make up went on smoothly, which is the result I am used to from microdermabrasion. The device does fill up with dead skin after one use so you have to take it apart and clean it thoroughly. Personally, I think that's fine as that allows me to see the results, but if you think you won't clean it don't buy this device. If it does not keep removing skin after the first use I will return it, but I am hoping it is just a slower milder process and I will review again after I have used it on a regular basise.
Meanwhile I have to mail back the device that came without the

product_title: Maybelline New York Fit Me Matte Plus Poreless Foundation Makeup, 1 Fluid Ounce
review_body:
I was using Rimmel's Lasting Finish and was fairly satisfied with the staying power of it, but since they reformulated it, I was getting breakouts and it was looking cakey after just a couple of hours. It also didn't last nearly as long after they messed with it.

So, I was watching some reviews on drug store foundations, and this sounded like one I would like. I have some redness in my skin, and my skin is normal with a bit more oil in the Tzone. I tend to break out easily. I have been using Hard Candy's primer with a green tint under this to combat the redness, and then with a damp beauty blender I go in with the Fit Me foundation. I really love it. It gives good coverage and it's easy to build up more where I need - like my nose, around my mouth and chin. Very blendable. Looks quite natural. I let it dry for a few minutes before setting with powder. Amazing results! I love this makeup. It doesn't break me out, and it gives great coverage. I would give it 5 stars if it had a pump, because it is rather thin and pours out very easily if you aren't careful.

product_title: Detangling Hair Brush â Gentle Detangler Hair Brush & Comb â Pain Free & No More Tangles â Reduce Hair Loss and Breakage â Great for Adults & Kids
review_headline: Highest recommendations for ANYONE with long hair that tangles to get one of these - they are a HUGE time saver for me
review_body:
Free product provided for evaluation and review.
I received the BLUE version.

My first thought when I first saw a brush like this was \\"OMG it's just a plastic brush, why's it so expensive??.\\" I wasn't impressed by its looks. . I was just out of the shower and I'd conditioned my below the waist length hair - it is VERY long, and fine- and was prepared to use a wide tooth comb and 20 minutes of my time to detangle it, but that's when I found the real value of a brush like this.

Massive tangle attacks happen to me every so often. Usually I throw my hair over the top of the bed but sometimes it works it's way down and I wake up with it just a mess. I use a silk pillow case, and do everything I know to do to keep tangles down, but sometimes they still seem to happen all at once.

This brush though - this plastic brush- just zips right down the length of my hair, getting all the tangles out, wet or dry. It's the design that really matters. It's curved, and the bristles are set wide, and are thick and the part through the hair in order. When I get a BIG snag, I just hold that section and concentrate on it for a few seconds and that's all it takes. A normally 20 minute job is now about 1-2 minutes long.

This brush is my new best friend. It's going to save me so much time, and let me grow my hair even longer. Bottom line: It works.
Highest recommendations for ANYONE with long hair that tangles.

Other things I like - it feels nice on the scalp, is comfortable to hold, and it is very easy to clean.
Downsides- it is big, strangely shaped, and takes up some storage space.

product_title: Aura Cacia Essential Oil, Focusing Sandalwood, 0.5 fluid ounce
review_body:
It is very difficult to buy pure Indian sandalwood (Santalum album) essential oil (EO). Being expensive is one thing, spending the money for a adulterated or fake one is another. Even a trained nose may not be able to tell the difference. Only a lab analysis such as gas chromatography (GC) can detect all chemicals. Since we don't want to wear or inhale unwanted chemicals for aromatherapy purpose, the second best choice is the Australian sandalwood (Santalum spicatum) EO.

Of course there are different grades of Aussie sandalwood oils. However, Aura Cacia's oil has a nice aroma, with certain consistency. If you are used to Indian sandalwood, you may need to adjust your senses for Australian one. The top note is very different: resinous, woody, sharp, and dry. It is not unpleasant, but takes time to get used to it. This may be due to the lower content of the santalol, the key ingredient of the sandalwood aroma. Nevertheless, once your nose passes the top note, the middle note and the base note is very close to the Indian one, sweet, spicy, tenacious, elegant and euphoric.

Since the EO source is sustained and controlled by Australian government, there are certain standards of the oil. However, the downstream vendors and sellers may still adulterate the oil. A trusted source with fair price is important. In the case of sandalwood EO for aromatheraphy, a close relative is much better than an imposter.

product_title: FOOT SENSE All Natural Smelly Foot & Shoe Powder - 3.5 Oz/100 Grams - Foot Odor Eliminator lasts up to 6 months. Safely kills bacteria. Natural formula for smelly shoes and stinky feet. Safe & natural. Protects disinfects and deodorizes.
review_headline: Smell reducing but mess making powder
review_body:
1. I don't like being pushed into writing a review when I buy a product. I happen to be someone that writes reviews often. I like to actually try a product before reviewing. 2. I don't like the packaging. It was delivered in a zipped plastic bag and the powder was already all over the inside so that was a sign of poor packaging already. 3. The holes in the applicator is either too small for the product or the product is too thick for the holes. Either way I have to shake, tap, turn it upside down/right side up, tap on the side, etc. to get the product to come out at all.

My 6 year old has some strong foot odor. She is wearing skechers go walk 2 shoes. I washed the shoes first. It was fully dry when I applied the powder. The powder made a mess. It is so fine it got all over everything nearby but since it's "all natural" I was not worried about it. I was, however, worried about inhaling the stuff. The smell is very pleasant and it certainly did not "erase" the smell but I was of course not expecting it to. I left the powder in the shoe (I used a very generous amount and I even put some on the outside of the shoe.) She wore the shoes at school and when she came home it was smelly like her feet but not as strong. I was pleasantly surprised. I reapplied and again left it overnight. The smell was fainter but still obviously there. I thought this was just not going to work. She also bathes every night and I dry her feet very well. I leave enough powder to make sure it impacts her feet and socks. I applied once more and now her shoes do not smell. I want to see how long it will last. I am very very surprised. So 4 stars for a product that works but takes several applications. 2 star for a messy delivery of product into the shoes.

review_headline: Refreshing to use, Attractive to display

Note: The lather is smooth and slippery (on the body and on the tub surface), and I can't tell if it \\"drew out\\" dirt/oil from my facial pores. But the bar itself is very rough and exfoliates well when run directly against my skin (arms, legs, torso; it's too rough for the face).    I have rosacea and cleanse my face with [[ASIN:B000052YLF Neutrogena Acne]] bar. This lather did not aggravate the rosacea and it didn't cause the dryness that Neutrogena can. With its fresh (and fleeting) fragrance, I'm looking forward to using it in the summer.

product_title: Vidal Sassoon Salonist Hair Colour Permanent Color
review_headline: Great at home dye without the harsh side effects of brittle hair
review_body:
I received the Vidal Sassoon Salonist Permanent Hair Color in 5/0 Medium Neutral Brown. I did receive this free from Vidal Sassoon but my review is 100% my opinion only! I have brown hair so this was a good one for me. The instructions and the bottles were clear to me. I donât think it was difficult at all but I am sure that, if people only skim the directions or bottles, they will find it confusing. I mixed the first step, dyed my roots and waited the allotted time. Then I completed the second step of the dyeing with the serum product. There was definitely enough dye for my head of hair. I have super thick hair and a LOT of it (as I am always told when I get my hair cut) so they really gave enough product. The product was thick so it was easy to apply and actually SEE where it was placed on your hair. It was not so think, like other products, that it absorbs quickly into your hair and you cannot actually tell what hair you have dyed. It was so thick that I stopped using the brush and just put it on with my gloved fingers.

The Vidal Sassoon Salonist Permanent Hair Color was not as potent as other hair colors that I have used. I actually dyed my hair when on vacation and it did not stink of the room for the remainder of the evening. When I dye my hair at home, I have to air out the house because it stinks that much! Now, it DID still smell like hair dye but it wasnât as strong as other products that I have tried.

As for the color, the 5/0 Medium Neutral Brown was the best match to my natural color than any other product that I have tried. Typically, my hair becomes dry and brittle after dyeing and gets much worse as the weeks go by. Not the case with this product. So far, my hair is in the best condition of any home permanent coloring. It was soft and is still moisturized and I have continued to use the conditioner weekly too. I am now over a month out from dyeing and my stubborn grays are starting to come back so the longevity of the dye is no more than any other box home color. The color was not brassy in any way and still isnât weeks later. Overall the color was excellent and my hair is in good shape post dye. Now if only my grays would stay dyed as long as the rest of my hair does.

I was able to get my hair dyed in less than an hour. It was great to have it done for a fracture of the cost and time that it takes to go to the salon AND my hair feels and looks great!

review_headline: Great absorption, terrific orange fragance, super results!
review_body:
I am greatly enjoying this Vitamin C Serum from Alina Skin Care. It impressed me from the very first application.

I love the orange fragrance--not too strong and it diminishes with time. But it is the initial whiffs of orange that are very uplifting as it is applied to the face.

It has a consistency that is easy to spread on the face, and it absorbs so quickly into the skin, too. It is immediately apparent that there are soothing moisturizers in the mix. And, so far, the moisturizers have not clogged my pores.

I have used other Vitamin C Serums before: Some are thick and almost syrupy and I don't like the feeling that the serum is sitting on top of my face. Others contain a bit too much acid in them, and while the initial few applications make my skin feel nice and tingly, eventually my skin becomes too dry. This Alina is just right for me! It soaks right into my skin and causes a slight warming effect. It seems a perfect balance of components.

*I received a sample product from Alina Skin Care.

product_title: L'Oreal Paris Go 360 Clean, Deep Exfoliating Scrub,Natural Apricot Beads, 6-Fluid Ounce
review_body: I will admit I've been using Laura Mercier's exfoliating rub for the face, and it is a little over $30.00. However, I thought I would purchase this to compare it. First of all, if you like a "fake chemical apricot" smell, perhaps the smell will be tolerable. But to me, it is a horrible and quite nauseating smell, unfortunate, especially for a face product. I am really surprised this was not mentioned in the reviews. Second, the granules are just a bit too small and too sparse to do a good job scrubbing. Third, the texture of the product is a little too wet, so it does not provide quite the level of friction needed to remove dead skin really well. I will not purchase it again, even if only ONE of those reasons were the case, because it ruins the overall effect.

product_title: Reach Mint Waxed Dental Floss 100 Yards Per Pack
review_headline: Indespensible for a healthy mouth and heart
review_body:
More and more studies tie heart and overall health to healthy gums and daily flossing. Food particles between teeth generate bacteria, destroying gums and therefore the teeth. All of this is directly related to heart disease. Along with a good regimen of brushing it is also imperative to floss daily. Children should be taught to do this at an early age so they can carry on the brush/floss habit through their lives.

I find that Reach Mint Waxed floss does the best job of between the teeth cleansing. My teeth are closely set together and the waxed floss slides right in between my teeth, extracting all the particles. My dentist told me a handy hint on the use of floss. As so often your hands are wet when flossing, he suggested to tie a knot into a longer length of floss (a knot like is tied in sewing thread). Then when flossing, slowly go around the loop, always flossing with a new area of the thread. Put your hands inside the loop and use only one thickness. I find that I can hold the floss taught and I don't carry the particles removed to another tooth.

I love the minty flavor but it is certainly not over powering. The floss is nice and strong and the wax provides a nice smooth action.

product_title: Brytan Lane Mango Papaya Hand Crafted Bar Soap, 5 oz
review_headline: Scents That Can Transport You to Another Place
review_body: I received this product for free in exchange for an honest review. First of all, the packaging is very nice! It came in a small box packed with foam peanuts to protect the soap, which I thought was nice. I have purchased too many items on Amazon that come broken or beaten up. Now, to the soap. Let me just say, this stuff is incredible! I'm not a fan of bar soap in general, but really that was the only down side for me (and only because I'm too lazy to use the bar, haha). That being said, though, this stuff smells AMAZING. I chose the Mango Papaya scent and, oh my Lord, it was like a tropical vacation in my shower. The scent woke me up and made me feel refreshed as I got ready for the day. I thought I should mention that I really, really, worked the soap up into a lather all over, and it looks like I've hardly made a dent in the bar of soap. I'm thinking it's going to last a long time! Also, the soap is smooth and feels good on the skin. I was worried that it would leave my skin dry, but my skin was actually very soft after the shower! You won't be disappointed with any of these soaps! :)

review_body:

Anyway, this was just slightly higher per bottle than at Fresh Market. Have tried many other Limeades; Simply product is good for margaritas, but when you want a clear, crisp, clean finishing Cosmo or pomegranate martini, you have to use this stuff.
My only concern was the shipping packaging. The bottles came in a 12-pack, with cardboard bottom and shrink-wrap plastic. But in the shipping box, the plastic was maneuvered around, with cut-up pieces of cardboard in between, and then piled in were those horrid packing peanuts! These things should be banned from shipping. Particularly for an organic product. Surprisingly, the two boxes I got each had some heavy outside damage despite "Fragile" labels all over, and yet somehow none of the bottles was damaged.

I found that the tape wasn't very sticky (-1 star) and I have to constantly keep it in place or remove and re-apply the line.

review_headline: It does not dry nicely on my face - it feels tacky afterwards
review_body:
This serum is just okay, and I don't think I will purchase it again.

I am 3/4 the way through my first bottle - I use one dropper 1-2 times a day, and decided to store the bottle in the fridge after the first couple uses.

This serum is not clear, and has a little bit of a smell (more so after it is applied - I can smell it on my face and fingers). It does tingle a little bit after application. It was mild though, did not last very long and was not irritating to my skin. It does not dry nicely on my face - it feels tacky afterwards. Trying to apply makeup over this (even an hour later) does not bode well. Also, I have not noticed any changes in my skin tone/texture etc. in comparison to other similar products.

I have used this serum and the OZ Naturals vitamin c serum.

product_title: Schick Xtreme
review_body:
There isn't another disposable razor I've found that flexes the way these do. Kind of like a "C" shape that really gets around corners well and isn't bulky. Schick does a nice job with the blades as well, they're long lasting and really nicely made. No stray cuts and scrapes with these.

Bedsides the flexible head, these are no nonsense in the other respects. (But this is a good thing. Why put all that technology into fancy handles, colors, and other junk you don't need.) The blades are the key, and Schick does them right.

These value packs are a great deal for the money, you may be able to find them out in town-but not at this price! (I compared all the major drugstores for price on this one. Amazon wins again!)

product_title: L'Oreal Active Daily Moisture Lotion 4 oz
review_headline: Budget Lotion with a Luxury Feel
review_body:
Wow, wow, wow! Add this to my list of repeat lotions! I never use the same lotion two bottles in a row, but I do like to revisit previous lotions if they prove their worth to me. This one is a definite yes to the revisit list.

What I LOVE about L'Oreal Paris Active Daily Moisture Lotion:
- it is incredibly light and spreads easily.
- there is absolutely no sticky feel afterwards.
- the moisture lasts all day (I work in a very dry warehouse environment and many lotions have not passed the test of keeping my face reasonably moist throughout the full day).
- there is no unpleasant odor, while there IS fragrance in the lotion it is so light that it does not bother me (I am one who often falls ill from various fragranced products).

The best part is that I get all the benefits of this lotion at an amazing price. This really can't be beat!

product_title: Water-Resistant Professional Skin Care Face and Body Brush System by ToiletTree Products
review_body:
Update 8/2/15: I've discovered the secret to not getting suds all over when using this brush. You cannot use a liquid wash with this, it must be a solid bar soap to work properly without getting stuff all over the place. So between the excellent customer service I received from Toilettree, and the one flaw with the brush, I give an average of 4.5 stars. (Last update, I promise)

Update 7/18/15: So back to disappointed. Been using the new brush all week and with the exception of the first day, I'm still having the same problem. I even let my daughter (age 16) try (with a different head of course) and she got the same result as me, soapy foam spraying all over the bathroom! Maybe it's user error, and I do have to give Toilettree Products a thumbs up for excellent customer service, but unfortunately I'm not amused with this product.
Update 7/14/15: So, not long after posting a 2 star review of this product, Steve Parisi of Toilettree Products contacted me. He apologized for the bad experience and wanted to send me a new one free of charge. Got the new brush today and tried it. So far, so good. Even using the same brush head I was using before, I got no sprayage of soapy foam all over my bathroom. It's only the one time so far, but we'll see how it goes.
This brush is OK. I guess it does its job cleansing the face. It's not very loud or rough on the skin. The only problem I have with this is it spins so fast that it sprays water and foam all over. I'm not sure what I might be doing wrong. I give my face a rinse first, I wet the brush (even shaking off the excess water), put my cleanser on the brush, put the brush on the handle/motor part, put it on my face and turn it on. As soon as it works up the lather, the soapy foam is spraying all over the bathroom! Because of that I don't use this as often as I would like.

product_title: Revlon ColorStay Eyeliner with SoftFlex, Black 201, 0.01 Ounce (28 g) (Pack of 2)
review_body:
I much prefer liquid eyeliner for my eyes, only wearing pencil liner on lazy days, so normally I'd not spend this sort of money on a pencil liner and although this has more 'features' than a normal pencil how it wears doesn't differ much from bog-standard.

You have a smudger and sharpener on one end and the liner itself on the other end, it's retractable too so is more than your bog-standard pencil liner, but I found this more difficult to apply as there was no control and unless retracted right back it felt like it was going to snap. For a smudgy look this works out fine but for any sort of precision application this isn't going to work out - obviously as a liquid liner user I'm somewhat biased, but as stated above this one doesn't differ much in wear from bog-standard pencils at half the price.

It does stay on for a while without smudging all over your face, but no more than another pencil liner.

review_body: this mascara grew on me. it was an impulse purchase because i was running late to a halloween party and, hey, might as well try something new. the brush looked goopy and clumpy (really short bristles, tons of mascara on the brush). my first application made my lashes look really fake and chunky, and they clumped together. i personally prefer my eyelashes to look smooth and natural. at first, i'd swipe on the manga mascara then use an empty fat mascara brush to straighten everything out. after a few applications, i was able to get nice, smooth, long lashes every time using only the manga brush. this mascara gives me the longest lashes of any brand, hands down.

review_headline: Amazing eyeshadow Palette its a must have
review_body: So far so good and I am in love. I normally use a primer or something that will make the shadow stay put because my skin is so oily and I am not very good at putting eyeshadow on. I use NYX cosmetics primer in white and now the Shany eyeshadow which I am in love with. The pigmentation in the shadows is really great and the variety in colors is amazing! They even have a couple of colors that are mixed with flecks of different colors in them to give you a fuller or more enhanced version of colors that may be included in the set but you may not know or want to mix. I love that idea. There are also colors you can use as primers here. The color lasted all day and I have a 6 am (heading out and commuting) start to my days and don't get home until about 8pm or so. This palette is amazing! I honestly believe that this is one of the best inexpensive (I refuse to pay 50 to 60+ for a teeny palette) palettes you will buy here on Amazon or directly on Shany's website. You don't have to agree with me but to me this is a really  amazing purchase and I love it. Buying the other palette soon for good measure. product_title: Yariew Professional Cosmetic Makeup Brush Set Kit with Synthetic Leather Case,black
review_body:
Meh. I didn't pay much for this set, so I didn't think I would be getting all that great quality, but I bought them anyway to investigate.

This set comes with many many brushes, in a plastic fold up carrier. To be honest you can really tell the lack of quality when it comes to the larger brushes, shedding and no quality to the shape, so I tossed most of those almost immediately. I ended up keeping most of the smaller style brushes. They do come in handy on occasion when I need to apply something unusual that I don't apply everyday on a new brush. They are not my every day brushes but I do use them on occasion, and it is nice to have brushes like that around you can use.

In hind sight, I think its better to spend a little more money on a nicer set with less brushes. The quantity doesn't really make up for lack of quality here.

review_headline: Noise ruins a great brush. As other reviewers note
review_body: Noise ruins a great brush. As other reviewers note, it doesn't seem to be an issue with the body of the toothbrush but the brush heads themselves. I can't tell if it's just a bad design of the brushes or if they intend it to do this but I'd much prefer the quieter hum I was used to with my first gen sonicare brush... After filing down the inner metal ring of the brush head it certainly helped minimize the VERY LOUD sympathetic vibrations but did not fix the issue. If this was not the case I would give this item a 5 star but the sound right now is ridiculous. There's no way this should have made it out of QA but going by other reviews this is the typical result... I loved my first sonicare but I will avoid them in the future because of this.

product_title: Schick Hydro Silk Razor Disposable Razors for Women Our Best Disposable Shaving Razor - 3 Count
review_headline: Throw the rest of your razors away- the Hydro Silk is all you will need!
review_body: I am so happy and lucky that I was chosen through Bzzagent to test Schick's new Hydro Silk razors for free (thanks Schick!). I have used many different brands of disposable and non disposable razors in the past and this razor does just as good of a job as a non disposable razor. I always ended up going back to a non disposable mans razor which I found to do a better job....until now! The shave is not painful as some disposable razors are, thanks to the 5 curve sensing blades with skin guards. 5 blades- WOW!  The razor definitely shaves those hard to reach places with ease because of the contoured oval cartridges and I have yet to get any irritation as some disposable razors leave you with. I even tested not putting lotion on after my shower which is my normal routine, and hours later my legs still felt smooth and hydrated. I was definitely impressed and will absolutely buy these razors again. It has been almost 3 weeks since I have started using the razor and I still am getting a nice close smooth shave. Most other disposable razors don't last nearly as long! Great product Schick! I urge you to try it!

review_headline: Not Really A Pomade, More of a Sculpting Glue
review_body:
I took a risk and tried this based upon a recommendation from the blog "The Art of Manliness" and I gotta say it's pretty awful.
It's hard and difficult to spread into your hair.
They say that you need to wet your hands and hair and then put a dime size portion of the "pomade" into your hands and rub them together.
Supposedly the heat and friction from this should make the compound easier to spread.
It really doesn't.

Before you purchase this, take a look at it at your local Target or Wal-Mart and make sure it's the product you desire for your hair.

William Mize
"How to Keep a Gratitude Journal"
"My Journey to Lose Weight with LCHF"

review_body: Collagen cremes have been around for decades. Unfortunately, there is no evidence that they work. As Smart Skin Care.com notes, collagen molecules are too big to be absorbed by the skin. Just For Me Conditioner Hair Milk Silkening, 13.5 Ounce
review_headline: For my hair, best on shampoo day
review_body:
As someone with curly hair who washes my hair usually every 3 days (sometimes 4), it's important to me how my hair looks over several days. On subsequent days I'll either tie up my hair before my shower (getting my hair damp but not wet), or "rinse" without shampooing.
This conditioner was absolutely fantastic on Day One -- my curly hair fell in gorgeous waves. But on subsequent days, my hair flattened out more than usual, with a somewhat "crunchy" texture that made me think it hadn't rinsed out completely, and this happened both times I tried it.
But the great aesthetic pleasure is in the actual use. For some reason, using "hair milk" that is so creamy and white is a delightful experience. It is moderately fragranced, with a nice scent.
All told, I'll save this for "day of" conditioning, when I want my hair to look its best for a special occasion.

product_title: Jojoba Oil, USDA Certified Organic, 100% Pure, Cold Pressed, Unrefined. Revitalizes Hair & Gives Skin a Radiant Youthful Look. Great treatment for Face, Lips, Cuticles, Stretch Marks
review_body:
Jojoba oil is an ingredient commonly mentioned in many beauty magazines, and itâs with good reasonâitâs found in many beauty products from shampoos to moisturizers. This bottle is filled with the pure oil itself, and can be used as a moisturizer for both the face and the hair. Having used this for a month now, I must say itâs a fantastic natural moisturizer.

There are a variety of oils out there that also have moisturizing properties, including argan oil and rosehip oil, but Jojoba oil tends to be a bit cheaper than those two. Another thing I really like about this is the fact that it has a very light nutty odorâyou can barely detect it. I put this on after a warm shower and applying a toner and wake up the next day with extremely soft skinâI love it! This bottle specifically may not look like much, but since you donât use much per application, one of these should be able to easily last 2+ months.

Overall, I think this is a great starting choice for anyone looking for a natural alternative moisturizer and want to give the oils a try. Itâs one of the most budget friendly choices, and it really does work. For those who feel weird about putting oils on their face/body, they actually get absorbed by your body rather quickly and I havenât experienced any breakouts whatsoever. If anything, theyâve helped my acne due to how nourishing it is for the skin. Just make sure to apply the oil sparinglyâyou really donât need that much.

Please note that I was sent this product for review, and I hope that itâs been helpful for you! Feel free to leave any questions/comments below and Iâll do my best to respond.

==The Good==
+ Works fantastically as a moisturizer
+ Very light scent
+ Great value

product_title: Clubman Pinaud After Shave Lotion
review_headline: Good scent, great value, interesting semiotics
review_body:
Pleasant and retro. Most men know the sandalwood-like smell from the Pinaud talc they still use in old fashioned barber shops. It's not a truly great cologne like you'd get from a great Jermyn street perfumer like Floris or Penhaligon, but it's manly agreeable, and suggests old-fashioned propriety and democratic refinement. I don't know that a youngster could carry this off, but if you're old enough to wear a beret without looking like you're in costume, this would work for you.

I can't for the life of me figure why they haven't hiked the price and marketed this to hipsters for the irony value. Good fashion move if you're twenty something with horn rims and "interesting" facial hair. . . .

There's also the price to consider. This is dead cheap and you'd spend four times as much to find better in a compounded cologne. Good value for everyday wear.

review_body: The best thing about this product is that you don't need globs of it. I simply apply it for a few minutes and as soon as I rinse I feel more volume. It's an instant feeling of satisfaction and I've already mentioned the brand to a few friends. My hair is very greasy and not many products leave my hair feeling light and manageable. I workout three times a week and being able to have such an easy way to treat my thinning hair is actual helping my self-esteem. Experiencing new growth every week has made me feel stronger as a woman period.

product_title: 6 Kleancolor ALTER EGO Metallic Eyeliner Duo (MLE408) Pencil Liguid Liner
review_body:
Uck.....I should have known better!! Flashy packaging that is not up to par. I LOVE makeup, and probably have enough for 3 lifetimes, so I know my stuff. The bottles are awkward,the bottom bulb a liquid, the sharp end a small pencil. The purple bulb was broken off-so I have no way of getting to the liquid liner. I did like the blue and silver liquid, but it doesn't remove like normal liner. It's almost like you used spray paint, and is a job to get off.
I don't want to be that rough to remove makeup so close to my eyes!! I could see how this stuff could easily bother anyone with sensitive skin.
Bottom line(pun intended), don't do it! I know the price is good, but, I don't see myself using any of these for all day use, so I wasted my money.
Don't wast your money, it's crap.

product_title: Kitoko Oil 9.8oz
review_headline: If I could give more than 5 stars I would
review_body: I first tried this product after receiving a free sample from my salon. I've honestly never come across a better hair product in my life. I purchased the 3.2 Oz bottle on Amazon about a year ago and with three times weekly use it has lasted me until now. Though seemingly pricey at first, it's actually beyond worth the cost considering how long it will last you. A little goes a long way. I use heat on my hair daily, leaving it extremely damaged for most of my high school and college years. Most products just leave my hair with a coating of useless weight but kitoko oil is unbelievably light and powerful. I love how soft it makes my hair feel and I feel that it has repaired every strand in ways that I can't even begin to describe. It also smells great which is a huge bonus. You can use it on wet or dry hair. I usually run it through while wet and then run just a little more through after blow drying and before styling with a flat iron or curling rod. I'm just amazed that more people aren't aware that this hair saving miracle exists.

review_headline: I have to say I am very pleased with how my skin seems to glow

My husband bought this for me along with the face and body cream. We received some chaga soap and I have been using all three for over a week now. I have to say I am very pleased with how my skin seems to glow. I have very oily skin and at the age of 54 I can not wear any kind of make up due to break outs. I have very uneven skin tone or what is known as a ruddy complexion. After having using the Chaga soap, age defying face serum and the chage face and body cream I have noticed my skin is not as oily and my skin tone seems to be evened out. I love how it feels after I finish with my morning and evening regime. A must to have for every woman, no matter their age. With all the chemicals in our cosmetics and the pollution in the air around us this is a welcome to me.

In the past my husband bought me Dr. Ohhira's beauty soap. I've used it for several years and I have to say this beats his organic facial beauty soap.

product_title: BEST Vitamin C Serum CE Ferulic Acid - 17% L-Ascorbic Acid + Vitamin E + Ferulic Acid + Hyaluronic Acid- 100% Pure Natural Ingredients with Powerful Anti-Oxidants Best Anti Aging Serum on the Market!
review_headline: Not going back.  No results, fast degradation.
review_body:
Turned yellow 2 weeks after use (when vitamin C serums go from milky white to yellow, it signifies oxidation and thus negates any anti-oxidant effect that the vitamin C is supposed to render in the first place).

Also, is NOT a clear serum as depicted in their picture, but an opaque milky white color that turns yellow in 2 weeks. I kept it in the original box, closed, and behind the medicine cabinet. The only times the bottle was exposed to air and light (the elements that oxidize Vitamin C serums), was when I would quickly remove the dropper to drop some serum on my skin, and replace the dropper and seal tightly and put back in the box, then back into the medicine cabinet. Yet it still degraded rapidly.

And of course, noticed NO difference despite 1 month of use.

review_headline: It works great if you use it correctly
review_body: I purchased this about 2 months ago. At first I tried to follow the instruction but it was hurting my skin. After trying it once every week I finally learned the right way to use it for me. I have sensitive skin. So even though it said "medium layer" I really should put a think layer on my face instead. If you feel that it is too strong for your skin or feel dry afterwards, it's possible that you've used too much too. The best way to figure it out is to have just enough so that it dries within 10-15 minutes. If you leave it on your skin for too long it will definitely hurt. With a thin layer, I can actually rub it off like it said in the instruction. It works great and makes my skin really soft. I still get a little negative reaction here and there on small spots but I think it's normally. Just a little itchy and I can totally deal with it. Definitely a great buy.

product_title: InstaNatural Vitamin C Skin Clearing Serum - Anti Aging Formula with Retinol & Salicylic Acid - Natural & Organic Wrinkle, Acne, Dark Spot, Fine Line & Hyperpigmentation Defying Facial Product - 1 OZ
review_headline: A little potent but worth it.
review_body:
I started using this line of products a few months ago after reading several positive reviews. I'm 36 have always battled severe acne and discoloration. It's generally horrible. I started with just the serum, then added the cleanser, then the night cream, then the toner and then the mask.

Overall, this combination of products has drastically improved the look feel and overall health of my skin.

This serum is great, and I've noticed a drastic improvement in my skin since I started using it, but sometimes it does cause minor irritations like blotching, minor itching and a little dryness. I only use it at night because of this and I always follow up with the night cream. If you have sensitive skin like I do, I do not recommend using this serum more than once a day. I can say however, that there is a noticeable difference in my skins condition and appearance and I feel I look healthier than I ever have.

I now can wear less makeup and even feel comfortable wearing my hair out of my face on a regular basis. I've never felt better about my own face and it's because I decided to invest in a line of quality products that actually works for me. I have tried several other product lines on both the mainstream cosmetic side and the natural side resulting in poor or nightmarish results.

There's something about this line that just works for me and I'm so thankful. I may sound a little dramatic here but for me it's a big deal. Being able to actually like the skin on my face has been a big life changer for me. I recommend this line to anyone with combination and sensitive skin. It all takes a little getting used to but it's completely worth it.

product_title: Silk'n SN-001 FaceFx Anti-Aging LED Handheld Facial Device
review_headline: Reduces wrinkles, but I have some safety concerns
review_body:
I find that this makes a difference, but there are some cautions, too.

Some relevant info: I'm in my early 50's with pale skin and have an oily complexion and "sensitive skin"... there are a number of skincare products that are too harsh for me.

Pros:
1. Does actually improve skin tone and diminish wrinkles.
2. I have a skin type that sunburns easily and reacts to some beauty products; I don't have any bad reactions to using this device. (My face does get warm after use, as described, but nothing like a burn, and nothing that causes concern at all.)
3. I am leery of using this near my eyes, so I avoid my crow's feet. But it's helped on the "necklace" of wrinkles I have on my neck, around the mouth area, and between my eyebrows.

Cons:
1. There is some controversy/disagreement about the long-term health implications of using red LED therapy, and whether it might be associated with cancers. However, I can't find a study on pubmed, so it might all be hearsay / internet gossip.
2. Please be especially careful near your eyes, which of course are especially delicate. I suggest that you close your eyes while working anywhere near your eyes, so that you're not shining the LED directly onto your eyeball. Even with eyes closed, I still think it's questionable to work on the eyelid, for example... you're still deliberately heating up your eyeball.
3. The LEDs are set back from the edges of the device, which means it's hard to shine the LEDs on your crow's feet without getting what I consider to be too close to my eyeballs.

Obviously:
1. This is not going to entirely make wrinkles go away. It diminishes them. The video seems to me to set reasonable expectations

I'm giving this four stars because it does what it says; decremented one star because of the safety concerns.

FWIW, mine has a cord, not a battery and charging station.

product_title: Crest 3D White Professional Effects Whitestrips Dental Teeth Whitening Strips Kit, 20 Treatments - Lasts 12 Months & Beyond
review_body:
I researched and spoke with my dentist about all the options for teeth whitening in depth for a while and found the reviews and information lead me towards this product. I was already using the 3D White toothpaste and already noticed a very slight difference just using that alone and decided to get their mouthwash too. I immediately started using the strips the day they came in. It's been 5 days and I've noticed a HUGE difference. I chose professional effects not only because I had my braces removed this year, but I am a smoker AND a big coffee drinker (both leave heavy stains, as most of us know) and it has already removed a majority of the damage I've done to my mouth. I'm extremely ecstatic about this product and will finish the pack as well as order another next year and go through it again (As recommended by Crest and other reviews).

WARNING: However, these strips DO indeed make your teeth sensitive. I do not mean necessarily just to cold air or cold drinks/ice. It's almost a short throbbing pain in some areas. It didn't persist for me, just happened for a few minutes after. Also...do NOT, I repeat, DO NOOOOT wear these longer than the recommended time on the instructions (30 minutes) if you want to avoid sensitivity. I went an hour (just to experiment) on two treatments and noticed a HUGE difference with pain and sensitivity. If this is a big concern for you, I did notice the mouth wash and toothpaste they offer under the same like do help with this issue. You could also consider trying a toothpaste FOR sensitive teeth to help.

product_title: Personna Double Edge Razor Blades
review_body:
I have been going up in blades as Gillette and Schick have been going back and forth. 2-3-4, 5 with an edger. The Mach 5 is currently $39.88 for a twelve count - $3.32/cartridge. The Mach 5 is probably a closer shave when brand new. That being said at 3.32/cartridge I tried to make the cartridge last longer than it should. The more you use the same cartridge the less smooth the shave.

At 13.30 for 100 double edge blades - you could change a blade every 2 days and shave every day with a new edge - for half a year and 17 days At $13.30 for the pack of 100 - that is 200 brand new blade edges for the price of 4 Mach 5 cartridges. The new edge of these blades shave very close - just maybe not quite as close as a 5 blade. Again - the tradeoff is at $3.32/cartridge you won't be switching out the Mach 5 as often and your shave won't be as close either.

Stop trying to make those expensive multi-blade cartridges last longer than they should. Old worn out blades probably causes more irritation than anything else.

product_title: Vitamin C Serum 20 for Face with Hyaluronic Acid & Vitamin E Oil, that Helps Fade Age Spots, Clear Adult Acne & Get Rid of Wrinkles for a Glowing & Younger Looking Skin
review_body: This product in two words simply amazing. It smells great very citrusy which I love , and when you are applying something to your face you want something that smells good. I have been using this product for about a week now and I am already noticing a great improvement in my skin. Which two MAJOR important ingredients for me Vitamin C and Hyaluronic Acid. Vitamin C is an antioxidant that slows the rate of free-radical damage -free radicals are unstable molecules that damage collagen and cause skin dryness, fine lines and wrinkles. Research suggests that vitamin C may also reduce sunburn caused by exposure to ultraviolet B radiation and prevent the consequences of long-term sun exposure, which can lead to skin cancer. This doesn't mean you can take vitamins or apply topical vitamin C and then bake safely in the sun, but you can help keep your skin healthy and supple by making sure you get enough of this antioxidant vitamin. Hyaluronic acid isnât harsh or skin-stripping at all. In fact, itâs the exact oppositeâa powerful humectant (aka moisture-binding ingredient) that keeps skin plump and hydrated and, yes, young-looking.As we age, skin moisture can drop significantly, which makes the skin lose elasticity and expose the signs of aging on the skin. Hyaluronic acid plays a critical role in skin health with its unique ability to hold in moisture. Hyaluronic acid is also a âsmart nutrientâ as it can adjust its moisture absorption rate based on the humidityârelative to the season and the climate. I have received this item during a promotional period and the views I have expressed are my own.

product_title: Volumizing Powder
review_headline: I really like this product.  Five stars!
review_body: This powder works great!  I sprinkle just a little on my roots in 1 inch partings down to my ears and rub it in well.  It provides nice volume and works better for me than powdery dry shampoo.  For the back of my head, I shake some on my fingers and then rub it in well, right into the roots.  The volume lasts most of the day but it's easy to revive with my fingertips and a few upside down shakes of my head.  I bought this product at Sally's when there was a buy 1 get 1 sale because I was curious about it and with the sale, I figured I had nothing to lose. The regular price is about $6.  It works much better than I'd hoped.  Once on the scalp, the powder turns clear so there's no white residue.  I'm sure it works as well as more expensive products that are triple the price (after all, how different can they be?) like Bumble and Bumble Pret a Powder. It also doesn't make my hair oily or dry it out.  I was using Living Proof Amp, which is a cream, but this works much better for me.  It also isn't sticky or stiff like a root spray.  I've found it works best on second day hair, however.  All and all, I really like this product.  It's nice to be pleasantly surprised by something new.  And although the container is small, you really need very little to do the job, so it will last quite a while.  I'm a fan of other BTZ products, namely Smooth Criminal Primer, the matte clay putty and the dry shampoo, so I'm glad the brand lived up to my standards with yet another excellent product.  I definitely recommend this volumizing powder.  It works like a charm for me.

product_title: Natural Aqua Gel Cure 250ml
review_body: This stuff has to be magic, illegal, or both. It works sooo well. I was completely skeptical that you could actually feel you skin balling up under your fingers where it was coming off. I mean seriously. That sounds crazy. I have some kind of dermatitis, not sure what, around my nose. It basically turns red sometimes, burns, then peels. When I first got this I was in the peeling/flaking stage and my face was looking rough. Literally. I tried this and boy did it ball up under my fingers like it said it would. Afterwards my skin was smoother than it has been in a very very long time. No more flaking. I'm still a little skeptical of the "natural" claim after looking at the ingredients but it sure does work.  As for the people saying it's not your skin balling up under your fingers it's the gel, all I know is that there was dry skin flaking off of my face before and after something balled up under my fingers there wasn't. Take that as you will.

Every time I use this, I scratch less than I originally have before, the skin on my hair is less irritated, and my hair stays drier (but still moisturized) longer. Plus, the smell is amazing and very therapeutic, reminding me of aromatherapy oils.

I am going to continue to use this and am debating on getting more because this is doing something that my original shampoo wasn't: fixing an issue I've had for years. I might even try the dandruff shampoo version Maple Holistics has.

product_title: Remington SFT200 Sonicfresh Rechargeable Toothbrush, White
review_headline: Cheaper Than The Alternative, But The Quality of the Toothbrush Hasn't Suffered
review_body:
I'll begin this review by getting into the technical aspects of the product and my experience with the charging, usage, etc.

Charging the brush is easy: you literally just stand it up in its cradle and plug it in. Once the light encircling the top of the base turns from red to blue, it's done. The instructions state that before its first use, it should be charged for 16 hours. (That's also how long it takes to fully charge it each subsequent time, though a quick charge of 1 hour yields about four 2 minute brushing sessions.) I wound up having to unplug mine after 4 hours (not because of the toothbrush, but because I had to unexpectedly leave my house). When I tried to resume charging it the next day, the light was blue and stayed that way, so I thought I'd go ahead and begin using the toothbrush, thinking that the charge would likely only last for a short while. By the time the light began blinking from blue to red (which indicates it needs to be charged), it had lasted through almost 50 two minute sessions, much to my surprise. So it really holds its charge for a very long time.

The unit is slim and not at all bulky, and the brush head is on the smaller side, so I wondered if I would really feel like it had cleaned a lot of surface area before the brush indicated either that the section was done or that the entire 2 minute session was. (The instructions indicate that it's helpful to brush your teeth in quadrants, allowing 30 seconds per section, with the brush pausing in its vibrations at each 30 second mark, and then shutting off entirely after 2 minutes.) As for results, the brush head may be relatively small, but I do feel like it really cleans my teeth, and I can also say that it looks like it's removed some surface stains, as well.

There are three 3 cleaning modes that can be easily changed just by pushing a button. The clean mode can be a little intense. My teeth and gums are fairly sensitive, so this mode with its really strong vibrations isn't something that I can use all the time, but when I do, it gets the job done very well. The sensitive mode decreases some of that intensity to a more pleasant level, and that's the one that I use most often. The massage mode is very gentle, and is supposed to be used on the gums, which is something I haven't done, as of yet.

Other things of note: this unit does come with a replacement brush head, so all told, this is supposed to be enough to get one through for a full six months. It also comes with a slim travel case, and little colored bands that can be used to differentiate between brush heads if the base is being used by multiple people.

As for my overall take on this, I've been very pleased. I'd looked at a rival company's product that was *insanely* expensive, and I simply couldn't justify spending that much on a toothbrush. This one is a fraction of that price, and in my experience (and from what I've read of the more expensive one) this one does pretty much all the same things and works just as well. It really cleans the teeth; the timer function comes in very handy so that you know exactly how long to spend on each quadrant; and it holds a charge for a very long time. It's a good quality, effective product, and I think prospective buyers will be pleased with it.

product_title: Big Shampoo by LUSH by LUSH Cosmetics
review_headline: Smells good and adds a bit of body
review_body:
I bought this pricey shampoo because I was sick of my limp, blah hair and, well, it made promises. Promises I could not resist. Here they are:

Size matters: Suitable for all hair types, but especially for limp locks. Once you go BIG you never go back.
Shine on: Fresh lime juice delivers instant shine and leaves your hair feeling extra clean.
One of your five a day: Full of vitamins, minerals and trace elements, Tooth Wracked Seaweed strengthens damaged hair.

Tell me, could you resist all that?

Anyway, my hair is baby fine and mid back length so you can imagine how blah it looks when left to dry naturally. I typically wash it every other day, adding a little dry shampoo at the roots for \\"oomph\\" on day 2 and using a headband around the head and wrapping the hair around it, spritzing with a bit of water and leaving it alone to dry while I get ready. This gives me pretty spiral curls and a little lift without damaging my weak hair further. Day 2 looks pretty good. It's Day 1 that is the problem. I don't blow-dry so it usually just hangs there pin straight or gets tucked into a bun.

Today I tried out Big Shampoo. It smells like heaven. Yes, I know what heaven smells like. Heaven smells of coconuts with a wee hint of limey sweetness. The texture is a bit strange, seeing as 50% of the base consists of genuine sea salt crystals (the large kind). I wet my hair before scooping out a bit and rubbing into my scalp. I massaged it to melt the salt and it lathered up nicely and rinsed out easily. I followed up with a bit of Veganese conditioner on about 6\\" of the ends because, let me tell you, my hair felt dry. If I hadn't used the conditioner, I doubt I would've been able to get a comb through it without resorting to a detangler. So be warned. After combing, my hair did feel more voluminous than usual (which isn't saying much, to be honest but I'll take it) and now that it's completely air dried, the texture feels different, almost like I'd spent a day at the beach. It definitely has a bit more life than usual. I think with a blow dryer, it would be noticeably voluminous. As is, I am quite happy with the results. The scent is subtle and lovely and my hair has a little more bounce and isn't lying flat against my head. It doesn't look any shinier than normal but I'm okay with that. Shiny, for me, usually means it needs a wash!

Does BIG keep its promises? Well, it keeps the first one. The jury is still out on the other two. I'll update the review after I've used the entire tub which may take me awhile because my hair is so fine and I don't wash every day.

If you have a LUSH boutique nearby I recommend grabbing a sample to see how it works for you before buying the entire tub.almost like I'd spent a day at the beach. It definitely has a bit more life than usual. I think with a blow dryer, it would be noticeably voluminous. As is, I am quite happy with the results. The scent is subtle and lovely and my hair has a little more bounce and isn't lying flat against my head. It doesn't look any shinier than normal but I'm okay with that. Shiny, for me, usually means it needs a wash!

If you have a LUSH boutique nearby I recommend grabbing a sample to see how it works for you before buying the entire tub.

product_title: Philips Sonicare Powerup Battery Toothbrush
review_headline: Improved version of the non-rechargeable Sonicare
review_body:
This is an improved version of the battery (non-rechargeable) operated toothbrush. The original one had a battery compartment that was difficult to open and very difficult to close completely. This updated version is much better. And it's more water tight as well.
I prefer these to the more expensive rechargeable ones mainly because I don't want a charger and cords all over my counter. These use inexpensive AA batteries and lasts a couple of months. The entire toothbrush is inexpensive as well, under $20. During sales, you might be able to find it for less than $10.

product_title: Caribbean Solutions Beach Colours Natural Self Tanner - 1 x 6 oz
review_body: I unfortunately don't take time to review items. However, I'm choosing to sit down and leave a review for this product. I am so happy with this sunless tanner. I am of Irish and Welsh decent and therefore have very fair skin. I'm am extreamly careful with sun exposure because I have family history of skin cancer. But, I also don't want to look super pale in the summer. I have used multiple different brands of self tanner. I did finally find one that worked for me but, I became concerned about the chemicals. So, the search was on yet again. I came across this product and took a chance even though the only reviews were from people who had received the product as a free trial. I thought well, I have spent way more on other name brand products that didn't work so, I ordered it. I have been using it for three weeks now and I absolutely love it! It gives me exactly the right amount of color. It's light and fluffy and I don't need a mitt or a sponge or anything but, my hands. I have had no streaks or any issues. I was surprised how long the color lasted before I felt I needed to reapply. And the best part is the ingredients!!! 100x better then anything you will find at s drug store.

product_title: Beauty Aura 100% Pure Grapeseed Oil
review_body:
This review is for the 4 oz. bottle of Beauty Aura Grapeseed Oil. I have mentioned in my other reviews and I will continue to mention how much I enjoy Beauty Aura Products. They have definitely make a long time customer out of me. My bottle of grapeseed oil arrived in a plastic bottle and a safety seal underneath the cap. The cap is actually a snap cap which is great to prevent accidental spillage.

This grapeseed oil is cold pressed from the seeds of grapes. Grapeseed oil is rich in vitamins, minerals, antioxidants and essential fatty acids. It I a great carrier oil which means that other more potent essential oils can be added to this oil. It is a very light oil and will be absorbed by the skin almost immediately with no sticky greasy feeling.

I use grapeseed oil along with others in a hot oil treatment for my hair that always leaves my hair feeling soft and wonderful afterwards.

I have received a discount on this product in exchange for my honest and unbiased review. I enjoy writing reviews and put a lot of effort into how I feel about the products. I think it is important as consumers to make a well informed decision before purchasing a product.

product_title: Jojoba Oil, USDA Certified Organic, 100% Pure, Cold Pressed, Unrefined. Revitalizes Hair & Gives Skin a Radiant Youthful Look. Great treatment for Face, Lips, Cuticles, Stretch Marks
review_headline: Super moisturizing and it has made my hair and skin so much softer!
review_body:
I had never heard of using Jojoba oil for hair, skin, and nails, but I knew that you could find this amazing super moisturizing oil in a lot of hair and skincare products, so I was thrilled to try it out.

When it arrived I used it in my hair that night. You don't need a lot, a little goes a long way, so I squeezed 3-4 drops out (I have long mid-back length hair) and smoothed though the base of my head down, focusing on the tips especially where I have lots of dry, split ends. I have super dry hair and it's even worse this time of year, so I loved that this really smoothed my hair out and made it noticeable softer and smoother. In fact, my husband even noticed and commented on how soft my hair felt and that it smelled good too!

I applied my this Jojoba Oil to my hair at night before bed, but it worked great as a styling/smoothing cream when you're styling your hair for the day.
After a week or so of using this on my hair every other day, it feels really soft and looks so much more moisturized. My split ends have also been quite a bit less noticeable too!

You can also use this fabulous oil as a face or skin moisturizer too. I loved that even though its an oil, it still feels really lightweight on the skin. My face soaked it up pretty quickly and I was left with no oily residue (my skin is naturally dry too). Again, you only need about 1-2 drops for your face.

I also have dry, rough cuticles and have been really neglecting them lately, so I was excited to apply this oil to make them softer, smoother, and overall healthier. I applied about every other day and my nails and the cuticles are already looking much better!

I have absolutely loved using my Jojoba Oil from Kate Blanc cosmetics. I'm thrilled that there are so many wonderful uses for it, and I love how incredibly moisturizing and nourishing it is for skin and hair. A little goes a long way so you can expect this bottle to last you a really long time too!

product_title: E-Cotan ECO Tan Organic Winter Skin Gradual Tanner Plus Moisturizer by E-Cotan, Fair/Medium Skin Tones, 7.04 oz
review_body: When I first used this, my feet turned an almost orange-ish color. I was disappointed after reading many reviews about how this tanner doesn't turn your skin orange. However, I have very pale skin and I didn't apply regular lotion to my feet beforehand (pro tip: apply lotion to your feet and other rough areas before using this). Your skin doesn't immediately look darker after application btw, it takes a couple of hours. When I took a shower the next day, the color faded and blended a little, which I wanted, and looked much better. I'm on my fourth application in 2 weeks and the color is finally stable and definitely not an almost orange-ish shade; I think it takes a few applications to get it right. I'm not a fan of the smell, but it's bearable. Overall, I'm happy with how this works! Just wish it wasn't so expensive for only 300ml.

review_headline: didn't work for me - still recommend
review_body: I used this product daily all over my face and body for over four months. This was my second purchase, the first time I purchased on eBay and because it was not effective after 1 month I thought it make have been a counterfeit product, so I purchased it again here on Amazon. I have medium brown Indian skin and bought it to reduce dark marks in the underarm/bikini area and also on my face. I also hoped that it would help some light hyperpigmentation on my legs from ingrown hairs and prevent new ones from forming with vigorous almost daily exfoliation. Unfortunately I found that this product made no difference in my skin at all. I did not even feel a tingle, no matter how long I left it on, and I have very sensitive skin. The one thing I noticed that might attest for its strength was little red bumps on my face and chest that went away after about half an hour. The smell was pleasant and it worked well as a regular soap, but didn't work as expected. My skin remained the same colour all over and I experienced no dryness or peeling or sensitivity. I would still recommend trying this product as it is inexpensive and has received very many positive reviews.

product_title: Hugo Naturals Color Protecting Shampoo
review_headline: and Hugo Naturals is not my favorite. Here's why
review_body:
I've been searching for a while for a natural alternative to commercial shampoos, and Hugo Naturals is not my favorite. Here's why:

PROS: There are no sulfate containing compounds in the shampoo.
I have curly hair, and I don't have many fly-aways or frizzies going on while using this shampoo.

CONS: I don't have frizzies because my hair feels like it's coated with grease less than 18 hours after washing. I'm actually embarrassed to wash my hair the night before I go somewhere when I'm using this shampoo.
As might be expected from the lack of sulfates, the shampoo doesn't lather well. It's so difficult to work the shampoo in enough to feel like it's cleaning my scalp that I've actually caused mechanical abrasion to the tips of my hair and now have dry split ends.
The use of this shampoo and the accompanying conditioner has caused acne breakouts all along my hairline.
The fragrance doesn't really smell like coconut, and is tolerable at best. (I really don't like it at all, but I don't quite think it's objectively nasty-smelling.)

Overall, due to the mechanical difficulties, the smell, and knowing that I won't even look good afterward, this shampoo has taken most of the pleasantness out of my morning shower. I am a frugal shopper, and I can't even use the whole bottle that I bought.

product_title: Glycolic Acid Cream 10% Face Moisturizer. Best Alpha Hydroxy Acid Products; Exfoliating, Anti-Aging Lotion with AHA for Acne Prone Skin; Natural Exfoliator for Day and Night
review_headline: Makes my skin feel soft and healthy
review_body:
This face cream is great. It arrived very quickly and the packaging and container are very nice. I love face creams and try a different kind every time I run out. I think I may have to stick with this one though.

I was offered this cream with a discount to try it and review it and I was so excited. It is very thick so if you don't like thick face cream you may not like it or just may want to use it at night. I use it morning and night but am considering just using it at night because I want to use a face cream with sunscreen. That is my only complaint with this cream.

It smells OK but has a hydroxy acid and those usually have a distinctive smell. It's not strong but doesn't have any other fragrance. I don't mind or even notice the smell much but that's just me.

After using this cream for one day I had 3 people comment on my skin. There was a noticeable difference. My skin feels more hydrated and soft. My makeup looks more natural and doesn't just sit on top of my skin. I only wear a powder but when a powder doesn't blend it looks bad. I've noticed my coloring in my skin start to even out. I had a few sun spots that aren't noticeable anymore.

I would recommend this and will definitely be buying it again.

product_title: Aquis Exfoliating Back Scrubber
review_headline: Works Great On Back AND Other Hard To Reach Areaa
review_body:
This product was purchased because due to failed back surgeries, I have a hard time reaching certain areas of my body. The rougher side of the Scrubber is great on the back, and even works on the calluses of the feet when I use it while sitting on a chair in the shower.

The smoother side accomplishes what I REALLY bought this item for: cleaning the area the toilet paper doesn't quite get clean enough. Soaping up the smooth side and using a back and forth motion while placing the Scrubber between my legs cleans that area PERFECTLY. Then rinsing the Scrubber thoroughly, then soaping and rinsing again gets it nice and clean for the next use.

I tried several so-called "Butt scrubbers" and "Hiney Cleaners", all of which had plastic handles supporting some sort of cleaning material. These items were cheaply made, and every one I bought was broken after one or two uses. The Aquis Exfoliating Back Scrubber accomplishes the task perfectly, and more than likely will not break or tear apart for quite some time if I take good care of it.

I bought another one as a gift for my brother and his wife.

product_title: Shikakai Powder 3.5oz (100g) - Hesh Pharma (Pack of 2)
review_headline: Works well in combination with Aritha powder
review_body:
I use this to wash my hair. My hair is waist length, fine, blonde, pin-straight. It's moderately oily and I wash it every 2 or 3 days without an issue. I'm allergic to normal shampoos and conditioners and tried this as an alternative. Using shikakai powder alone did not clean my hair very well. It stayed odd and greasy-looking after I rinsed and dried. However, using this combined with aritha powder seems to do the trick. Aritha powder was too harsh on its own, but combined, I get clean and healthy hair! I use about a teaspoon of each and make a runny paste. I rub the paste into my roots and let it sit for a few minutes before rinsing. You have to rinse thoroughly or you might notice some grains of powder falling out of your hair once it's dry. I haven't had a problem with this, though. I like to follow up with a vinegar rinse (maybe 1-2 teaspoon of vinegar to 16 oz of water) and my hair loves it. Without the vinegar, I feel my hair gets a tad dull using just the powders. I've not noticed any darkening or color changes using this method.

I normally use baking soda to wash my hair. I must say, baking soda does a better job and my hair seems to prefer it. But I want to color my hair, so this is my second option to protect the dye job.
