product_title: Majestic Pure Indian Healing Clay Powder, 16 Oz
review_body:
I live in central Oklahoma and I've been bitten by spiders (Brown Recluses and others), and other similar critters more than a few times. Unlike some people, I do not react strongly to the spider's venom, but I DO take a long time to completely heal, sometimes as long as six months. The wound will slowly grow in size, ooze plasma, itch, and look pretty nasty during the healing process. I usually just clean the wound often with hydrogen peroxide and apply a Band-Aid. The largest one of my bite areas has ever grown was the size of a nickel - some people react strongly and their wound can grow very quickly to become as large as a dinner plate and eventually require skin grafts! My wounds will close up and heal in time, leaving scar tissue behind. An interesting note: I've read some research (yeah, on the Web, so a grain of salt is in order), that suggests that the aggressive wound and large area of damage from some spider bites is not due to the spider's venom but due to the flesh-eating bacteria on the spider's fangs, and that the bacteria is injected along with the venom. That seems somewhat logical since the amount of venom injected is tiny.

So, a couple of weeks ago, as I was working at the computer, I idly scratched at an itch on my right index finger near the knuckle. Whoa! A piece of skin about 1/4" by 1/2" came right off and underneath was the telltale sign of a Brown Recluse bite: raw, red exposed flesh, somewhat bumpy, itchy, oozing plasma, etc. etc. I had some activated charcoal powder and herbal extract liquid from a "Brown Recluse Bite Kit" that I had ordered years before. The kit's instructions said to mix up a poultice and apply to the bite site, replacing the poultice several times a day. The charcoal mix WILL work to draw out the venom, but it is quite messy and somewhat slow. I decided to try the Sodium Bentonite approach touted by several websites. I jumped up on Amazon and used my Prime membership to order the Majestic Pure Sodium Bentonite Clay powder and a 2 oz. bottle of Colloidal Silver (natural anti-biotic) to mix with the clay to make a poultice, for a total of only about 20 bucks. In just a couple of days I had the goods, mixed up a batch of clay + silver solution (looks like grayish-green mud), and applied it to the bite site. As with the charcoal poultice, I washed the bite with soap & water, cleaned it with hydrogen peroxide, and applied fresh poultice and a Band-Aid several times a day. In just three days, the wound was very much improved - shrinking in size, less oozing, less redness, and notably faster healing than with the charcoal. After 12 days the bite site was completely closed over - no more oozing, no itching, and not red but only slightly pink. I'm convinced! Sodium Bentonite clay will be in my medicine cabinet from now on.

Some people may be wondering why I didn't go to my doctor. I DID see my doctor the first time I was bitten years ago. He told me that medical science doesn't really have a good treatment for festering spider bites, other than to prescribe pain killers and surgically excise the rotting flesh, as was done for my son. As for me, I'll use the clay + silver treatment whenever I can.

I will leave positive plus feedback on Amazon this weekend when I have more time. review_headline: The cheap perfume smell is just too strong
review_body:
[Good]

It works. It does slightly improve wrinkled skin.

It's not shiny.

The cost is reasonable.

[Bad]

I do not have a strong sense of smell. I currently have a tough time detecting rubbing alcohol from an open bottle, yet this moisturizer's smell is just too strong even for me to use during the day and even at night unless you sleep alone. When people buy this product, they aren't buying a fragrance, let alone a cheap one with a really pungent odor. The only thing that super, strong fragrance does is cheapen the product as well as the people wearing it.

It's in a jar instead of a tube. The jar may be more aesthetically pleasing but a tube is just more practical.

[Verdict]

There are other creams that are just as effective without the crazy, strong nasty odor.

review_headline: Great oil, does exactly what it is supposed to.
review_body:
Quality of oil appears to be high, it is a very light yellow/brown, has no odor at all. I have been using it in a facial cleansing oil I make. I also use it for carrier oil for essential oils at times. The price is right for the size of the bottle and is a good value. The only reason I am knocking this down to 4 stars is not the oil or quality if it at all. During shipping the bottle cap came loose and the inside the bag it was in was a wreck. The oil had soaked off part of the label. It was sealed in a plastjc bag by itself so nothing else was hurt in my order. Would I reorder again? Yes I would, I understand a cap can come loose. The oil itself is great, Made in USA, cold pressed and Hexane free.

I have a few other uses for this oil. I make a home made flax seed hair gel for extremely curly hair. I made a batch yesterday and it worked wonderful! Worked great as cuticle oil. I havn't used it yet for feet, but it should work great for pedicures also, a few drops in warm water for a soak. I have a little really itchy dog and have tried everything, ans short of steroids nothing helps and she is to old for that anymore so i had ti find alternative ways to combat this problem. I now mix oil in an oatmeal conditioner, I use tea tree, almond, grapeseed, jojoba or coconut usually and add 2 teaspoons to a couple ounces of conditioner add a little water and use it as a rinse and she doesn't itch to bad for a couple days.

Disclosure: I received this product on a promotional discount for my honest review and they are 100% my own opinions. I received no monitory compensation and I am not required to give a good review. I am also not associated with the seller in any way. This disclosure is in accordance with Federal Trade Commissionâs 16 CFR, Part 255: Guides Concerning the Use of Endorsements and Testimonials in Advertising. I try to do my reviews honest with the pros and cons I can see myself in a product from use, and with facts that a potential customer might find useful.l.

review_body: I"m loving this product.  Another 5 stars for Sublime Beauty! I could go into all of the science of it but I would probably mess something up in translation...so read the product description to better understand it.  All I know is that it works!  I've noticed a huge difference in my fine lines, my husband has noticed, my Dad even noticed (and he's completely oblivious...I even put pink peek-a-boo's in my hair back in October and he STILL hasn't mentioned it...I have black hair people). review_headline: Body Merry Retinol Surge Moisturizer Review
review_body:
Body Merry has been a guest over here in the past and always welcomed! Like you don't need to call before you arrive type of guest :) and it's because I really enjoy using their products. They work and who doesn't like using stuff that shows results because my beauty regimen is not just for fun......I'm sort of on the run from the tick-tock clock of time. I enjoy the memories with people and experiences, just don't wrinkle me!

I was sent Body Merry's Retinol Surge Moisturizer. It's an all-in-one product that can be used by itself as a last layer application or you can amp your routine by using a serum and then a thin layer of Body Merry's Surge Moisturizer. The product offers:

2.5% Retinol in a cream form
Hyaluronic Acid
Vitamin E
Vitamin B5
Green Tea

Ingredients (as listed on website): Organic Aloe Vera, Organic Sunflower Oil, Palm Oil, Pentylene Glycol, Phospholipids, Retinol, Polysorbate 20, Potassium Phosphate, Tocopheryl (Vitamin E), Plant Derived Hyaluronic Acid, Glyceryl Stearate, Cetyl Alcohol, Stearic Acid, Kosher Vegetable Glycerin, Organic Jojoba Oil, Wildcrafted Green Tea, Wildcrafted Propolis, Shea Butter, Panthenol (Vitamin B5), Phenoxyethanol, Ethylhexyl Glycerin, Xanthan Gum, Citric Acid.

The moisturizer really covers everything from giving you an instant boost from the green tea, uses Aloe Vera versus water as it's base and you have nourishing agents like Shea Butter, Jojoba oil and Vitamin E. Body Merry goes one step further by making sure their Hyaluronic acid is derived from plants and let us not forget the major player here, the 2.5% percentage of retinol. The product is all packed in a pump action bottle, so no air, light or even bacteria can easily come in contact. That to me is insurance on your purchase!

Application:
A one pump serving was enough for me to cover the areas I wanted to treat on my face because I have combination skin and that means some areas get more moisturizer than others. I then had enough to treat my neck and chest area because people tend to over focus on the face when the rest of your body can also show aging. I applied the product under make-up and never had issues of my foundation not looking right hours later or even problems with blending. The acids in the moisturizer keep everything in check. Make sure to use SPF (even though you should already be) because retinol products may make skin sensitive to the sun, plus why damage the skin you are trying to take care of.

Verdict:
Like with all of Body Merry's products so far, I am happy with the results and the price point. I got tired of OTC products not declaring the percentage of retinol in their products and just taking their word that there was even a significant amount to make a difference. I might as well squeeze a bottle down the sink if it's not going to work! With Body Merry products, everything is forthcoming and no proprietary blends to hide behind. Body Merry tells you what you are getting, how it's going to work and what to expect, plus goes beyond and adds a satisfaction guarantee. No hassles and I like exchanges like that because the beauty world should not be complicated. We all want to look our best, we all can't afford and/or don't want to undergo surgery, so we just want stuff that works. Body Merry's stuff works and that is something I (and my skin) truly appreciates.

product_title: Philips Sonicare Powerup Battery Toothbrush
review_body:
I have had two Sonicare brushes over a 10 year span. This would be my third. This is not like my prior ones. The prior ones (even the cheaper $30 non-rechargeable one) oscillated only the head, and the frequency was so high it caused water and toothpaste to foam up. They worked very, very well.

This model is just a vibrating toothbrush. If feels like they just stuck one of those cheapo vibrator modules on it that they stick on razors and every other thing on the planet these days. The frequency is quite low and the whole thing vibrates (not just the head) which wastes energy. I do not recommend this brush if you are coming from better Sonicare brushes as you may be disappointed as I am. I am surprised Philips would even put the Sonicare name on this brush as it cheapens the brand.

review_headline: Exfoliates Skin so your serums and creams penetrate and work better
review_body:
I have been using this facial brush for a few weeks now, and here is what I love about it. It comes nicely packaged, and includes a cleansing brush, exfoliating brush, body brush, and pumice stone. You will need four AA batteries to get started, but other than that, set up is easy and simple. You can choose your favorite gentle facial cleanser, and choose which attachment you want to use.

I prefer to use a Vitamin C cleanser for my face, and either shower gel, or skin cleanser for other parts of your body. I am hoping that with continued use, my face will appear smoother, and my skin tone will be more even. I have heard great things about these Skin Brush Systems, and think it's a great way to get a gentle, yet deeper clean, and exfoliation.

This system also treats acne scars, fine lines and wrinkles, discoloration like sun spots, hyper-pigmentation and melasma, and rough, dry skin.

I would highly recommend this to anyone looking for an affordable, and gentle way to take care of your skin. This product appears to be high quality, and won't take up too much room in your bathroom drawer either. I did receive this product at a discount in exchange for my honest, unbiased review.

review_headline: I have used it for months and I love it.
review_body:
I have been using this for a couple of months now and so far I really love it. My skin lady who I love recommeneded me this product and boy was she right.
Since my skin type is more oily it is best for me to use a gel like moisturizer because it is not too cremey. When applying this it feels really good and working it into your skin is really easy to do without having to put a lot on and over moisturizing thus making your skin oily.

All you have to do is put a little on and it can stretch across your entire face. Which is great for ensuring you do not over do it and to make this product last months, which is an extra bonus because of the price tag.

The price is worth it because of the high quality of this product and the fact that if you use it right, it can lasts for months on months. So in all actuality, you will not find yourself spending that much on moisturizing.

If you are like me and need a gel based moisturizer this was definitely the best choice for me that I have seen and if you are looking for a toner to I would go with this one: Yonka Essentials Lotion Yon-Ka (PNG) 200ml/6.76oz and for a face wash this one: SHISEIDO by Shiseido Shiseido Pureness Deep Cleansing Foam--/3.6OZ

You can find both of them under personal care at [...] and have them shipped right to you including this moisturizer which I love.

product_title: Eucerin Diabetics' Dry Skin Relief Body Creme, 8 Ounce
review_headline: Eucerin Diabetics' Dry Skin Relief Body Creme
review_body:
I have mixed feelings about this product - in the past I've been very pleased with the quality of Eucerin products - they do make some very high-quality (and not necessarily cheap) skin care products. I'm not sure what makes this particular product marketable to diabetics - to me this just seems to be a marketing gimmick to boost sales. I am not a diabetic but didn't hesitate to give this creme a try - winter has left my skin in serious need of moisture on a daily basis, particularly my hands which tend to crack if I don't moisturize often. I found that I liked this product best when used on my arms and legs and body, but not so much on my hands. It moisturized well, and absorbed fairly quickly on my body but did not seem to absorb as quickly on my hands so I don't think I would use it as a hand moisturizer. It helped relive the dry skin and itch that is a result of the dry winter air - even later in the day my skin did not feel dry and itchy like it normally does a few hours after applying a body creme. While the label does say 'fragrance free' that does not mean it doesn't have any scent at all, it just means they have not added anything to enhance the scent. There is some mild, non-offensive scent to it but nothing that lingers or is annoying.

I do have a concern about the inclusion of alpha-hydroxy in the ingredients. While this is included to help remove dead skin and soften, it does also make you more sensitive to the sun. While this isn't a concern for me in the winter-time where I don't spend much time outdoors, I don't think it's something I will be using much after winter is over and I'll be exposed to the sun much more. If I were a big outdoors person this would be an important factor to consider before purchasing this creme.

product_title: Jerdon JGL7W Euro Lighted Mirror with 5x Magnification, 4-Light Settings, White Finish
review_body:
Im pretty picky and have searched all over the internet for the right one. Here are my review bullet points:
PROS:
No distortion in the mirror.
Good size, you can see your entire face.
The light filters help you with makeup application.
The switch is easy to press on and off.
The light gradually gets brighter (must be the fluorescent) After its warmed up, the brightness level is just right- bright enough to see your pores but not blinding.
It has a back stand which I decided not to use. Instead I taped up the back and mounted it to my wall. So its nice they designed it to have this option in mind. Lays flat against the wall and doesn't stick out.
The bulbs don't get hot.
Lightweight for travel.

CONS:
The design is quite an eyesore. It's clunky, dated looking, doesn't match any home decor, and looks cheap.
You cant adjust the level of brightness.
The plug in outlet seems useless.
The lever to shift the light filters back and forth is cheap and flimsy.

product_title: DenTek Professional Fit Maximum Protection Dental
review_headline: it has been my favorite of all the night guards I have tried
review_body: I purchased this dental guard in October of 2014 for nighttime teeth clenching. I don't really grind my teeth, but I clench them, and sometimes if my tongue or cheeks get in the way, I would wake up with sores. So that being said, I'm not sure how this would work for someone who grinds a lot -- I'm not sure if it would stay in place, since it doesn't conform to your teeth. But for me, it has been my favorite of all the night guards I have tried. I have tried many different kinds of over-the-counter night guards, trying to avoid paying hundreds of dollars for one from the dentist, and this one works well for me. I tried a few different "boil and bite" night guards, but they were bulky and ultimately ended up rubbing my gums or tongue and causing pain. This one took a little getting used to, because it doesn't conform to your teeth like the boil and bite guards, but after a night or two wearing it, it works like a dream. I was also concerned about the durability since it seems pretty flimsy, but so far it's been great. The pack I bought came with two and I'm still using the first one.

product_title: ACURE Deep Root Conditioner, 4 Ounce
review_headline: the best conditioner ever, and I've tried them all
review_body:
Ok, I'm really confused by another reviewer's comment that it feels like they put nothing in their hair. Shocked actually. They must be confusing this with the shampoo....I dunno. First of all it's not watery, and it's extremely hydrating and detangling. I've tried most of the high end brands out there (aveda, Paul Mitchell, biolage, redken, purology, etc.) And this conditioner beats them all. I do have to say the 'old' (pre loreal buy out) purology conditioner in the purple bottle was amazing and very similar in comparison to this. However that was a VERY expensive salon brand that was hard to find (I realize that's not the case now). I think that was the most I'd ever spent on shampoo and conditioner, couldn't bring myself to buy it again until it was beginning to show up at places like ulta. They both are minty and tingle but detangle and condition like nothing else I've tried. I should say that I color my hair and live in a desert climate so my hair needs all the moisture it can get. It's long (down to the middle of my back) and prior to this conditioner, very hard to brush out after the shower. I do use this as a regular conditioner each time i shampoo (every other day) and I do use less than regular conditioners (normally a handful, crazy I know). Right now I'm using Acure's mint shampoo.

Oh ya, and this is natural! I mean look at the ingredients! Nothing bad in there!

Disclaimer: I'm completely obsessed with most all of Acure's products with the exception of the facial toner which broke me out.

I hope more people try this awesome product!

review_body: Highly disappointed! I usually love everything Braun makes. I have used their shavers since I was old enough to shave. This product, however, if seriously flawed. Within a few months of use I broke off a few of the teeth ... WITH MY FACE. C-mon, that is just cheap product design. As well, just after a year ( right after the warranty ran out) the battery started to die. I know have to make sure its plugged in for a good 30 minuted before the motor works well enough to shave. Even then it only lasts a short time. The battery is not user replaceable so after one year it is ready for the trash.

review_body: Amazing skin cream. It has rejuvenated my skin after about one week of use, and it's looking more even. Doesn't smell bad or chemically. I have super-sensitive skin and this stuff has never caused a reaction or stinging like some other products I've used (kiel's) But yes, it does look shiny when its first applied. It's not 'greasy' as some have described here, rather it's a moisturizing concentrate that absorbs with an hour. I recommend it as an overnight treatment rather than a just-before-I-go-out thing. Do an exfoliating scrub before bedtime and follow it up with a thin layer of Golden Sundrop. Do this every night and you'll start seeing a wonderful difference within a week. Plus a little goes a long way...a jar lasts me about three months. I've even started mixing a bit with my conditioner and leaving it in my hair...I swear my hair used to look like fly-away hay, and now it's moisturized, shiny and even curly...this stuff is amazing!

review_headline: it's not good for summertime skin
review_body:
It's ok. It doesn't break me out, which I almost expected because it has coconut oil in it. However, it's not good for summertime skin. It definitely needs to be set with powder or this baby will smudge and run everywhere. I don't like how it just sits in a layer on my skin. Although greasy, it helps to apply if your face is moisturized first, as it is hard to move around on dry skin. It's hard to explain. I won't be repurchasing.
Also, if you want to use this product every day or use it for a larger area of the face instead of just two or three spots, expect to run out fast. It is tiny! Definitely lacking in bang for the buck. I really do like RMS living luminizer (although it is also tiny and way overpriced), but for me, this is just one of those "emporer's new clothes" products/brands.

product_title: Philosophy Hope in a Jar Daily Moisturizer
review_headline: but it was of poor quality. I would recommend simply buying it directly ...
review_body:
I have used this moisturizer before, but when I opened this particular package, it smelled a little strange (as if it was old/gone bad). I still tried it for ~1 week on my face and, although it felt a little bit stickier than normal, it was okay. However, after a few days of using it, I noticed that I was breaking out a lot (which normally never happens to me), primarily underneath my cheekbones. Therefore, I stopped using it for a few days and noticed it clearing up. I tried resuming the use on this, but I started breaking out again.

The product came quickly and on time, but it was of poor quality. I would recommend simply buying it directly from a beauty supply store for the full price, because it was not worth saving the $15, when I have out the whole product anyways. I don't know if other people had this issue, but I'm sure the cheap price is due to the fact that it was past the shelf-life of the product.

product_title: Trichloroacetic Acid - TCA Peel 50% Medical Grade 1oz. 30ml Pro Size (Level 4 pH 0.6)
review_headline: Be careful, can make you darker.
review_body: Ok, so I bought this based on some of the excellent reviews. I have had peels done professionally but not a TCA. I have also done the Jesner peel at home but I was not getting the results I needed. I bought the 50% and diluted it to 25% because I was worried it may be a little too strong.  It burns a lot more than the other peels I have done in the past but that is expected since it is stronger. It got red, frosted and all of that stuff. I did everything I was instructed to do. My skin peeled and it looked great and I was happy. Then I noticed that all the areas that were peeled and was looking great gradually got darker and darker each day. Not sure what the heck is going on. This is not supposed to be happening. I am a Black woman but a darn near White person in skin tone. I warm others, be careful when considering to buy and use this stuff, you may get an undesired result at the end.

product_title: Feather All Stainless Steel Double-Edge Razor Model AS-D2
review_headline: Afraid of Nicks and Razor Burn?
review_body: Are you afraid of using a double edge razor because of nicks and razor burn?  Well, I was too.  I inherited my father-in-law's old Gillette Double Edge Razor.  I tried a variety pack of razor blades, which included feather razor blades and they all caused nicks and razor burn if I was not extremely careful shaving.  So, after doing some research and reading other reviews about the Feather Double Edge Razor, I decided to take the plunge and spend some money.  Well, those reviews were right.  The Feather Razor is worth every penny. No more nicks and razor burn!  It offers the smoothest shave.  I can now shave with confidence.  There is one catch with using the Feather Razor.  You need to use Feather Razor Blades!  I tried some of the other blades I had left in my variety pack and the shaves were not very close.  They all left some stubble, even when I shaved across the grain. I hope this will help you in making a decision about investing in a Feather Razor.  It is well worth the money, I use it everyday.

review_headline: Try It!  I bet you'll like it!
review_body: I've tried quite a few natural toothpastes (XyliWhite, PerioBrite, Tom's) in search of something that helped with my dry mouth.  I don't have severe dry mouth but I do feel my tea fiendish ways cause my above average dry mouth issues.  I picked this toothpaste up from the store on a whim.  I liked the packaging (:)) , was curious about neem and especially love xylitol gum...so I thought why not try it in a toothpaste?  I had tried all the other limited natural toothpastes your standard generic grocery store offers as well, so I was not expecting much.  Wow, I was pleasantly surprised and happy with Himalaya's toothpaste!  I like the taste (the neem?) first of all!  It's a fresh taste that I can't quite compare to anything else.  The packaging is good (not that it matters, but as someone who appreciates good design, it only adds to the experience), and, most importantly, this stuff seems to help with my dry mouth!  Win, win, win!

product_title: American Crew Molding Clay, 3.0 Oz
review_headline: Great Product - Applies well to dry hair
review_body:
This is great hair product. I have used AC Fiber in the past and tride this for something different. I like it a lot. It is a little easier to get out of the container, and spread evenly on your hair. It has a slightly more greasy hand to it (before application). As a result I find this product a lot easier to apply to dry hair. And ultimately that is what I use this for. If my hair has some moisture in it still from showering, Fiber is my go to, but when I apply mid day, or later on after showering, this is my go to.

Some reviewers noted that this product was very difficult to washout. Maybe it is because I bathe regularly, or because I am particularly good at shampooing my own hair, but I did not find this product at all difficult to wash out of my hair. It does not behave like petroleum jelly, anyone who says it does is an idiot.

review_headline: like a dollar and 15 cents or something
review_body: Purchased this at Walmart. I was going back and fourth between purchasing this or the Loreal BB cream, which has been completely sold out at my two local Walmarts. Finally I went in and they had this and the Loreal BB cream in stock. The price of this was over a dollar cheaper, like a dollar and 15 cents or something, so I purchased this instead. Also this said it was "8 in 1 coverage" whereas the always sold out Loreal BB was listed as "4 in 1 coverage" So between those two deciding factors, I decided to go with this one. I will start by saying if you are a person who never wears make up, or a pre teen who is just starting out in make up, this would probably be a great starter for you! I also want to say I applied this with my fingers because I was in a hurry. I usually apply things like this with a foundation or buffer brush or with a beauty blender sponge, so the result might be slightly different if I had done it my regular application way. The con for me is how light it is. After putting it on, it just looked like my normal face, nothing happened. It didn't do any of the "8" things listed. If you're going for a suuuuper natural look (aka nothing), then this would work. I was hoping for at least the "glow" factor listed as one of the 8. The pro is it blended with my skin tone very well. Good starter product or good product if you have absolutely perfect skin with perfect pores and need something extremely minimal and light. Not perfect for me though and now wishing I had spent that dollar extra to try out the Loreal brand.

product_title: Philips Sonicare HX6212/05 2 Series Plaque Control Rechargeable Toothbrush, Special pack
review_body:
I was skeptical. I resisted for a year, then finally caved in bought a Sonicare toothbrush as a new year's resolution (to take better care of my teeth).
I turned it on and looked at it, "So what? its just vibrating. Doesn't look like it'll do much. Hows that gun help my teeth?"

Boy, was I wrong.

Pros:
-My teeth feel like I just came out of a dentist's office.
-I can already see a change in color and stain removal (and I'm still using the same toothpaste and mouthwash)

Con:
- Its so much louder than I expected it to be! BUZZZZZZZZZZZZZZ!
As a night owl I almost feel guilty for brushing my teeth at 1 am, worrying if I'm waking up the house.
- I have a sensitive mouth, and while the toothbrush itself has been great, I will consider getting "sensitive brush heads in the future"

Overall this is great for your teeth,
maybe not for the light sleepers around me,
but I made a resolution to care for my teeth so folks can just wait until next year to get on that list. JK.

product_title: InstaNatural Retinol Serum - Anti Wrinkle Anti Aging Facial Serum - Helps Reduce Appearance of Wrinkles, Crows Feet & Fine Lines - With Vitamin C and Hyaluronic Acid 1OZ
review_body:
I decided to try this serum because I have been trying to improve my skin's health. I am only 25 but, after years of playing softball and long summers of swimming, I have fine lines around my eyes and forehead from squinting at the sun. I wasn't too sure what to expect but the results I have seen have been nothing but positive!

The first thing that I always do when trying a new product is smell it. This smells citrusy and is very pleasant. If you're worried about it lingering or being too strong, you should know that it fades quickly and is not overpowering. I applied this after getting out of the shower and noticed that it did make my skin a little flushed and tingly. I have super sensitive skin and it was nothing that alarmed me. My skin was not use to this type of product and it quickly adjusted and I had no problems after one week. I applied it at night so it faded by morning. This will make your skin feel very tight. That means it's working! That is what it is supposed to do. If for some reason your skin feels too tight, apply a light moisturizer and it should subside. It has definitely helped my skins health and after a month I can tell a huge change in the tightness around my eyes.
*I was provided a sample for review and I do not promise a good rating in return, nor am I affiliated with this company or compensated in any way.

product_title: Retinol 2.5 Serum for Wrinkles, Sagging Skin, Acne Dark Spots and Increased Collagen Production - 98% Natural, 72% Organic - Vitamin A, Vitamin E, Hyaluronic Acid - Puristica
review_body: I feel the same way about what I put on my face as I do about what I put in my body...the "cleaner" the better. My favorite thing about Puristica's retinol serum is the ingredient list which is full of organic and vegan ingredients and an effective 2.5% retinol. I can't say i always eat well, but I can always put the best ingredients on my body to absorb into my skin. Like other serums, the process is:wash, tone, serum, moisturizer and that's how I use this serum. The generous 2oz bottle holds a serum with good viscosity. This may seem funny to say, but I have tried other serums in dropper-delivery bottles and found them to be runny or watery. Puristica's serum is thick but melts to disperse easily across my face and absorbs quickly. There is little wait time for the serum to dry before moisturizer application. I have only used the product for a short time now so i can't speak to long-term results, but I do notice significantly more moisturized skin when I use this serum as part of my routine. My skin looks immediately plumped and refreshed in the morning, which is huge. I chose a retinol to stimulate the production of collagen and elastin so I am looking forward to the results from this natural, high potency product! * Discount given for unbiased opinion. I would recommend the product and order from the seller again.

review_body: If you are like me, you are on a never ending quest for full long hair, and then you might be intrigued to hear that Hair Rescue GOLD Plus Supplement might just have the answer to your follicle dreams. However, the question I've been always asking is: can oral supplements really help you get healthy, full long hair? product_title: Braun Silk Epil 7 Skinspa Wet & Dry Epilator Hair Remover For Face and Body
review_headline: Pain-free after some trial and error!
review_body:
I was so excited to receive my Silk-epil 9 - what female wouldn't be excited about a way to not have to shave multiple times a week? However, this was the first time I've used an epilator. So I read the pamphlet front to back and got started right away! The first time I used it, I was a little too eager and I did it on my dry bare skin - I hadn't just showered nor had I exfoliated in at least a few days. Bad idea. It was pretty painful. At first I was a little upset, thinking that this would be my only time using it. I waited a few weeks until I felt like I needed to shave/epilate again, but this time I found this very useful link:

http://www.braun.com/us/female-grooming/adviser/how-to-achieve-best-epilation-results.html

I also watched a couple videos on youtube. This time, I used it in the shower (after being in there for at least 5 minutes) and I pulled my skin with my opposite hand to stretch it out a little right before going over it with the epilator. This time - PAIN FREE! It was amazing. I was able to go up to the second speed right away. My legs were a little red after so I made sure to wear pants that day, but the desk day the red was all gone and my legs are so smooth. The best part about it, I can go weeks without having to shave or epilate again! Yayy!

And the facial cleansing brush - such an awesome perk! I use it daily and love it!

product_title: Beaute Galleria - Bundle 4pcs Blackhead Remover Pimple Extractor Popper Bend Curved Tweezers for Acne Comedone Blemish Whitehead Zit Removal Tool Kit with Instructions
review_headline: Learn how to use them first, then enjoy the benefits of scar-free acne removal
review_body:
A certain type of person really enjoys medical videos. A subset of that type enjoys videos of medical procedures. A minority of those weirdos gets into the gross videos like zit popping. I'm one of those psychos. I love everything from zit popping to the absolutely insane stuff found on Rotten.com (VIEWER DISCRETION REQUIRED THERE--DO NOT GO THERE IF YOU ARE AT ALL SENSITIVE TO BLOOD AND SCENES OF GRISLY DEATH!!).

That said, a lot of the videos above can also be educational. YouTube apparently requires that a lot of them be classified as educational, and there are several physicians that approach it with patient education in mind. Those are where I learned about these tools. The best zit popping videos do not have screaming idiots and shaky cameras, but instead have steady close ups and advice that can be used to improve your health. These tools are what the professionals use to remove acne--for good reason.

I'm old enough now that I have few breakouts any more, but I have young daughters that still suffer from our oily genes. I bought and tried these tools based on what I'd seen in zit popping videos, and I'm impressed with their effectiveness even in the hands of a rank amateur. Growing up, I of course popped hundreds of zits the way we all know is damaging to the skin and I have the scars to show for it. If I'd had these tools, I would have been able to remove active acne lesions without damaging the nearby tissue.

Since receiving these tools, I've had a couple opportunities to try them out, mostly on blackheads on my nose. It's amazing how well they work! I don't know that their use is necessarily intuitive, but having watched the zit popping videos presented by physicians and other professionals, I knew how to use the tools appropriately. I find them easy and effective to use and I highly recommend them to anyone with acne. Watch the videos or attain your training elsewhere, and use them in good health. And good looks!

product_title: ULTIMATE 8 Piece KABUKI Makeup Brush Set With Designer Case plus BONUS Fan Brush. Hand-Made Powder, Foundation, Buffing, Concealer, Blending Brushes and More. Professionally Endorsed.
review_body: Why use the fan brush as the main star of this kit to lure customers? I have no idea. The quality control is surely lacking, the ferrule of my fan brush is cut out very awkwardly, so it doesn't fan out evenly; I didn't notice this until after I cleansed the brush after taking it out when I first received it in the mail. It's bent in such a ridiculous way, so I wouldn't bother using it-was hoping to use it for highlighting. The only positive thing that I'll say about this fan brush is that it does have a great amount of synthetic fibers for highlighting application, BUT, it wouldn't deliver as well-due to the uneven cut of the ferrel. This leaves me to question if all the fan brushes were made this way, and are people just making do with this? The flat top kabuki doesn't have enough stiffness, as it doesn't have nearly enough hair as the Sigma F80 as well, so I can only imagine that applying foundation will only take more time. The tapered kabuki brush is not fun to clean either: it doesn't rinse well when it comes to cleaning (I've tried rinsing my Philosophy purity cleanser off of it for at least 4 times now), which I just gave up on it. The other brushes are okay, but given the few faulty brushes, this kit doesn't even deserve a shrug and a "meh, it's alright."

review_body: My family genes (among other things) gave me very dark circles under my eyes even at a young age.  I've tried other products that claimed they would fix them, but, they made literally no difference at all.  My only option had been makeup to cover the dark circles until I found this product.  After a week using the gel, I noticed that the majority of dark had diminished, and I didn't need to 'spakle' the dark circles to cover them.  I realize that because my dark circles are partly genetic, I'll never be able to get them completely gone, but, this eye gel definitely makes a difference I can see, and I'll bet anyone with dark circles under their eyes could see an improvement using this.  I highly recommend it!

review_body: [[VIDEOID:283d7f995771f38ec7580f5c928c6f17]] WHERE THE PARTY AT? Don't show up looking all plain jane. Add some metallic tattoos for the ultimate fashion statement! There are TONS of different designs to pick from and they are SUPER EASY to apply. Just cut out what you want, put it on your skin then apply a warm compress (paper towel or towel is fine) wait 10-15seconds (the box says 30) and pull off slowly and your ready to rock for up to 6 days. You can remove the tattoo with baby oil if you are more of a one nighter type of person. Mottos supplied the sample for review and I would like to thank them for that. Check out my demo video.

product_title: Africa's Best Ultimate Herbal Oil with Ginseng 12 oz
review_headline: My new go to shave product for a fraction of the cost.
review_body:
This is by far, the best shaving accessory I have come across. As a huge fan of Shave Secret Oil, I noticed this comment in one of the reviews. At the big Wally World, the Shave Secret runs about $4 for a small bottle about 1/50th of the size of this This product at the same Wally World was a whopping $1.96 Yep, that's right $1.96.

I immediately purchased it and used it in the shower to get rid of my morning stubble. I was totally impressed with how smooth and soft my face was after using this product. The razor glided across the skin, much like it did for the Shave Secret product, but at a fraction of the cost. I can also tell you that still tonight, over 12 hours later, my face still is soft from the oils in this product.

I will definitely make the switch.

The smell, while not as manly as Shave Secret, is tolerable. Yes, it does lean towards the baby oil, baby wipe scent, but within an hour of shaving or rubbing it in, that fades.

Definitely worth the purchase.

product_title: Urban Decay Perversion Mascara, Black, 0.4 Ounce
review_body: This is an absolutely fabulous mascara. It lengthens, thickens and makes lashes look amazing. I received a sample tube in a beauty box and loved it so I bought the full sized tube. Not for the high price here though - at another retailer. (Sorry, Amazon!) The tube is big and the brush is quite big as well. One coat takes my lashes to new heights but two or three give me really long, dark and thick lashes that don't clump or flake. The mascara isn't watery and doesn't make a mess on my face. I have many mascaras from the cheapest to most expensive and this one is among my top three favorites. I can even sleep in it and wake up with my lashes looking perfect. Not that I recommend sleeping with makeup on but it happens. I am really pleased with Perversion and recommend it to people who have short or light lashes and want really long, stand out ones. I like MEGA lashes and I get them from this mascara. It also comes off fine with cleanser or makeup remover but doesn't run in humidity or if my face gets damp. It isn't waterproof but it also is not one of those mascaras that melts down your face if your sneeze and shed a tear. Really good mascara for about $20.00.

review_body:
I use this in conjunction with kojic soap. I've been using both for about 3 years and thru TRIAL and ERROR the below is the routine which works best for ME. When I first started using Piona it made my skin sensitive. I started buying an aloe leaf ($1.99 at any supermarket) and applying it 10 minutes after I applied the cream and the irritation stopped. Be careful and only use on area which you want to lighten at first if you want an even skin tone. Also use sunscreen daily (sometimes 2x a day (I'm in Florida) and nighttime anti-aging cream

Apply to dark spots 2x a day (morning and evening) for two-three weeks.
Next month apply to spots in the morning and entire face in the evening.
Next month apply daily in the evening
Next month use every other day in the evening
Stop using and apply for a few weeks if I notice any spots. Treat spot immediately when darkening is noticed or you'll have to begin routine again

People compliment me all the time on my skin and say I look 15 years younger than I am. GOOD LUCK!!

I'm mistaken for being 15 years younger than I am all the time

product_title: L'Oreal Paris Cosmetics Infallible Pro-Matte Foundation Makeup
review_body:
I am loving this foundation. I've been using silicon based foundations for years, but even they didn't last all day. This product lasts ALL DAY most days. Not only that, but my eye liner, which normally migrates down under my eyes, stayed put- the foundation didn't mix with it at all.

I tried it first on bare skin. It smoothed out evenly. Then I tried it over a silicon based sun screen; it worked just as smoothly and still stayed put all day- even though I was working hard outside and worked up a sweat.

This product covers super well- I have red patches and dark spots and this covered them better than any other foundation I've tried. It still has a natural look, though, not mask like. It also minimized my large pores, kind of giving a blurred effect. It was kind of like taking Photo Shop to my face! The finish is neither matte nor shiny; pretty realistic and natural looking.

review_body: This stuff is simply amazing. I bought it on a whim as i had a coupon for a rimmel product and the store i was at didnt have the one i originally wanted to try. So happy i did. within the first days of using it i saw improvement! i only use it at night as it is too thick for me to wear it under mascara but just at night is working fine for me. i apply it on my lash line, lashes (i bought mascara brushes at my local beauty supply store and use them instead of the ridged one that comes with it) and also on my eyebrows. since using it over the past 2 months, my lashes have grown much longer and a bit more thicker and i have substantially more coming in!!!! i dont even need to apply liner on my top lash line anymore unless i am going for a more dramatic look as since my natural lashes have thickened and multiplied, it already looks lined! it has also worked wonders on my brows. i had bald patches and they were scarce from over-plucking them in high school and had to fill them in every morning with the pencil and powder and it was a hassle to say the least. now the patches are starting to grow in and i have more brow hairs coming in all over that area as well! i still use the pencil and/or powder to shape but not nearly as much ad i used to have too. if anything i have to trim my brows too often now!! (i am totally ok with that tho!) i also really like that the ingredients arent as harsh as a lot of the other brands on the market and that is big for me. i will forever be buying and using this stuff and if it ever gets discontinued, i only hope i find out early enough so i can stock up and hoard all i can get my hands on! product_title: SHANY Nail Art Polish Stamp Set
review_headline: Nice little starter set, but with a few drawbacks, read on
review_body:
Got these as a starter set, and as a \\"starter\\" set for stamping, these are fine. NOW.. I will say I have average (not large) nail beds, not tiny, but definitely not small either. I will outline the pros and cons here.

PRO:
* nice variety of subjects, objects, designs and \\"textures\\"
* small and easy to handle
* stamps take polish well and transfers pretty good, BUT FIRST I have to clean them between stamps for them to work 100%, (which is normal)
* they fit into generic small round stamping cases fine
* you get 25 plates with a bunch of designs/objects on each one, which is a great deal
* looks like they do have a backing on them now for support and to help reduce the sharpness

THE MEH or SO-SO: * the storage box these came in was just \\"OK\\", but I ordered a case for them the next day after I received them, because in the little square black paperboard case they came in, you can not view of find the plates you want easily. Invest a few bucks in a decent bound case for easy viewing, selecting and storage. SO.....I ordered and LOVE the \\"PUEEN 168 Nail Stamping Plates Synthetic Leather Holder Case Organizer\\" for $15.99 via PRIME on Amazon. http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00HMIPKTE/ref=cm_cr_rev_prod_title

CON:

* the entire nail designs, for example the snake skin texture stamp, will NOT cover my entire thumbnail, I do NOT have huge nails, just average, and these just are not big enough to cover the entire nail unfortunately. There is a boarder of base polish around the nail. These seem like they were made for VERY petite/small nails. I'm not the only reviewer who noticed this as well. (I included a photo of this as well) This problem is noted with every single one of the \\"larger\\" rectangular imprint stamps on the plates. They were made for people with very tiny thumbnail beds.

* the blue protective shield covering that goes over the top of the plates when you get them is so difficult to get off, you have to use something sharp to rip it a little so you can peel it off! (Which scratches the plate a little) THESE SHOULD HAVE A SMALL PULL TAB FOR EASY REMOVAL! My nails weren't even good enough to get these off. (I included a photos of this) It took about 25 minutes to get all of them off the plates.

* the edges can be sharp. Be careful. I didn't find it a huge issue, but if a child were working with them or playing around with them, scratches or cuts could happen. They have included a backing on them now I see (another earlier review noted they didn't have a backing and cut her fingers), but now they do, but they can still be sharp at the right angle.

SO, my review overall is that this is a good \\"Starter\\" set for stamping. But the lack of a decent thumbnail bed coverage, the degree of difficulty to get off the protective plastic coating prior to first use and sharp~ish edges were the pitfalls.ficult to get off, you have to use something sharp to rip it a little so you can peel it off! (Which scratches the plate a little) THESE SHOULD HAVE A SMALL PULL TAB FOR EASY REMOVAL! My nails weren't even good enough to get these off. (I included a photos of this) It took about 25 minutes to get all of them off the plates.

* the edges can be sharp. Be careful. I didn't find it a huge issue, but if a child were working with them or playing around with them, scratches or cuts could happen. They have included a backing on them now I see (another earlier review noted they didn't have a backing and cut her fingers), but now they do, but they can still be sharp at the right angle.

SO, my review overall is that this is a good \\"Starter\\" set for stamping. But the lack of a decent thumbnail bed coverage, the degree of difficulty to get off the protective plastic coating prior to first use and sharp~ish edges were the pitfalls.

Even my very fair skinned husband who burns easily was thoroughly impressed.  He thought I should make tubs of it for friends and familyâ¦and I'm going to do that.  Anything to encourage people to use non-toxic, natural products on their bodies!  The chemical spray sunscreens are so unhealthy, they get absorbed into the bloodstream, we're inhaling it and our kids our ingesting it. I can't see why anyone would chose anything other than this awesome zinc mixed with coconut oil.  The consistency was perfect and it smelled great too!  Also, it's cheap!  Get it and make your own sunscreen!  It takes 2 minutes!  Also, on a side note, coconut oil is antiviral.  I find it to be a bonus to know that my 3 year old is coated in an antiviral substance.  You just can't go wrong!

review_headline: Not a fan of the mint, or twist cap on 2nd tube.
review_body: I got this product free from participating with BzzAgent.  Not a big fan of the 'system'.  I didn't notice any difference in the whiteness of my teeth.  Not a big fan of peppermint, would prefer a spearmint version.  The one big issue I have is that tube 1 has a flip top (great!), but the 2nd tube is a twist cap. So you finish the first step, and your toothbrush (and maybe your had) is wet, and now you need to hands to hold the 2nd tube and twist the top off.  But I don't want to set my wet brush down anywhere, so either you try to twist with one hand, or keep the brush in your mouth, or put it in a cup or something.  Would have been much easier to put the flip cap on the 2nd tube as well, which is much easier to do with one hand.

product_title: Primal Pit Paste All Natural Deodorant Stick, Aluminum Free, Paraben Free, No Added Fragrances
review_headline: The Only Non-Aluminum Product that Works for Me
review_body: I discovered Primal Pit Paste (the unscented version) about two years ago, and I'm still using it because it works. It keeps me free of odor, even in the middle of summer when I'm drenched in sweat after working in the yard. The "pit paste" can get kind of crumbly if you try to slather your arm pit with too much of it. After several months of using this product (and dealing with large crumbs of this stuff falling on the bathroom floor during every application), I finally happened to notice that there were instructions on the bottle for applying the deodorant. (Dummy me.) Following the instructions ("Place the open stick on your pit and let your body heat soften it up for a few seconds.") kept the crumbles away. It really doesn't take much of this stuff--only a thin coat--to keep odor away.

product_title: Fruit of the Earth Aloe Vera Cream 4 oz. + 4 oz. Jars
review_headline: Better than most creams I've tried
review_body:
This cream is EVERYTHING!

I'm very picky when it comes to lotions/creams/moisturizers, but Fruit of the Earth exceeded my expectations - to say the least. I've been using this cream on my face and hands over the past few days, and it's really helped stop the dryness and cracking that would typically occur in this horrifically bipolar NYC cold weather.

It's not too thick, but not so thin that you feel like it's going to wear off in 10 minutes, so that's good. In addition, it lasts like forever. I typically don't have to reapply - even after washing my face.

It's a cheap alternative to crappy creams on the market, so you might as well give it a try. I love it!

I like the vitamin C cleanser. It does not have a strong fragrant smell yet it does smell natural and without harsh or heavy chemicals. It certainly gets the job done. It leaves my face feeling refreshed and cleansed while not drying out my skin, which is often times a problem for me when using face washes. I like the bottle size as well as I appreciate the price point. I like this product and will purchase it again when in need.

When I use the skin brightening scrub (3-4 times a week), the skin brightening serum (twice a day), as well as the vitamin C face wash daily my skin has become less problematic, smoother and more clear. All in all I have seen a difference in my skin since I have started using these products :)

product_title: Haircut Pro Vacuum Haircutter, Blue
review_headline: Money saver and hair looks fine.
review_body: I've used Flowbee for years and saved a lot of money, time, and hassle with haircuts, but the Flowbee is getting a little worn out. Came across this and decided to try something different. So far it works good. Still getting use to it, but am getting the hang of it pretty quick. product_title: Crest Pro-Health HD Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Healthier Mouth via Daily Two-Step System - 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
review_headline: TWO steps are definitely better than ONE :)
review_body:
I received Crest Pro-Health HD for free complimentary of BzzAgent as part of my bzzAgent campaign.

This product is a 2-part whitening and better oral health product that claims to work within a week. Honestly, firstly, I was a little skeptical because a week seems a very short time to me for any at-home teeth whitening product to work; a few weeks would have seemed believable though. Secondly, I thought it was "too complicated" to use, having two items, not just one.

Anyways, I started using the 2 step/2 minute regime and within less than a week, I was already seeing improvements in my overall health of mouth. My breath was fresher and cleaner, and my teeth were looking whiter. My mouth is definitely benefiting from this 2 step system. I must say, though I find it cumbersome but I like the concept - use one product to get rid of plaque and use the second to polish away the stains and whiten your teeth.

Both toothpastes taste great. Also these don't cause any sensitivity in teeth or gums.

All and all I have to say it is very effective, and performs as it claims. With Crest Pro-Health HD 2-step toothpaste system, Crest ushers in new era of toothpaste for a healthier mouth and whiter smile. I am sold on Crest Pro Health HD, and I definitely recommend it!
#BzzAgent #HealthyObsession #Sponsored #GotItFree

product_title: Purederm Exfoliating Foot Mask - Peels Away Calluses and Dead Skin in 2 Weeks!
review_headline: Very impressed....I have lots of dead skin build up on my feet
review_body:
I started using this product Aug.19. Nothing began to happen until today. I soaked my feet in Epsom salt & alcohol (small amount of both) for about 35-40 minutes. As I was soaking my feet, I began to see the water getting cloudy. Took my foot out the tub and seen the dead skin beganing to peel off (day 1 of peel Aug. 23). I know that if this is just day 1 of peel I can only imagine what next week peeling will look like.

I have lots of dead skin build up on my feet, and was starting to think I would need to use a 2nd foot mask to get the ball rolling. After today I see that one is all I need for now. The product arrived a day before it was suppose to and was nicely packaged. I will be ordering more of these (for friends and family). I will do another update in a week or so. I HIGHLY RECOMMEND THIS PRODUCT!!!:)

product_title: Gillette Fusion Bundle
review_headline: The best a man can get???
review_body:
I received this kit from Bzzagent to review. I shave my face about 1-2 a week but I shave my head almost every day. I've used Gillette, Dollar Shave Club and Harry's recently (as well as an electric shaver, but I won't compare that). Here are my thoughts based on my usage:

Pros:
Excellent feel in the hand
Comfortable shave
No knicks or cuts
The detail trimmer is great for getting under my nose and behind my ears
Very close shave on my face

Cons:
Relatively expensive
Not the closest shave on my head. In fact, I found myself having to go over the same spots multiple times to get a close shave

Conclusion:
If you just shave your face, then this is a great razor. It's expensive though compared to DSC and Harry's and I think that Harry's gives a slightly better shave, though it doesn't have a detail blade. If it did, the Harry's would win hands down in my opinion, especially at half the price.

product_title: H2Ocean 4oz Piercing Aftercare Spray
review_headline: The best stuff for your piercing!
review_body: I got my ears pierced at Claire's and Hey at the time I was not very educated on aftercare or piercings in general. (DO NOT GET PIERCED AT CLAIRE'S, they have no training except maybe an instructional video, and guns aren't sanitary). I was pierced with sterling silver (not a correct metal to be pierced with!!) and was handed the claire's aftercare product. After about a week my ears were bloody, then it escalated to pus & swelling and I had no idea what was wrong. I babied the piercings and they were just getting worse. This product saved my piercings, after even a day there was a major improvement. A few days in and pus was gone, and a week or two later they were perfectly healed. I started going to a professional piercing place for my navel and lip piercing, and my piercer states that this is the best product on the market. It's easy to use, just spray and go. I like to spray alot so that the piercing gets soaked. It will not likely cause anyone any sort of irritation, its extremely gentle. I usually get an allergic reaction from everything I use, but not this. I swear it speeds up healing time. People I know have gotten the worst reactions from unprofessional piercing and aftercare advice, and I always recommend them this product to fix whatever problems they have, and it never fails! I Plan to get more future piercings and I'll need more bottles of this stuff, I pair this with sea salt soaks and I have the perfect aftercare.

product_title: Isehan Kiss Me heroine make | Mascara | Long & Curl & SUPER WATER PROOF Mascara
review_headline: Eyelashes stay curled all day!!! (Isehan Kiss me heroine mascara)
review_body: Amazing hold!  My eyelashes stay curled all day.  It's possible to get some curl without using a curler and just using the mascara wand to push them up, but the results are far more impressive if you curl them first.  I attached a pic of my lashes before and after - sorry about the poor resolution.  I think you can still get a good idea of the curl. (FYI - I use the method where you rotate the curler until it's parallel to the floor.)  They stayed that way for at least 12 hours (most mascaras straighten my lashes back out regardless of what the formula is). I also took a nap and slept on my face - that usually kills all my makeup but my lashes looked the same. A few tips - It dries fast so you need to separate and straighten your lashes quickly if they got crooked or crossed when you curled them.  Also, I'm used to doing multiple swipes to build volume but I haven't been able to do more then 2 swipes with this. I haven't tried layering a volume mascara over it.  I can see fibers on the brush so I think it aids in lengthening a little but my lashes are a good length to start with (just light) so it's hard to tell.  I didn't realize this is waterproof and it's been a challenge to remove.  It's the only mascara I've ever needed to work at removing.  I had the most success with DHC oil cleanser then Maybelline waterproof makeup remover.  (What didn't work was regular Maybelline, Purpose cleanser, Sheseido makeup remover and The Body Shop makeup remover.  Vaseline helped but it took a lot of gentle massaging and there was still a lot left.)  I will definitely order this again.  It took a little while to get to me but it showed up weeks before the projected date and is worth the wait.

product_title: Bar Soap, African Blk with Al, 5 oz
review_body: I like it... a lot! I usually buy the Claus Porto soap(s) because they're long lasting, great scent and mild... but cost more. Was on the hunt for more soap and and saw the Nubian Heritage African Black soap listed, and decided to try it.    First off- it's a great deal for 6 bars of great soap.     It is also very mild... a friend taught me a trick, just touch the tip of your tongue to any wet bar of soap. Most commercial/corporate soaps will make it tingle, or burn, or leave a bad aftertaste from that small contact. This soap... nothing. No tingle, no lingering taste or burn at all.    I enjoy the scent. Unusual, but that is something I look for. When I first got my shipment, the 5 bars were wrapped in a sealed plastic bag inside a paper mailing envelope. The scent seemed very strong... I could easily smell it inside the two unopened packages. I thought that I would be returning it if it was that strong. After un-wrapping, the smell quieted down (overnight) until now it's not overpowering at all, even wet in the shower. After showering, just a hint remains... at least to me.    Doesn't leave my skin with that dry, no oils left (at all) on your skin feeling common to most bar soaps. I shaved with it, and worked wonderfully. No irritation and made the razor just glide.    Will have to wait and see how long it lasts. One reason I buy Porto soap is because it is hard milled 7 times. Which means they run the finished soap thru rollers, compressing it and removing any voids or air 7 times. This makes the soap last a lot longer and not just melt away in the shower. Which makes Claus Porto soaps a reasonable price for how long they last.    Plan on giving my friends a bar or two for their enjoyment and feedback.    If it regrows the hair on my head I'll give a 5 star rating.

I tried many brands of sunscreens for my face and always ended up with "prickly skin".  Paula's Choice Hydralight is the first sunscreen that doesn't irritate my skin at all!  It also keeps me from burning in the sunshine.  It takes a few minutes to really absorb but I absolutely love it and wear it under my makeup almost everyday in the spring/summer.

product_title: Acnefree Drying Lotion, 1 Ounce
review_body:
This works well enough for that occasional blemish. One does have to wear it overnight and then wash one's face in the morning (to remove the dried-on product). For some, this may not be an option (I know that my dermatologist is adamant about not washing my face in the morning if I washed it at night). However, for a teen, this may an option (especially, if that teen merely suffers from a stray blemish once in a while).

This is not intended for those with severe break-outs. In that case, the Proactive line is phenomenal. This drying lotion is a nice addition to your medicine cabinet for that "skin emergency."

review_headline: The Argan Oil I Paid For
review_body: My first Argan oil. I was messing around with a bump below my eye and totally stretched out the skin (I so know better, too) so the skin was so much baggier and wrinkled compared to the other eye after so I got the derma roller for that. I have used the derma roller under my eyes 2 times without anything except my regular creams.  Recently, I got the oil. The first night when I applied the oil (not after rolling btw), I rubbed in more than 3 drops on my face as it seemed my skin was super dry and left it on over night. I woke and my skin was noticeably smoother under my eyes and so was my whole face. I keep looking in the mirror through out the day and yep, still smooth. I used it as a toner and used only 2 drops. My skin looks very supple and does well under my make up. I did not get this for free. I really love the results so far and hope to keep them. It's hard to say if the results of the oil would be the same without rolling. I'm 44.

I contacted the seller and they sent me timer knob where the problem was from the inside of the hood. I tried to contact them again and they discontinued their cellphone. review_body: This is a very nice, well made sleeping mask.  My only complaint concerns the totally unnecessary dual ear plug loops sewed into the head strap. First of all, I did not need nor want the cheap, pliable ear plugs, but since they came with the mask I was stuck with them. They are basically junk and probably an afterthought to increase the value (or the price) of the mask.  What surprised me was that the cheap ear plugs came with two holders sewn into the head strap of the mask.  Those holders make the mask very uncomfortable when you are lying on that side. They might have been useful if the ear plugs were of better quality or the holders were made of softer material. I will probably take a pair of scissors and cut them off.

product_title: * Discontinued * Beard Oil Tube
review_headline: Received item for free to review--Now I am hooked and will buy for years to come.
review_body:
Note: I received this product for free to review. I review all products as if I paid full price for them.

I am an Asian male and honestly cannot really grow a full beard as well as my facial hair-gifted friends from other ethnic backgrounds. I would never have thought to bought this product by myself...After getting contacted to review this product, I read the reviews on this page and decided to give this product a shot as it seems many people use this off-label quite successfully when they do not have full beards.

I usually need to shave everyday, because my facial hair is very sharp and would easily irritate my skin if I do not shave it. Sometimes I am lazy or running late and would prefer to not shave, especially if I know I do not really need to be clean-shaven for work that day. However, I always would inevitably shave just to avoid irritation.

For the last few days, knowing I do not need to look super professional at work, I decided to just give it a shot and not shave for a few days. Instead I decided to use this beard oil. This beard oil is amazing! I used to be all irritated and red by the second day, even with the use of several facial moisturizers and lotions. This beard oil seems to beat all the facial moisturizers/lotions I used because it actually SOFTENS the hair!

No, I am not going to grow a beautiful beard anytime soon and start looking like a rugged Chinese cowboy...but at least I can grow stubble for a few days without worrying about irritation. (I still will shave every few days though just because I need to look professional.)

This free bottle I received will last me for a long time (I'd guess 6 months or so), but I will definitely not hesitate in spending $8.99 for another bottle when I need to.

product_title: Henna Maiden Hair & Eyebrow Color: 100% Natural & Chemical Free
review_body: This henna made my hair look fantastic! My hair is permed, dyed and highlighted. After a summer of working in the garden it was bleached, dry and rough. I decided to look for an alternative to dye and highlights. I'm so glad I found Henna Maiden. I ordered using Amazon prime same day and had the product that evening. Henna Maiden come with the henna, gloves, plastic cap and instructions in the package. I added a teaspoon of salt as suggested in the direction for a deeper color and about a cup and a half of hot water. The one packet of Henna Maiden was more than enough for my neck length, fine hair. I left it on for 3 hours under a heating cap. It took about 15 minutes to rinse out with conditioner. After I dried my hair - WOW! It looked thicker, had a little shine and was much smoother and soft to the touch. The color is slightly darker than I expected and darker than the picture online. It's still lovely. Next time, I'll forgo the salt or try the light brown.

product_title: Bed Head Men Matte Separation Wax 3 Oz (gold Packaging)
review_headline: Best hair product to style your hair that you will ever find..
review_body:
I have been searching everywhere for a hair product (wax, gel, etc) that will give me that messy hair, out of bed look without making my hair look dry or shiny. After I gave Bed Head a try, the search is over.

After applying this to my hair, my hair still has volume and the natural look. If that is what you are looking for, then this will give you the hold and appearance that you're seeking.

It is more than strong enough to style your hair, and it does not leave your hand filled with your hair that has fallen out. Also, it smells nice. I put this on at 6:30am and by the end of the day (10:00pm), it is still strong as when I first applied it.

I highly recommend this product. The size may seem small, but you do not need to use a lot of wax to style your hair. One container should last you at least 2 months. I have been using it for a month and I am not even half way through the container.

review_headline: Found the fix for richness and depth....
review_body: Used on its own, even 4 layers it does not reach the depth of the original regular non uv/led polish. However, I will give you the secret I learned in error. I was going to do a playful french mani with a base of sheer gold instead of pink and changed my mind. I only did one thumb and did not want to clean it off, it was so sheer, i didnt think it would make a bit of difference. I painted over my thumb with two layers of ruby pumps and one top coat of pink gel ultra topcoat. I did my other unfinished nails as directed. The difference is unbelievable. The other fingers are cool and sparkly even playful. But the thumb?! The depth, the richness, the inner glow, its not cool at all, just rich and warm. My new red will always begin with a base of sheer gold!

product_title: Comfy Towels Microfiber Salon Spa Black Towels - 29" x 16"
review_headline: A Great Towel for Quick Drying!
review_body:
I often shower right before work and hate going in with my hair still wet. Comfy Towels microfiber salon towels help dry my hair quicker than I thought a towel could!

Microfiber is great for cleaning and drying my car, but I never thought it would work well for my hair! The same moisture-wicking qualities I enjoy in my car towel are at play here and this towel literally sucks the water out of my strands. This towel is so soft and the perfect size to throw over my shoulder on my way into the shower.

This towel does require a bit of upkeep, but in my opinion it's nothing extraordinary. By running it through the washing machine alone at first like the instructions suggest I was able to deal with the dye running as other reviewers have mentioned. These towels are best kept together with other black microfiber items in the wash, which is proper laundry technique in the first place.

I am very impressed in the quality I found in my Comfy Towel microfiber salon towel! I did receive a sample of this product but price doesn't change how absorbent it is, nor does it effect my review,

product_title: 42 BEES Slant Tip Stainless Steel Tweezers
review_body:
These are meant for eyebrows, I know. I got them specifically for my wife to use to that end and to occasionally sneak using myself since I sometimes get "old man brow" with that one long, stray, weird-colored hair. I'd appreciate if you'd keep that bit quiet.

Anyway, so far, these tweezers have been used by my wife as directed, by myself in secret, and to remove splinters from our kids' hands and feet. We also used them to pull a cat's claw from my dog's face. (Don't ask)

These are great tweezers. They're sharp, but not cutting-sharp, just sharp enough to make sure you can get a grip without trouble. They grip well and offer enough leverage to get the job done. The little eyebrow comb is a nice touch too. Not that I've, ahem, used it, ahem. (Remember our deal)

Note: I received these at a deeply discounted price in return for a review. This review is my honest assessment.

product_title: Exclusive By DS Laboratories Spectral F7 Efficacy Booster Agent 60ml/2oz
review_body:
I had n excellent hair tranplant about 10 years ago . 4 years ago I went into heart medications and MOST all drugs for a heart condition have side effects that will make you gain weight (A LOT) or loose your hair. The doctor who perform the hair tranplant DID confirm that heart medications will kill the best of hair transplants - The good news is that the follicle does not die but the growth is so slow you do start reverting to a pre-transplant condition. I have had a LOT of experience in hair growth with a patent to my name. This is a home made remedy I made available to the public domain but the ingredients contain a few items (DMSO , MSM) that can affect your heart . So i was in trouble as I saw my $15,000 hair transplant dissappear. by coicidence I ran into the ASTRESSIN-B study . I KNOW how to read cautionary disclaimers and the "it is not FDA approved" and "tests are still on the way, screamed "THIS THING WORKS" So I ordered one SPECTRAL F7 and one Spectral RS. In my hair loss battles I've found that we wash our hair way too often so the fact that both products pointed out you did not have to wash your hair before use told me the makers know about hair.
i TRULY saw inmediate results . Thin vellous growth began to thicken a good sign the root (more accurately the Papilla) was being nourished properly and the the TOPICAL Spectral F7 had a very good absoption mechanism (this gets technical) After a week i can feel and see hair sprouting and did not fall flat but had a "spring" feel - (you push down it bounces back up) that is AMAZING results. Today I am putting my second order for a 4 month supply. I also noticed that a small amount of Rogaine foam will give tremendous body to the hair when you use it in conjuction with these products. So my only recomendation is to pass on the daily hair washing and conditioning or just use water but no shampoo . Shampooing every 3rd day seems ideal. It seems that this company has hit on something . my ONLY complint is that the spray nozzle seems to get clogged but a few shakes brings it back to life.omething . my ONLY complint is that the spray nozzle seems to get clogged but a few shakes brings it back to life.

product_title: Facial Phyto-Peel by Ageless La Cure - Natural, Organic, Exfoliating by Phyto 5, 2.5 Ounce
review_body:
Phyto 5 Phyto-Peel has natural AHA. It comes in a 2.5 tube. It has a pleasant, faintly medicinal scent. A little goes along way. I squeezed out a blob the size of a dime and messaged it in circular motion, according to directions. My face feels as clean and soft as a newbornâs behind.

Phyto-Peel boasts of âgene expression,â âpro collagenâ and of clearing pigmentation spots. I admit I do not know what this means.

Thereâs an ingredients list that covers three fourths of the side of the box.

Because I received the $73.00 Phyto-Peel in exchange for a review I felt it only fair to do some research on facial peels and scrubs which start in price from $3.00 so that I can help you decide which products to purchase. I was curious what makes a low cost vs. an expensive product. I never found out.

At a cursory glance online, I did learn there are more than 19 facial scrubs and peels.

I also learned that many of these products could help you survive if youâre ever stuck on an island or in a desert without food. Their ingredients are a veritable salad bar.

Phyto-Peel contains mango and banana. Other facial scrubs contain: grapefruit, pineapple, walnuts, rice, grains, oatmeal, apricot, oat and almond flour, green tea, strawberry seeds, cranberry, papaya, raspberry enzymes, sea salt, citrus, tea, tree oil and honey almond.

There's a brand of scrub called 'Triumph and Diaster Rock and Roll Suicide.'

You can also find a recipe online to make your own scrubâ¦for pennies.

I wind up purchasing many of the products I have received for review from Amazon Vine.

Not this one. It is nice, but not $73.00 worth of nice.

product_title: MY Konjac Sponge All Natural Korean Facial Sponge with Activated Bamboo Charcoa
review_headline: When I got the sponge and took it out of the package I was like, âBoy this is stiff and has to be ...
review_body:
Today we are going to take a look at this facial product called MY Konjac Sponge Bamboo Charcoal Facial Sponge. When I got the sponge and took it out of the package I was like, âBoy this is stiff and has to be scratchy on the face.â Well once I put the sponge in the water it softened right up.

The sponge is said to help with preventing and helping clear up acne so I was excited to try this as my sonâs face breaks out easy. When I first opened it up I got excited to try it that I wasnât sure if I was suppose to put any soap or anything on it. Well I read the instructions and it says just get it wet until it is soft and moist and then rub it in a circular motion. I had him us it from day one to see if it would help his acne and to be honest did not notice any difference in his complexion.
