product_title: Virilem - Fingernail Clippers
review_body:
Nail clippers? Really? My immediate reaction when approached to review this product was a huh-moment. One would be hard pressed to find a junk drawer in America that doesnât hold at least one dime store nail clipper. So I didnât think there was anything a manufacturer could do to improve upon something so basic in male grooming. Wrong! These arenât the same cute little chrome clippers; theyâre turbo-charged. Iâm talking strong, durable stainless steel, and precision sharp at the business end.

As a single guy, a million years ago, I learned that first impressions go a long way when meeting women. They are very detail oriented, and a manâs fingernails are a visual calling card that can be more impressive than a platinum bankcard. Virilem Nail Clippers are well made and very sharp - sharp enough to also do a great job on toenails. But clear the room, because those thick toenail clippings can be semi-dangerous projected missiles.

While this device looks like most other nail clippers, once you hold it in your hand, the difference is clear. It has the feel of a real tool. Virilem has designed and manufactured a high quality clipper that precisely cuts nails. But thereâs more! The rounded edge of the clipperâs lever is perfect for pushing back cuticles to facilitate uniform nail growth. So itâs a complete nail grooming station in one little device. A lifetime or 30-day money back guarantee tells me that Virilem Nail Clippers For Men has set a new gold standard for the well-groomed male. Highly recommended! A sample product was provided for this unbiased review.

review_headline: Really does have a smooth, dewy appearance - one of my favorites
review_body: I really like this foundation, and wish more stores near me carried it; I noticed that often pharmacies carry the other Maybelline products, but not this one for some reason. I feel like it looks almost like it makes your skin 'glow' a little, it creates a very smooth, dewy look. If your skin is very fair, I don't think this will match a very fair tone; I don't feel like it's really 'porcelain,' this shade is a bit darker and has more yellowish undertones than my skin, but not by much, and I think it's worth it for how pretty it looks. It comes with an applicator, but I apply it with my fingers directly just because it's easier for me that way. I have acne and skin imperfections, and feel like this foundation provides good coverage. One down side is that for me it does get oily after a few hours, but that partly has to do with me having acne-prone skin. I usually apply a primer beneath it, so it does last for a while. It doesn't cover my pores completely but it does look good.

product_title: Crest Pro-Health HD Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Healthier Mouth via Daily Two-Step System - 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
review_body:
When I first received my sample of this two step toothpaste from BzzAgent, I must admit I was more than a little skeptical that 1. It would actually whiten my teeth and 2. I would be able to keep up this 2 step process for more than a couple of days.

Step one - for me, it seems akin to every other minty toothpaste out there - same refreshing taste, same clean feeling after. Definitely does the job of a toothpaste. So far, so good. Step two: at first, I was thinking, this is going to get old really quick. Who has time to brush with 2 different products? Especially when I'm rushing to get off to work in the morning, or when I'm super tired after a long day of work and then getting the kids to bed. No way would I be able to keep this up. I started off determined to try it for a few days to see if it made a difference, with the intention of cutting out the second step after I could determine if it whitened or not just as a time saver. After over a week of brushing morning and night with both Step one and two, I can confidently say that it really does work. My teeth are definitely whiter. Even better - it really wasn't hard to adjust my routine to include both steps. I've been able to keep it up all week without a problem and plan on keeping it up since it has been so easy.
And as a plus, it has helped reduce the gingival inflammation I've had since my last pregnancy, which means no more bleeding gums!
I do have to mention, that the hydrogen peroxide in Step 2 can make it a little abrasive. At first, I noticed actually more irritation and bleeding to my gums - but quickly learned it was because I was brushing too hard with it. (I've always been overzealous with brushing my teeth, which is my brushes look frayed after only a couple of months). As soon as I figured this out though, I've been able to adjust by brushing more lightly and carefully - I actually pay attention to what I'm doing while I'm brushing my teeth now instead of doing it automatically while thinking of a thousand other things. I think in the long run, this product has re-trained my to brush my teeth in a healthier way and will save the life of my toothbrushes, or at least help them to last a little longer. Thanks Crest!y while thinking of a thousand other things. I think in the long run, this product has re-trained my to brush my teeth in a healthier way and will save the life of my toothbrushes, or at least help them to last a little longer. Thanks Crest!

product_title: Crest 3D White Brilliance Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Deep Cleansing via Daily Two-Step System, 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
review_headline: Loved it at first...but then the staining happened
review_body: I received a kit for free from BzzAgent and Crest for testing purposes.  At first, I loved this kit and couldn't say enough good things about the simplicity, convenience, price, and pain-free, instantaneous results.  All you have to do is brush with the paste and the gel for one minute each, twice a day, as you normally would.  In that regard, this is one of the easiest whitening systems I've ever used.  However, BE CAREFUL.  This product contains stannous fluoride which can cause staining.  There is a disclaimer on the product which I hadn't noticed until I got a slight brownish color (almost like a coffee stain) on my teeth.  Supposedly, this can be due to improper brushing, but I had been very careful with following the directions and even using a timer when brushing my teeth.  At this point, I'm disappointed because of how much I loved this product.  Now I'm stuck with this staining and I don't know how to make it go away.  It isn't terrible, but I definitely notice it.

product_title: Beauty By Shea Raw Unrefined African Shea Butter
review_headline: A Fantastic Product for Beard Care
review_body: This works great for beard care.  I was experiencing uncomfortable split ends and dry skin under my beard.  I started using this myself after purchasing it for my girlfriend for Christmas.  I had been in the market for something new to oil and maintain my beard, so I figured I would give it a shot based on all the positive Amazon feedback.  Sure enough, my beard was feeling fantastic and has been since.  It's so simple to massage a bit into your beard, and the hair absorbs the Shea Butter so well you don't end up with greasy hands after you apply.  A downfall of many beard oils for me is trying to get it off my hands after application.  There is no issue with Shea Butter.    Another review mentions that it has an odor for about two hours (he notes that it isn't a bad odor).  I agree it smells much like you would expect a nut-oil to smell -- I rather like it.  It's a very natural odor.  I seem to adapt to the smell rather quickly, he mentioned several hours of smelling the product, I rarely notice it after initial application unless I'm petting my beard.  I've had multiple other beard oils that smell worse and linger all day.  In my opinion the Shea Butter smell is very minimal compared to many other beard products.    I recommend this for anyone with a beard (or any hair for that matter).  One caution: Don't use too much at once or you might end up with greasy feeling beard/hair.  This is true for any oil.  With many oil products after you've over-done it you're going to have to take a shower or walk around with oil-soaked beard/hair.  Shea Butter actually recovers from this situation rather well, just keep rubbing it around and transferring it to other hair/skin.

product_title: Dreadnought Shaving Cream (DNSC100)
review_body:
Having researched this cream for about 2 weeks, I finally pulled the trigger. Upon opening the lid for the first time, I noticed a light, clean, fresh laundry scent.

The Lather: Using my Parker shaving brush, I lightly covered the bristle tips with the cream. I used my Fine Accoutrements shaving bowl (with anti-static technology *wink*) and whipped up a very sizeable amount of thick lather. I couldn't believe how much lather so little cream was capable of making.

The Shave: after virtually painting the lather on to my face, I got an unbelievably close shave. The slickness that the cream provided was top notch. I was able to take 3 easy passes across my face with absolutely no irritation. I could have skipped using an aftershave, because my face was so felt so healthy and hydrated.

If you're thinking about pulling the trigger on this shaving cream, just do it. I know the price is a little high, but this jar should last you about 2 months (50 shaves).

Let's face it, you deserve a top notch shaving cream!

review_headline: Great Stuff!!! Never stiff or sticky
review_body: This gel works great on my hair, which is naturally wavy rather than curly, but when I use this I get great curls. I shampoo and condition my hair (comb through the conditioner with a wide-toothed comb) then towel dry and apply the gel right away. It's important to put it on while hair is still wet-- doesn't work so good if my hair gets dry. When applying I crunched my hair up into curls, then use a diffuser hair dryer to set the curls. I can get two or three days out of the way-- if hair flattens out after sleeping on just sprits with water to activate the gel and re-crunch. My hairdresser taught me how to do this, works great, I gets lots of compliments on my curly hair. (My hair length is between my chin and my shoulders, layered cut, colored and highlighted. I use Goldwell products for shampoo and conditioner, love them.)

product_title: AGEbeautiful Creme Lightener
review_body: I used to use powder bleach -- no more!  This crÃ¨me does the trick without frying my hair.  I used a highlighting cap and got blonde highlights in my very dark dyed hair in about an hour -- no frizziness. Thehighlights were definitely on the more golden side than ash, but that's because I started with dark hair. Before taking off the cap, rinse out the bleach, towel dry, and tone your highlights with the cap still on.  Then rinse, remove the cap, and shampoo and condition.  I used Wella Charm Color T18 to cancel out any orange/yellow and get that beige/silver tone I wanted. Over the last few months I have added more and more highlights with this lightener to the point I am now an overall dark ash blonde with light ash highlights. Love it!  My hair is soft and swingy.  You'd never know I used to be a dark brunette.  I get tons of compliments and look 10 years younger.

review_headline: The applicator sucks, its a brush tip and takes me longer ...

Plus if your lip color wears off, which it is prone to doing with this product on top, and you want to reapply your original lipstick ontop, the product builds up and looks patchy and like little gross pieces of product/lip bits are falling off. I would not recommend this.

-I would have liked a center part down the back of the wig

-sheds a bit

Pros:
-great quality for the price

-no visible tracks
-excellent shipping, got here really quick

It moisturizes my face perfectly & also makes an amazing base for any foundation. It's not oily or dewy like many primers. It's just a really good product.

product_title: Hawaiian Tropic Sheer Touch Lotion SPF 50 Sunscreen-8 oz
review_body:
First off, I absolutely despise wearing sun block! The smell and feel are usually to waxy and toxic. However, this sheer lotion is perfect! I go to theme parks and even work outside. I put this on first thing and then again for safety purposes. I have never once been burnt while wearing this and I am very fair skin and prone to burning.
I've already recommended this product to many people and they claim to love it as well. I do plan to try their other products after I finished my first bottle!
Now as a side note I'm in Florida where we have very hot and extremely humid weather. I apply sunblock at least twice. I'm not sure how well it works for swimming but regardless I still apply it more than once throughout the day, only because it sucks being burnt.

product_title: Cleopatra's Choice Organic Shea Butter - Grade A Highest Quality - Raw African Shea Butter - 100% Pure and Unrefined - Ivory Color.
review_headline: it works just like Shea butter has for me in the past
review_body:
After using it, it works just like Shea butter has for me in the past. A little bit goes a LONG way. Will I use it for my go-to moisturizer? No. I have never loved the overly-heavy feeling of Shea butter, and I do think that it feels greasy when applied. That being said, I am happy to have it on hand to use for really dry-skin days, as well as a carrier "oil" to mix with my essential oils.

Although I did not have this brand, I will say that I loved using Shea butter on my stomach during my pregnancy, not that it necessarily helped with stretch marks (which is totally genetic, by the way), but that it really helped me on my itchiest days (which were quite often during the 2nd and 3rd trimesters).
-improves many skin conditions: blemishes, wrinkles, eczema, dermatitis
-treats skin allergies, insect bites, sunburns, frostbites
-treatments for extreme dry and cracking skin
-uses as a lip balm
-put under lipstick to keep it in place
-mix with a hair conditioner for a deep hair treatment
-put on feet before you put on socks
-apply to your belly to reduce stretch marks (before, during, and after pregnancy)
-use on cuticles
-rub on insect bites to help relieve itchiness
-apply to paper cuts to reduce the risk of scar or pain
-use as a hair sculpture gel
-use as a carrier oil with your favorite essential oils

review_headline: ... been using another brand of C serum and saw good result immediately
review_body:
I had been using another brand of C serum and saw good result immediately, but over time when I was running out I stopped seeing further improvement so I decided to try this product because of the reviews. I am very happy to see continued improvement, and it is especially noticable when used twice a day as the instructions suggest. My skin looks brighter, smother, more even toned and all around better and younger looking. I had little red broken veins on my cheeks from Rosesa which have now disappeared! I now only need to wear coverup under my eyes. Now as I'm writing this I'm wondering if it is appopriate to use this in the eye area as well? I have a relative that I think would appreciate this C serum so I'm buying her some for her birthday.

I especially like that the serum comes in an airtight bottle with a pump to protect the integrity of the C and antioxidents, which disapates when exposed to air.

I don't see any other products that this company produces but if there were some, I would be likely to try them if they were something I needed.

product_title: Organic Seaweed Powder (Ascophyllum Nodosum Kelp) - Age-Defying Natural Facial Mask & Body Wrap - Helps Improve Skin Complexion - Chemical-Free - Ideal For Sensitive Skin - Revitalizes & Refreshes
review_headline: Just heavenly!  Like a spa in a jar! ...but no where near the exorbitant cost :)
review_body:
I can't say that I've tried every Kelp powder on the market but I have tried a few. This is by far my favorite! It comes as a very fine silky powder in a generous sized jar for the price. Besides the silky powder consistency, it's pure and organic so what ever recipe you decide to try, and there are tons out on the web...there are no nasty chemicals to interfere or react to your ingredients. I've tried it 3 different ways so far. First just the powder and some warm water...the aroma is mild, not over powering at all (having said that, I grew up close to the beach so I may be used to it a little more then some so you'll have to judge that one for yourself). Next I tried as a morning recipe; Organic Orange Juice and a couple of very small drops of Tea Tree Oil. The combination of the citrus, Tea Tree and the aroma of the Sea was exhilarating...the only thing I'd recommend when using another type of liquid is to warm it up (just like the instruction said...duh! :)). I didn't so had to start the mixture over to get it to smooth out. Luckily I started with a small amount of powder so the little bit of waste was worth the lesson. As I worked the recipe to the creamy consistency I was looking for, I ended up with a little more then I needed for my face so I put it all over my neck, collar bone and down to the breast line...what an awesome mistake that turned out to be... my skin came out so smooth and soft that it's a regular part of the facial routine now. The last recipe I tried was adding a drop of Lavender and Chamomile Oil to the warm water mixture for an evening routine... just awesome...so relaxing, I felt like I was at a spa (...but, as with anything new; be sure to test on a small area under the soft part of your arm for a few hours before using the web recipes...everyone's skin is different). The only other wisdom I can impart is that even if you're making a very small batch, resist the urge to default to a small bowl for mixing...through a little trial and error I've found that a bowl with a wide bottom surface and a simple pastry brush works wonderfully...I also found that starting with a small amount of very warm liquid, add the powder as you would flour to a cake recipe...smoothing it out as you go left me with a smooth, creamy mixture. I like mine on the thicker side but you can thin to your liking by adding more water a little at a time until you have your perfect mixture.
Last, I haven't had a need to test their customer service skills for a concern or return but if their follow-up on the initial sale is any indicator then I would have to say an all-star service in my opinion. They're a small company with an awesome product and what looks to be a genuine interest in their customers concerns and opinions. I give the entire experience the full 5 stars and more! The next thing I'm trying is a full body wrap so I will be purchasing this product again.

product_title: PILATEN blackhead remover,Tearing style Deep Cleansing purifying peel off the Black head,acne treatment,black mud face mask 60g
review_headline: Wasn't blown away, but still satisfied!!!
review_body: I couldn't wait to use this product. I hate my blackheads. But I hate picking and scarring my face even more. Now that I'm older, I try not to pick my face as much. I had read about this on a social media site and of course, had to try it for myself. First off, it's really messy. If you are not careful, and take your time, like me, you will have this stuff everywhere. Yes u have to put it on kind of thick, and I reccomend 2 layers of it, just to be sure it peels off like it should. After 2 thick layers, and 45 mins of drying, I went to peel it off. Yes it does hurt, but if your an eyebrow plucker, or other facial hair plucker like me, then you will have no probs. I can't lie though, it totally made my eyes water. I was happy that it all came off in one piece. I did not see as much "crap" as I'd had liked to, but I def did see results. My face was a bit red, and dry after this mask, but nothing a little time and moisterizer can't fix. Am I blown away, no! Would I reccomend this product, yes.

(I read my e-mail or a Kindle book, etc. while under what I have come to jokingly call my "Bonnet of Beauty")  My hair is tame and curled and the curls stay in.  On non-hair washing days, I just put my hair up in the rollers, spritz and dry with the bonnet.  I also have a very large head (23") and I was worried that my head would not fit into a hatbox/hard shell type hair dryer with hair rollers in. There's plenty of room for my giant head and curlers with this.

product_title: Glass Nail Files by Bona Fide Beauty - Genuine Czech Glass - Crystal Nail File with Plastic Sleeve
review_body: Just received my nail file yesterday and I have already put it to good use. Upon opening the package I examined the file and found it to be very lightweight and thinner than I actually expected it to be. I really liked the actual design of the file. I am so accustomed to having the metal nail files and emery boards with rough texture that I thought this would be no different. This nail file has a much smoother surface and provides great results. I was able to file my nails without it getting snagged like when I use a metal file and it didn't fall apart like my emery boards would do. After filing my nails it was very easy to clean and looks brand new again. I love that it is small enough to put in a purse and the colors make it look stylish and modern.The end point is sharp and you will feel a pinch if you accidentally poke yourself however, it is not sharp enough to cut you. The only drawback with this product is that you can loose grip if you have sweaty hands because the handle is really smooth. My overall thoughts are that the product is a great investment and it is a nice replacement for emery boards or metal files. I have officially thrown my other files out and this is now my go to nail file.  ***I received this product at a discounted price for my unbiased opinion and it in no way had any influence on my evaluation of the product.***

product_title: Majestic Pure Fractionated Coconut Oil, For Aromatherapy Relaxing Massage, Carrier Oil for Diluting Essential Oils, Hair & Skin Care Benefits, Moisturizer & Softener - 16 fl Oz.
review_headline: Great oil, not so great PUMP!
review_body:
I tried out Majestic Pure's fractionated coconut oil and have mixed feelings about it. The oil is great but the packaging is horrible.

*UPDATE 04/19/2015* I ordered a replacement and this pump also is horrible. I am taking a star off because it isn't a one-off and for the hassle of oil leaking, I could get another comparable product/bottle with a pump that works.

This review will be rather short as it's a good quality oil that works in most places where you would use traditional coconut oil. The ONLY PROBLEM I have is the pump. I'm not sure if the ridges don't line up, the pump itself is faulty or I just got a wonky one but oil leaks out of the spout and the ring every time I pump it out. I like having a pump because it helps with the mess of touching the cap and getting the bottle oily but this one does not work for me. Hopefully this is a one-off and no one else has this.

Since it is a fractionated version, this coconut oil should be more stable. A tradeoff is that this oil is more lightweight which some may not like.

The scrub particles are moderate consistency, not too rough and not so small as to be ineffective, although they do dissolve quickly, as expected for a salt/sugar scrub. This scrub worked well for my sensitive skin, leaving it soft and polished, with no irritation, as usually occurs with salt-only scrubs. The consistency is good for a scrub; it is not so thick that it won't to come out of the tube easily, unlike some other brands. In the summer, this might be enough to leave your skin moisturized, but in the winter, you would definitely need to follow with a good moisturizer. This is made in Canada of natural ingredients and works well as a scrub; overall, highly recommended!!

product_title: Full Thickening Mousse Living Proof Mousse Unisex 5 oz
review_headline: I was wrong...this stuff is great...
review_body: Update: 7/30/15: I was wrong.  I admit it.  I thought this mousse was overpriced for the results.  And then when traveling, borrowed another friend's mousse.  Yep.  My hair didn't have all day volume and didn't hold my blow dry--leaving my hair looking a bit limp and wispy.  So, if you have fine hair that needs some ooompff, haven't found something else that works well and can justify it (which I now do as I eat crow and press order on Amazon), go on and order up!  I'm trying to resist the shampoo and conditioner right now, convincing myself that if I have $20 cans of mousse, they can fix your average shampoo/conditioner results just fine...  Don't get me wrong--it's not bad or awful.  It's less than okay when you consider the price because it's just not $20 good.  It's mousse. Does the same stuff pretty much any old can of mousse you can buy at your local Target or CVS will do for you.  Perhaps doesn't make your hair as 'crispy' as some--it's definitely gentler stuff--but there is no discernible level of thickening that merits the price charged.  I wanted there to be so I wouldn't feel silly spending that much on a can of mousse...but c'est la vie.  You live and you learn.  I'll just head back to your run of the mill, off the shelf mousse that is a fraction of the cost and it will be just good enough...

product_title: Tweezerman LTD Stainless Steel Mini Slant Tweezer (Colors May Vary)
review_headline: The only tweezer brand I use!
review_body: My mom used to tell me that Tweezermans are the only brand of tweezers I should buy, so they're pretty much all I've ever bought. I have a mini pair, a full-size pair, and a needle-nose pair. They just WORK, the way most tweezers should, but usually don't. They last years. The blades are always perfectly in alignment. I've never had a pair bend or break or lose their alignment. If your pair is solid-colored, the color won't scratch off or fade, even if they get thrown around in drawers and crushed in makeup bags the way tweezers usually are. My purple polka-dot pair has the dots rubbing off after two years, but besides that, they're in perfect condition. My use of other tweezer brands has been short-lived. I quickly get frustrated with their inability to grab short, thin eyebrow hairs as well as these can. Trust me, you're more likely to lose these tweezers before they dull or fail on you, and if they do become dull, you can just send them back to be sharpened. As a side note, Tweezerman makes it easy to send them in for sharpening. It took three weeks the one time I did it, and my old pair came back as good as new. Just make sure they're washed thoroughly in alcohol before you send them. It's their policy that they won't sharpen them unless they're clean, because EW, they don't know what you've been using those things for!  Like I mentioned before, I have a mini slant pair for travel and a full-size slant pair for home use, and honestly, I have no preference of one over the other. In my experience, the mini pair offers the same performance as the full-size pair in a smaller package. Order the pair you think will be easier for you, personally, to use. You get the same quality either way. I use the "Slant" model for eyebrow grooming, and it works great for that. I'd recommend getting the needle-nose (or what Tweezerman calls the Point) variety for medical needs like splinter removal and ingrown hairs, because they're sharper and more precise. But be warned: they're also dangerous and painful. My needle-nose pair lives in the first aid kit most of the time, because I don't want something that sharp anywhere near my eyes. :O  I can't believe other people have had the same problem with getting their Tweezermans stolen and used by partners. Who does that? Who uses someone else's gross tweezers? But it's happened: one day my boyfriend came out of the bathroom demanding to know where I got my "perfect" tweezers. Obviously, I had to sterilize mine and get him his own pair so that wouldn't happen again, because EW, I don't know what he was using those things for! His are dark grey and manly, and they're also new and sharp, so I doubt he'll keep using my purple polka-dotted ones. That peace of mind is worth every penny. Victory.  EDIT: I just realized since I have a brand-new pair sitting in my apartment now, I should compare it to my three-year-old pair that I've never had sharpened so you can see how they've held up over long-term use. So I'm including comparison pictures. The dark grey ones are brand-new, and the purple polka-dot ones are three years old. To the touch, the new ones feel a tiny bit sharper at the "top" point, but aren't easily distinguishable besides that. I'm also including a mini versus full-size picture. Hope it's helpful!

product_title: Julien Farel Flexible Gel
review_headline: Add volume and fight frizz in one great gel!
review_body:
I received this Flexible Gel by Julien Farel Haircare and I really like it. This is a product that my husband and I share. He has very short, but thick hair and it likes to give the appearance of having a 'fro if he does not use any product after he gets out of the shower. He is in the Navy so he has to take on and take off his hat all day long. He reports that his hair stays styled as he intended throughout his work day. He has a ceasar style hair cut and if no product is used you really wouldn't be able to tell what he is going for with his cut. He slathers some in his hair and gives it a finger comb through and calls it done.

When I use it, fresh from the shower, I apply the gel to my hair and then I blow dry. I flip my hair over my head and blow dry in that position until it is a little more moist then damp and then I stand up right, apply a little more gel and finger comb it for a few minutes prior to finish drying with the blow dryer. This really gives me a voluminous look that it shiny and healthy.

The hold last all day and as long as you evenly distribute the gel you will not have hard, stiff hair. I use it to add volume to my flat hair and my husband uses it to combat frizz-head and we are both happy with the results we get from the gel. It is an added bonus that it is formulated to fight aging in our hair.

product_title: Panama Jack Lip Balm Tropical SPF 45
review_headline: Delicious, smooth, moisturizing, and extra SPF! Did I mention delicious?
review_body:
This is my all-time favorite lip balm for the summertime. It has much more SPF than almost all lip balms on the market, and the other brands I've found that offer SPF 45 leave this horrible, bitter, chemically aftertaste that won't go away, as if I had literally squirted sunscreen into my mouth (blagh). This one tastes (and smells!) delicious, like sweet, creamy vanilla, with absolutely no weird aftertaste. It is incredibly smooth and does not leave my lips feeling dry or like I constantly need to reapply it. And since I spend a LOT of time by the water on sunny days in the summer, I feel like I'm being sun-safe by using this regularly. I can't find it in stores anywhere around me (I originally bought a couple of these on vacation), so I have to order online, which stinks having to pay more in shipping than the stuff costs, but it is definitely worth it. Yes, I am officially addicted, I can't be without my vanilla Panama Jack!

P.S. My boyfriend loves it too!

review_headline: ** BUY AND SPF.. contains NONE.  Protect your skin...  BUT.. this feels really nice and I like it.  :-)
review_body:
** Buy a sunscreen of some sort.. This has no protection!! You need SPF if you are trying to PROTECT further damage.

That being said, so far this feels really nice. The first few days it was greasy... don't panic. Stay with it a few more days and that should change for you. I have extremely sensitive skin, super large pores on my nose and chin, wrinkles around the eyes and mouth.
This isnt a miracle. My pores didnt disappear (not physically possible.. dont trust anything that claims otherwise!). My wrinkles are still there, damage, etc.. but my skin feels softer. It looks a tiny bit brighter. I'm happy. I'm not thrilled.

I will probably keep looking for something that I LOVE. But seriously, I have nothing bad to say about this, other than I wish it had SPF.

review_body:

The cape seems to be high quality.

The cons:

product_title: Neutrogena Rapid Tone Repair Moisturizer with Broad Spectrum SPF 30 Sunscreen, 1 Fl. Oz
review_headline: ... scarring quite badly and thought this would be a good product - a moisturizer that also helps even your ...
review_body:
I suffer from acne scarring quite badly and thought this would be a good product - a moisturizer that also helps even your tone? Why not try it! After a few weeks, I definitely noticed a difference - I could go out without putting on foundation and not feel like I'm scaring the people around me. My overall tone was definitely more even... however, it didn't do that much to the worst of my acne scars.

If you're looking for something that will generally even your tone, this is definitely for you! If you're looking for something that'll make a drastic change to the worst of your age spots/acne scars/freckles/etc., this used with something else will probably be your best bet.

I was definitely satisfied enough with the result to continue using this product and even purchasing it again! However, after using up my second purchase of this product, my skin started to change a bit. I used to be super oily (PS - this product definitely isn't greasy!), but then I had a really bad dry spell... which, of course, if you have oily skin, means your skin produces more oil to combat the dryness. It's strange. But anyways, this product definitely did NOT provide enough moisture for my skin when this started happening. If you've got dry skin, I suggest using this with another moisturizer or just using the night version.

product_title: Physicians Formula Youthful Wear Cosmeceutical Youth-Boosting Spotless Foundation SPF 15 - Light - 1 oz
review_body: This is pretty much my holy grail foundation. I have oily skin and rosacea, which means I have huge pores and redness. This foundation not only covers my imperfections beautifully, but it gives me a very skin-like finish AND lasts ALL DAY! I love the dropper and just put a few dots on each section of my face, working one section at a time (left cheek, right cheek, forehead, chin/jaw line). A little goes a long way. The foundation does have a slightly strange smell and the brush that comes with it is USELESS...but those two flaws aside, I reach for this foundation more than any other because of the "your skin but better finish" it gives. I apply it, as I said, in sections and use either a flat top kabuki or duo fibre stippling brush to apply. It also works well with pretty much any primer. I actually did a video review of this foundation because I love it so much, if you're interested. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HFNGc4INzLI

product_title: Emjoi Micro-Pedi PRO - Callus Remover (Most Powerful & Rechargeable)
review_body: I am REALLY glad I took the plunge and bought this tool.  I have extremely dry skin, and especially dry feet.  I have flat feet, I am an overpronator, and I suffer from plantar fasciitis AND a heel spur.  I often sacrifice a really great pedicure in terms of the nail care because I really need a nail tech who will scrub, scrape, and exfoliate away the two large calluses on my big toes and the dry skin on my heels.  Using this tool took a while, but it certainly wasn't as laborious as using a buffing pad in the shower or in the tub.  In fact, it was not laborious AT ALL.  It was a simple matter of running the thing back and forth over the calluses and dry areas of my feet.  This tool is used on DRY feet, and you should work over a large beach towel or bath sheet to collect the white powdery residue it creates (dead skin).  This comes with two Extra Coarse rollers, but I purchased separately some EXTREME COARSE rollers, and used the included Extra Coarse rollers for smoothing.  Nothing is perfect, but I saw a HUGE difference.  After the initial treatment, I think it will be quite easy to achieve and maintain desirable results by using this tool regularly.  It's very easy to use, and the results are significant.  Even if the rollers need regular replacement, I think this product is well worth the money.

product_title: Lafes Natural Dry Shampoo
review_body:
I found this to be a good color match for medium auburn hair. The product is somewhat awkward to use. It doesn't shake out well and comes out in small puffs of dust through a small dispensing cone. If you only need to cover a very small area then I can see this product being ideal. However, I was using it as a substitute to regular shampooing in order to prolong my hair's color between dyes. I tried shake it into my hand then blending it into my hair, that just resulted in a mess and poorly blended, still greasy hair.

The product contents seems to be excellent, but the distribution method needs to be refined. It smells amazing: fresh, a little musky but feminine. My biggest issue was the splotchiness it left on my scalp and hair line. The dust would settle in dots almost making me look dirty. I like the product and would consider buying more if they change the bottle format. I like the formula enough to keep it to use as an emergency back up and not it send back, but I rather pay a little more for an aerosol red dry shampoo like Bastiste that gives better overall coverage without splotches.

product_title: Nature's Gate Shampoo Biotin Strengthening Shampoo for Weak, Fragile and Thinning Hair, 18 Ounce (Pack of 3)
review_headline: Smells awful. Smell lingers on hair even after rinsing.
review_body:
Smells awful, like turpentine. I have had good luck with other Nature's Gate products so I didn't hesitate to buy this on subscribe and save in a 3 pack. I generally love tea tree products. Live and learn, should have bought one bottle at the store and then decided whether I wanted it or not. I am not sure if this is the way the product usually smells or if I just got some very old product that had been warehoused too long. It smells stale and "chemically" for lack of a better word - Sour. It does not smell minty at all. I also bought a conditioner that was this brand in a three pack (not tea tree) and it was fine. Don't know if I will feel bold enough to try a different shampoo again though without at least sniff testing it in the store. In our area, the only stores that carry this are distant so this is a bummer.

Addendum: I bought a bottle of tea tree oil to add to a peppermint shampoo, and in all fairness it smells the same. I suppose other teatree shampoos I've used were more peppermint than tea tree but this still smells awful and leaves my curly hair limp. Sorry, no go.

review_body: So far so good. It has a strong antiseptic smell to it when you are first using it but the smell goes away almost immediately and it makes my skin feel very refreshed. Since I started using it I have seen a dramatic decrease in breakouts so I HIGHLY recommend this product.

product_title: #1 Hair Growth Conditioner - Hair Regeneration System - For Hair Loss, Scalp Treatment and Dandruff Relief in Men and Women - Hair Growth Stimulating Conditioner 8oz Bottle - Great for Preventing Hair Loss in the Future - 100% satisfaction guarantee by PRI
review_body:
My grandmother is close to being 80 and her hair has just lost it's life. Her hair is really thin and every conditioner that we have tried to get for her just makes it so soft that she can not do anything with it. When I saw this Hair Growth Conditioner by PRI I knew that I had to get it for her. This conditioner is by far the best that we have come across. product_title: Brushing Rinse Toothpaste
review_body:
What I expected: paste/gel (anything denser than water) like fluid with decent mint smell that I could actually brush my teeth with and then swish it around as mouthwash. Something that would actually work as toothpaste and make my teeth clean.

What I got: water with extremely weak hint of mint.

It's 1% hydrogen peroxide solution that has some added scent/oils, but they are so weak that you can't smell it yourself. I can smell being 1" from my wife's mouth. It's so watery, that claiming that it's toothpaste is just preposterous. Very hard to keep in your mouth without spilling. All the cleaning is done with your brush and be prepared to do it for way longer than 2 minutes - and it will still leave your teeth feeling dirty.

Why don't the manufacturer call it what it is - a mouthwash. Very, very, very overpriced one.
Do yourself a favor and skip it, if you want a toothpaste.

Or, DIY with hydrogen peroxide, real mint or mint oil and make it stronger.

product_title: COVERGIRL Clump Crusher Extensions LashBlast Mascara Very Black 840, .44 oz
review_body:
Love the clump crusher! This mascara is my favorite, and it seems like I tried every $1-$40 mascara out there. It really extends my lashes for an"extensions" type look. However, what I like best about it is that it keeps my lashes smooth and separated, so I don't get those thick stuck-together lashes or clumps. I use the non-waterproof kind, but it will stay on overnight if I don't wash it off before bed, and my lashes don't get hard and crusty. I get compliments all the time on my eyelashes when I wear this!

As a note, this mascara only provides slight thickening. I have fairly thick black lashes, so I only need two swipes of this to lift and extend them - if you apply too many layers to try to thicken your lashes, it will start to clump up on you. In that case, you might want to try the purple or orange lashblast, which I also have liked, but they definitely pump up the thickness of your lashes a lot more.

review_headline: I don't like rocking the red irritated neck
review_body:
I have really sensitive skin, to the point that I haven't shaved in 5 years. I don't like rocking the red irritated neck.
I bought this with not much hope that I would use it much.
4 months in and I use it almost everyday. My wife is having to get used to a clean shaved face.
It took a little getting used to. I use the highest setting on most of my face. For my neck I use the 'white', or gentlest setting. The first few times I used it my neck would get irritated. Then I got the hang of applying very little pressure to my neck and going with the grain. It might take a few passes that way but its close and comfortable.
Great purchase.

product_title: Avalon Organics Scalp and Hair Treatment Shampoo and Conditioner, 14 Ounce Bottles
review_headline: Loved the results after first time use
review_body:
I don't know if it's too early to review this product. I used it for the first time yesterday, but my hair looks and feels amazing so I had to share it. I have thin and oily hair. I used to wash my hair every morning, because at the end of the day my scalp looked as if I had poured oil on it and therefore I didnât have a good looking hair the next morning. Dry shampoo didnât work; it looked oily like an hour after applying it. I recently started working out during the afternoons, so I knew I had to do something about my hair, since I knew it wasnât healthy to wash my hair every day, let alone 2 times a day. I started researching the matter, and found out that I could wash my hair every day IF I used a paraben, sulfate and phthalates free product since it doesnât strip your scalp from its natural oils. I casually found the Avalon Organics Thickening Therapy Biotin B-Complex Shampoo at a discount store so I knew I had to give it a try. I used it yesterday morning, and this morning my hair looked amazing, just a little oily, but there was no need to wash it again. I used a little bit of dry shampoo and it looked as if I had washed my hair again. So far, I love how my hair looks and feels after the first use. Will update when I get to use it more.

Update:

After a few months of using this product, I still love it. My hair is so manageable and feels thick.

review_body:
I've been all over the place on shaving. Got very into the good old wet shaving, complete with various boar hair brushes and actual razor blades and the whole thing, to "I don't have time for that" electric shaving to a dollar shave club membership to Harrys. My commitment to each ebbs and flows along with my facial hair.

Anyway, each method ends up taking me 20 minutes somehow. Any way I cut it, it's always 20 minutes.

This electric shaver is a perfectly average electric shaver experience. It charges overnight, it's got a little handy stand, and it shaves, albeit not perfectly. It takes you 20 minutes to do several passes and angles, but it gets the job done and you don't really have to do anything except put this thing to your face (turn it on of course).

If you want a mindless 20 minutes, use this. If you want to focus on the task, choose one of the other options.

product_title: X&Y ANGEL New Two Tone One Piece Long Curl/curly/wavy Synthetic Thick Hair Extensions Clip-on Hairpieces 26 Colors
review_headline: Fun and Believable, But Know Before You Buy...
review_body:
Pros:
* LOOONG!
* Surprisingly realistic. I've been to a couple of different stylists getting my shoulder- length hair cut to blend properly, as I would like to wear long extensions regularly, and the last time I went, one of the stylists not working on my hair (extensions in) gasped and remarked on what gorgeous long hair I had. She had no clue they were extensions, much less synthetic!
* The light brown color also matches my own natural color pretty spot-on, so that was nice :)

Cons:
* I've read that you need 2 sets if you have thick hair, but I would recommend getting several sets to everyone. My hair is thin, and one set just was not enough hair to make the length look natural on me. I suppose if your hair is already fairly long and you're only using the extension for added volume, it'd be fine, but if you're using them to add length, I suggest 2 sets for ANY hair type. I kept one as a 5 clip weft, and vertically cut the tracks of the second set into 1/3/1 clip sections (I use the 3 clip section at the nape of my neck, layer the 5 clip weft on top of that, and place the 1 clip sections at my temples).
* Does seem to tangle easily, especially when worn outdoors.
* Gets frizzed and ratty at ends when tangles are brushed out. I've worn mine for 3-4 days in a row now, and had to cut a small section out pretty much at the track because it was obviously uncurled, frizzed out, and just not blending in with the surrounding pieces of extension hair any longer. Not really a deal breaker for me, as the product is so economical that I can just order more when/if my current ones start looking worn out.
* Cheap, poorly sewn clips. Go to Sally's and grab a package of wig clips to keep on hand. I've had to replace 1 clip that completely broke the first time I snapped it, and I've had to re-sew at least one of the remaining original clips to the track lace every day that I've worn the extensions. Again, not a huge deal,as it's a $3 investment in a box of new, nicer clips and then about 2 minutes of sewing, but still worth mentioning.

All in all, I'd say to go for it if you don't like the idea of spending a ton of cash on something like this, yet still want to look glamorous and have it be fairly believable. The musts, as far as I'm concerned, are a good cut on your natural hair to get it to blend well with the extension hair, some slight doctoring/alteration of the extensions, and realistic expectations. I went into this without a lot of that knowledge, but am much happier with the product now that I've lived and learned! If it tells you anything, I have the straight version on order as I type :D

I love that it is 100% pure as some oils these days are mixed with others and labeled pure. I have thick, coarse, 4C natural hair that is also very fragile. The tea tree oil works great on the scalp to help relieve dandruff and itchiness. I also apply it to my skin after a mosquito bite. It seems to help sooth the itch as well. I also apply it to tooth aches. I haven't tried it on acne yet, but heard it works wonders for that too! Tea tree oils is definitely a staple in my medicine cabinet!

product_title: Garnier Fructis Sleek & Shine Moroccan Sleek Oil Treatment, 3.75 fl. oz.
review_body:
I was understandably hesitant about how putting oil in my hair could make it seem less oily :P. However, this stuff is amazing.

My background: I have deep brown/black hair that is naturally a light/medium brown. It's down to my waist at this point. I'm letting my roots grow out, but the damage of using very harsh developer in my hair for nearly a year beforehand has taken its toll. My hair basically feels like straw when I just use normal shampoos/conditioners. It's easy to see the damage. My hair has always been thick and frizzy, but dye damage brought that out in a very bad way :x.

I've been swapping between leave-in conditioners for a couple years now, almost always coming back to Garnier Fructis Sleek & Shine. With leave-in conditioner, I'd wash on a Sunday, be fine on Monday and Tuesday, but knew that if I had to go out Wednesday, I'd need another shower on Tuesday night. That put me at 3 showers per week, which isn't so great on color treated hair :/.

With this stuff, I wash my hair Sunday night, put it in, and then my hair looks awesome Monday, Tuesday, and Wednesday. It's soft in a way it hasn't been since before I used dyes. Sometimes I can even get a Thursday out of it before needing to shower again. I use two squeezes of about a nickle-sized amount of oil and rub it into my palms/fingers so that I can rub it into my hair. My hair is naturally wavy, and it dries (naturally) looking SO pretty with this. The natural waves are accented and controlled. It's honestly saved me from chopping 3-4" off the end of my hair.

product_title: Dermalogica Dermal Clay Cleanser
review_body: I have oily/combination skin and this cleanser is great at zapping the grease without stripping the moisture from my dry spots. It has a tingly sensation so be really careful of the eye area. There's no strong smell that I noticed. Overall, just a good, non-irritating cleanser. I use it with my Clarisonic and about one pump or a quarter sized amount gets the job done. Yes, it is expensive, but I find that you don't need to use a lot to feel like you're getting your face thoroughly clean. I think you get your money's worth. My only complaint is that the small amount of clay left at the opening, whether you use a pump or the smaller bottles, tends to harden and become unusable. I guess this is just par for the course with clay as an ingredient, but I wish there was some way to prevent this because it does waste a small amount of product.

review_headline: A Very Reasonably Priced High Quality Fragrance
review_body: Wow. If there was ever a cheapy but goody, this is it. Lots and lots of quality for the price. This is easily comparable to many higher end fragrances-- and for 4.3 ounces! You can definitely smell the juniper, Bergamot and lavender in here. I would classify this as a romantic fragrance; not at all trendy or clubby like, say, La Nuit de L'homme. Very suitable as a casual signature type scent. The projection is a little weak but you can always amp it up by spraying on a little more (it's about 10 bucks for a nice sized bottle of the stuff-- you don't have to worry about wasting it). I'd say you can get a good six hours out of this. To me, this is a perfect scent to wear for an intimate evening out with your significant other. It's pretty sensual in a warm snuggly kind of way (I think it's the pineapple note that pulls it in that sweet cozy direction). Highly recommended!

product_title: Braun Series 7 760cc-4 Electric Foil Shaver for Men with Clean & Charge Station, Electric Men's Razor, Razors, Shavers, Cordless Shaving System
review_body:
I have been using a few different Norelco electric shavers for the past 15 years, which seem to last me about 7 or so years before I replace them. I have had my current one for about 5 years and it was in need of a new shaving head. Unfortunately Norelco had changed the way they make their new heads and the quality is not nearly as good as before and with that said, I decided to give the Braun a try...

Simply put, I wish I would have changed a long time ago. It shaves much closer than my Norelco ever did, it does not require going over the same spot over and over to get those stubborn hairs, it shaves faster, and it is easier to shave (up & down motion instead of small circles). I much prefer the blade head of the Braun over the Norelco for those reasons.

Pro's: Better shave, faster shave, 3 setting control leaves the neck area with no red irradiation ever, cleaning and charging station work very well.
Con's: Bigger shaver in the hand, (Noreclo feels better to hold), louder than the Norelco, sounds more like trimmers

Overall, I am very happy with this Braun Series 7 shaver. I just hope it lasts as long as my Norelco's did, and hope they don't change their blade quality.

product_title: Eucerin Redness Relief Soothing Cleanser 6.80 oz
review_headline: My Cleveland Clinic dermatologist highly recommended their products
review_body:
Eucerin is the only product I can use on my face. I have rosacea and take a daily antibiotic. My Cleveland Clinic dermatologist highly recommended their products. I have started using their nightly face cream as well. The product came in a three pack and a very excellent price I must say. At Walgreens a single tube is often well over $10, not a good price. I have tried so many products for my face and really nothing else works as Eucerin Redness Relief. I will have this skin condition until the day I meet my maker so I need to make the best of it and deal with the cards I was delt.

At my last visit a dermatologist fellow examined me and could not believe how well I was doing. I hate the fact I will need to take an antibiotic long term, but I really think Eucerin Redness Relief makes the difference.

product_title: Feather Hi-Stainless Platinum Double Edge Razor Blades 50 Ct
review_headline: Time to Throw the Feathers to the Wind
review_body: These may be the sharpest blades on the market, but that's mitigated by them not being very smooth. I still find myself pulling and tugging at two days growth with these in my Merkur 23C. Sure, the 23C is not the most aggressive razor, but blades this sharp should not have an issue. I have actually had issues with these in my 37C too. I have consistently whipped up thick, slick, voluminous lathers before shaving with Feathers, so I'm not sure what I am doing wrong.. I really want to like these, but their lack of smoothness does not do my sensitive skin any favors. I do find that Feather blades are best used sparingly. I can get very close shaves with these in my 23C (though not the most comfortable shaves), but my face can only stand a shave with Feather blades once a week. I tried using these as my regular shaving blade -- I hacked my face up and caused plenty of irritation. They just lack the smoothness to be used on a regular basis. Personna Lab Blues are my new go-to: nearly as sharp, but much smoother.

review_headline: Keeps me dry and smelling like crap!
review_body:
I'm a strong believer that most products made for men are a superior quality than those made for women. I saw this spray deodorant and instantly wanted to try it, as I hate having the clumpy white stuff on my shirts. Unfortunately, it was all sold out, but the mens version from Dove was not. I bought that and I LOVE it! So when I finally found the "female" version, I bought some.

Firstly, it went on white and chunky the first time. Don't know why. Second time it went on fine.
However, it was like shooting baby powder into the air and made it really difficult to breathe. The mens did not do this.
Also, my underarms smell so horrible! I haven't even done anything today but walk around some, and I smell like a skunk! Again, this does not happen with the mens version!

I will never buy this product or recommend it. I'll stick to the mens!

product_title: Hot Tools Professional HT1305 Hot Rollers with Ribs and Cool Touch Ends, 1.25 Inches
review_body: I bought these rollers to travel with and since I generally only use carry-on size bags, these were the smallest ones I could find.  I have taken them on several trips and am very pleased with them.  They pack easily and take up very little space. They do get very hot so even experienced hot roller users need to be careful.  Since I need 10-12 rollers for my hair, I appreciate that the rollers reheat quickly as I replace them.  My 4 stars are due to the size/shape of the connections on the bottom, because it can be a little tedious to get the roller back onto the connector and I can see that the slightest damage to it would make the roller or connection unusable.  Only time will tell if normal wear and tear is tolerable. While I love the soft case, I am considering lining it with cardboard to prevent bending of the rollers when attached to the base, or may just pack the base separately from the rollers.

product_title: Majestic Pure Carrier Oil, 4 oz
review_body:
I've been using this oil for a couple weeks now and i must say i love it. It just feels so great on the skin. I have just recently introduced myself to jojoba oil for skin use (previously had gotten some from Trader Joes and loved the oil but solely used it for my hair). This oil is just awesome though. Whereas i've been using extra virgin coconut oil as a facial moisturizer for about the last 2 years, i have been incorporating this little baby on my face for about the last month or two. I have not broken out from it and in fact, i love the immediate glow it gives my skin even more than i like the coconut oil. Still semi-new to it so i'm not using it as a facial moisturizer 24/7 for fear of breaking out and just because i know the coconut oil has been good to my face, but so far so good! I will continue to use it. Also, I loveeee adding it to my lotion or just using it as a moisturizer by itself.

Extra bonus is the little stopper, dripper thing that comes with it!! I was super excited about that part & it makes this huge bottle very easy to use and control how much used!

review_body:
This is a very nice product!! Previous to this purchase I've purchased Lavender under the botanical name of Lavandula officinalis.

product_title: Lily Cup Size B
review_headline: Not as Comfy as I expected...
review_body:
I loved the idea behind this, but it's really long. I can't sit down without the tail poking out. Maybe other women have more room to spare, but for smaller women like me this wasn't comfortable at all. Granted, I haven't tried the compact version of this so maybe it's shorter.

I also found it quite uncomfortable width-wise as well, and removing it was a chore. The directions say to use your finger to loosen the seal it forms between the cup and your skin, but again I don't have much room to work with there. I don't enjoy the idea of digging around in there every time it needs to be changed to "loosen the seal." And trying to pull it straight out without doing that is... well, very off-putting.

I guess if you can overcome those obstacles it is a great idea, but I'll be sticking to other means.

product_title: Crest Pro-Health HD Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Healthier Mouth via Daily Two-Step System - 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
review_headline: It Works!  Brightened My Teeth in 7 days while still drinking coffee - but can be harsh on sensitive teeth/gums.
review_body:
I'm a BzzAgent and got a full size CrestPro Health HD to try and report on. It states you will have brighter teeth in a week and I found that to be true! It is a two step process, 1 minute of brushing with the purifying cleanser and 1 minute brusing with the perfecting gel. I will say that those with sensitive teeth/gums may nto like using this as the first step is very drying and gave me cotton mouth while the second step is peroxide based and can tingle or sting your gums if you are sensative. Bottom line - it works! But you must pay the premium cost, use both steps twice a day and bear some possible irritation.
A few other comments:
- I wish both tubes were flip top. Only step 1 is flip top while step 2 is a twist off.
- Can they create a senstive teeth/gums version or would that not be effective in the whitening process?
- Some feel the two step process takes you twice a long to brush and see it as a pain...but I felt it made me accountable for brushing 2 minutes and didn't feel bothered by the time commitment, especially when I saw results after the 7 day test - also this was with me still have my 1-2 cups of coffee each morning!

product_title: Philips Sonicare Xtreme e3000 Power Toothbrush
review_body: It is not true that there is a "newer version" of this product. Amazon should correct this misleading information. This battery operated toothbrush is truly a sonic toothbrush. The so called newer version, the "power up" is not sonic. It is the equivalent of the cheap automatic toothbrushes that you can buy at the supermarket--harsh on your teeth, noisy and not effective at reducing plaque. I made the mistake of buying it because I thought it was the equivalent of the Sonicare HX3351, which I have loved, and the battery operated feature is great for travel abroad. I have had three of them over about a decade--they don't last forever, but they are excellent while they do. Too bad Sonicare has discontinued this product!

review_headline: Great retinol cream, keeps skin young
review_body:
As my skin is beginning to age, I have turned to trying out new skin care products and retinol is one of my favorites. It offers so many benefits to the appearance and texture of skin and I do believe it will keep my skin looking younger for longer. I try to use mostly natural products on my skin so PurOrganica is one of my favorite brands and I have used a handful of their products and loved them all. So, when I found out they have a retinol cream, I knew it was for me.
This cream is awesome! It goes on smooth, my skin soaks it up without looking greasy and my skin has never looked better. It has a youthful glow and dew to it, its soft and I owe it all to retinol cream and PurOrganica. My skin had become rather dry and lifeless before I began using the cream on a daily basis, now all the damage from winter is gone and I couldn't be happier.
I received this item for testing, in exchange for my true and unbiased review.

product_title: Peter Thomas Roth Acne Spot and Area Treatment 1 Fluid Ounce
review_body:
This must be the stinkiest product out there. I am not too sure of its effectiveness, either. Basically, you inhale fresh air, put on this product, and then try not to breathe again for the next 5 minutes until the product settles a little. If my significant other had been using something as stinky as this around me, I think our relationship would have suffered. It smells like dead fish, mixed with rotten eggs, marinated in a sulfur bath, blended with all 109 elements in the periodic table (thus, double the sulfur infusion). Mind you, I don't mind a sulfur mask now and then, but this stuff is pungent, and long-lasting.

I braved through the smell at first, because I was desperate for a clearer face, but I didn't see any results, either.

This product is a fail. I like other Roth products, but not this one.

We will be ordering this again!

review_body:

So, i decided to look around and try to find the best, longest lasting, while also having great color, self tanner. And ladies and gentlemen, this is it. Don't even hesitate. i order a new bottle like once every 4 or so months. The first couple times, it's a learning experience, you'll realize what not to do, etc. (Tip, if you lay down or take a nap with this on, wear socks, because I fell asleep and my bare foot was up against my bare leg and the sweat from my foot took off the product from my leg in a little foot print lol)
The smell is tropical and most people really like it. The color guard is kinda green/grey so you don't really want to be seen for 3 hours while this is on, but i typically do this at night and do hmwk or clean during this time. After i shower it off, i go to bed and when i wake up, I'm golden and i love it. i get compliments 24/7. And the price is unbeatable.
THIS IS PERFECT. GET IT.

product_title: Schick Hydro Silk TrimStyle Moisturizing Razor
review_headline: I hate shaving. My skin is so dry that it ...
review_body:
I hate shaving. My skin is so dry that it hurts to shave. Waxing isn't an option because of the dry skin and cream removal products give me burns. So what's a girl to do? I tried the Schick Hydro Silk TrimStyle Razor and Bikini trimmer and I am....in love! The no slip grip offers an easy of shaving without the worry you'll 'slip up'. The moisture strips actually moisturize and my skin didn't burn at all. Shaving my legs, armpits and bikini area has never been so easy and painless. The razor gives a smooth shave on every part of my body and the trimmer makes it simple to clean up for bathing suit season.

*I received a product free for review from BzzAgent. All opinions are my own and 100% honest.*

product_title: ACEVIVI 18pcs Professional Wooden Handle Cosmetic Makeup Brush Set Kit with Case
review_headline: Pretty, soft, silky - amazing array of options. Tidy, professional-type kit. No Kabuki, but case has extra slots to add brushes
review_body:
This is an incredibly impressive brush set. I don't think anyone could help but be floored with the large array of makeup tools presented here. When you open the case, you have to actually unroll it; there's that many brushes in there - some of them pretty large! Even from my amateur perspective, I'd call this a professional's kit.

Thank goodness there's a list on the Amazon blurb for what each brush is actually for, or I'd be lost.I had no idea makeup brushes came in that many slight variations of kind. What I did was copy and paste the list from Amazon, print it out, and fold it right into the brush case. Unless you're a makeup diva, you might want to try this too.

NOTE:
There are two case and brush handle choices on this page: the purple ombre kit and the cream and gold one. Make sure you are ordering the one you expect. The cream and gold kit looks very luxe from the photos - appearing like a carry-clutch.

I have the purple ombre kit, which is more of a 'fun' look. The case has a textured pattern with flower heads, and a single strap with a magnetic snap closure. The brushes themselves are the ombre part, starting from white at the crimp, coloring into purple at the ends of the brush heads. Every "haired" brush except one has this white and purple look - only the foundation brush fades into brown. The spooley and eyebrow brush are solid black, though, and the sponge applicator is just cream.

PROS:
- Love the purple ombre brush look and the purple wooden handles. Pretties!
- The brushes themselves are very soft, and very high quality. A soothing kind of soft.
- The bristles are well seated in their crimp.
- Holds powder and liquids equally well.
- Easy to clean.
- Since everything is right here, and folds up out of the way so easily, you can keep your bathroom clean and tidy. No more scattered, loose brushes, or unprotected cup holders full of brushes.
- The large fan brush is impressive. I've never seen one like that in a kit available to the average consumer. It's bigger than my cat's paw.
- There's also a smaller fan brush, for the same kind of use, but allowing more control.
- The brush handles are suitably long for any size hand, with a good heft to them.
- A very nice flap folds down over the brush tops for extra traveling protection, and rolls up out of the way during actual use.
- Each brush arrives with a cheap plastic sleeve over the wooden handle, and the larger brushes also have a nicer 'sewn' plastic protective tip. I've kept the tip protectors, mainly because I am paranoid and OCD about my things. :)
- For everything here and the quality present, the price point is amazing! This kind of kit would run into a couple hundred dollars at a makeup boutique.
- I received this set as a review sample, but seriously, if I'd bought it, I'd be singing its praises anyway.

BONUS: Next to the the large fan brush are two extra, unused handle slots. These are a decent size. It's a thoughtful feature, since they didn't have to do that - I expected those blank areas to be sewn shut. I put a good quality eyebrow tweezer in one, and a nail clipper in the other. I love this form of consideration for the user.

CONS:
- At least with my case, the whole thing unrolls from the opposite direction I'd expect. I keep opening it upside-down. Frustrating, but not a deal breaker.
- WTF is with the sponge eyeshadow applicator? There are so many fine brushes here, with so many options, and they decided to add a cruddy sponge-tip? Did they just want to make sure they had a full compliment of 18 brushes and tossed in that one too? Does anyone like these?
- No Kabuki brush.
- The case and the brushes seriously stink. A big, gasping stink. I could smell the strong petroleum fumes right through the shipping package, and it only got worse as I tore into things. The case has a strong vinyl reek, and the brushes are infused with that reek. If you're sensitive to chemical fumes, I recommend airing the kit out before attempting any use. Even if you're not sensitive, I'd still recommend waiting a bit before use; breathing this is can't be healthy. Let it breathe. What I did: I laid the UNROLLED case out overnight in the bathroom. It still smelled for a few days, but eventually the fumes out-gassed into the air.

BEST BRUSHES:
- The large fan - feels like a feather on my face.
- Foundation brush - very silky.
- The blush brush is just right - not overfull, not stingy, not stiff, not limp. It's hard to find a really good blusher.
- One of the nicer angled contour brushes I've seen - often times these are too stiff. I feel like this one is more forgiving than most.
- Lip brushes - one is angled, one is tapered.
- The eyeshadow brushes really come into their own here. So many!
- The extremely fine liner brush is fantastic, if you have the talent for using liquid eyeliner. This brush comes with a special protector tube on the tip.

BEST USE OVERALL:
This kit is too large, too weighty, and too involved for daily purse carrying, unless you really are a super-diva. :) My sense is that it's perfect for three things:

1. To stay at home for ALL your brush needs, ever, (barring the desire for a Kabuki brush).
2. Travel needs. Unroll this puppy on your hotel sink counter, and have at it.
3. Professionals on a budget. If your job involves makeup application, you could spend the hundreds needed to assemble all this individually, buy a high end kit through a pro catalog, or just have this. Or maybe get the pro stuff and have this also, as a backup. It really makes a tight bundle, so it travels well. I wouldn't trust the single magnetic snap for heavy-duty use, but you could tie something about the bundle, or use a thick rubber band of some sort, and be good to go.

I've actually even thought aspiring painters might want to order this kit. Artist supplies are pretty spendy, and all of these brushes are well seated enough, and different enough from each other, that someone could use this just for art. Seriously.

RECOMMENDATION:
Highly recommended for home use, or for any travel that would be long enough to make lugging this around worthwhile (ie - longer than a weekend). Great brushes with a strange addition and one omission. Soft, silky, pretty brushes make using this a joy. A well done large makeup kit that also manages to be pretty.ven if you're not sensitive, I'd still recommend waiting a bit before use; breathing this is can't be healthy. Let it breathe. It's hard to find a really good blusher. - One of the nicer angled contour brushes I've seen - often times these are too stiff. product_title: HSI Professional Glider | Ceramic Tourmaline Ionic Flat Iron Hair Straightener | Straightens & Curls with Adjustable Temp | Incl Glove, Pouch, & Travel Size Argan Oil Hair Treatment | Packaging Varies
review_headline: After reading so many great reviews on Amazon I thought I'd buy the flat ...
review_body:
I bought the HSI elite professional model directly from the HSI website. After reading so many great reviews on Amazon I thought I'd buy the flat iron and wanted to make sure the warranty would be valid, so I purchased directly from the HSI. Glad Amazon is letting me write a review even tho I didn't buy from Amazon. This flat iron although sleek w/digital and light up green/blue temperature panel, sucks. It did not straighten my coarse natural ethnic hair and if it did (after many needed passes), my hair crimped and then puffed up (and this is with blow drying straight as possible and heat protectant/anti-frizz serum beforehand). Most other flat irons I have used before that cost way less have done a better and longer lasting job at keeping my hair straight. This flat iron could barely get my hair straight or keep it straight at that. I tried it on my sister's natural textured hair that was straightened prior with a different flat iron (was frizzing due to heat/humidity) with the idea that maybe the flat iron could sleek out areas that were beginning to frizz and the HSI flat iron could not even do that! What a disappointment!
HSI flat iron arrived mangled from the postal service. When I requested to send back/exchange b/c it seriously looked like it took a beating en transit, the company wanted to charge me, when I then asked for a full refund, I was told i would still have to pay for return shipping and restocking fee!! And I sent pictures to prove how the flat iron arrived too. HSI did not want to take responsibility for it and told me the postal service boxed it and shipped it to me like that and that the post office needed to be the one to ship it back to them free of charge for me. Well... post office refused and blamed HSI. I think if I had ordered from Amazon and my package arrived the way it did (looking mangled, crushed, and like it had been cheaply taped back together with a piece of tape they found laying around) they would have taken it back and not played the blame game with me-especially with an electronic item that is fragile to begin with. I had no use no use for the flat iron so it sat on my shelf for a couple months until today, when I lent it out since
HSI was the one I could care less about and was taking up extra space in my room- I don't care if I ever get that flat iron back.

I did buy the flat iron directly from HSI with a coupon, but it's still expensive for the poor quality job it will do with your hair. Do yourself a favor and buy off Amazon if you still believe the hype so you don't feel cheated once you find out what poor quality this flat iron delivers. Like I said earlier, maybe if your hair is already fine and thin (and possibly straight??) this flat iron may work for you. Otherwise, there are better and cheaper brands, sold by companies who care about their products and making sure the consumer is satisfied with the product. And even if you don't get the warranty with Amazon, I don't think it will matter as HSI will probably still charge you for any and everything they can to get out of paying anything from their own pockets. ;(

review_headline: ... gifted me a jar of this cream at the perfect time. I was almost out of my Clinique ...
review_body: My friend gifted me a jar of this cream at the perfect time. I love this product!  No more Clinique lotion for me!  This cream is heavy enough to moisturize but doesn't feel greasy at all.  It feels light to me.  I like that it has a very subtle scent (almost like chocolate) that doesn't conflict at all with my perfume.  Considering the quality of this cream, the price is inexpensive.  I know because I've tried the more expensive creams and they're not even as good as this one.  I am now paying it forward by buying a jar of this and giving it to another friend who is the ultimate connoisseur of skin care products.  I think she is going to love it.  Stay tuned for her review...

product_title: Tea Rose Perfume by Perfumer's Workshop for women Personal Fragrances
review_headline: A pleasant walk through a rose garden
review_body: I absolutely LOVE this perfume!  If you want the subtlety of roses without being overpowering, this is your scent.  I as a rule have trouble with heavy perfumes due to allergies.  I just can't handle them and many perfumes are so intense your husband will want you to get out of the car so he can open every door so he can breathe.  Yes, I have had that experience.  Perfume is an area where less is more.  You want your scent when people are close to be there, but you don't want it slapping them in the face. This reminds me of a pleasant stroll through a rose garden.  It was recommended to me by a fellow reviewer and I am so happy I tried it.  I want my signature scent to be roses.  You will not regret this purchase.  I highly recommend this product.  You will love it.

product_title: Dickinsons Original Witch Hazel Pore Perfecting Toner 16 Fl.Oz (Pack of 3)
review_headline: Has so many uses and really works
review_body:
This is the first time I bought with hazel. Had heard of it but until recently didn't know what it was or did.

It's medicinal in several ways. One, I cut myself shaving and this actually stops the bleeding every time. Just dab it over your face after you shave, if you do, and nothing will be bleeding provided the cuts are not truly deep. Also, it feels good. It's an astringent.

For my oily skin, this works miracles. Cleans pores so that acne doesn't develop. Leaves pores smaller too.

Mosquito bites? A dab and no itchiness.

Natural product - many uses and I'll buy again. Love the scent too, the natural scent as this is fragrance free.

Alexis is a complete GENIUS as a Makeup Artist and her list of A-List Celeb clients continues to amaze me!  I have done two photo shoots with Alexis at the helm and all I have to say is that I have never felt more beautiful and more sexy when I use Alexis' products and been transformed by her sheer Artistry and magic eye! product_title: Remede All Around Experts Translucent UV Coat-Untinted-1 oz.
review_body:
My skin reacts terribly to traditional sunscreen. There is some random ingredient that causes my forehead to react negatively. Remede provides great sun protection without that negative reaction. It's a bit pricey, but it's definitely worth the cost.
It goes on sheer and takes a little while to soak in to your skin. And you can leave the house knowing your face is protected from harmful sun side-effects.
I usually do it in this order: moisturizer, Remede, primer, makeup. If you don't have thirsty skin you could skip moisturizer and if you don't like a specific primer this product could work as one. Be careful with powders. If it's not all the way dry it will cake.
